Title Headline: 28 Skincare Products For Anyone Who Doesn't Even Know Where To Start
Short Description Sub Headline: As Troy and Gabriella sang, ğŸµI feel in my heart / the start of something new ğŸµ
Content Body: Shopping | | Beauty | 28 Skincare Products For Anyone Who Doesn't Even Know Where To Start | As Troy and Gabriella sang, ğŸµI feel in my heart / the start of something new ğŸµ | Posted on March 27, 2020, 18:00 GMT | March 27, 2020, 18:00 GMT | Sarah HanBuzzFeed Staff | GlossierPromising review: "I was a skeptic when it came to Glossier products all around, but I am so in love with this face wash. It makes my face feel clean without all the fake stuff that the 'lathered' face washes give you, and it is so gentle on my face! I suffered forever from hormonal breakouts (from birth control and PCOS) and this face wash calmed down all of that during ALL times of the month (if you catch my drift). Because of my lash extensions (gotta stay oil free), this cleanser is my end-all-be-all of face cleansers. I highly recommend it to everyone I meet!!!" â€”LizGet it from Glossier for $9+ (available in two sizes). And for any ~waterproof makeup formulas~, start with their Milky Oil. | Soko GlamThey're already not very noticeable (for daytime wear), but now that you're stuck at home all day, it's even easier to stick 'em on and treat your acne at first sight! Promising review: "Iâ€™ve tried so many products, including products prescribed by dermatologists, and none of them work as fast as the acne pimple master patch. My pimples are resolved quickly. â€”Anamaria W.Get a pack of 24 from Soko Glam for $5. Also available in Clear Fit and AC Collection (slightly larger, oval-shaped patches infused with soothing centella asiatica extract) versions. | @fleshbeauty / Via instagram.com, @fleshbeauty / Via instagram.comAgain, even if you're inside all day, you still need to wear SPF â€” sun rays can still penetrate your skin through windows!! This SPF has definitely stolen my heart. In my past sunscreen reviews, it's no surprise that I love chemical formulas and my skin handles them very well â€” but as always, do a patch test first if you're not sure! This SPF contains 10% homosalate, 5% octisalate, and 3% avobenzone â€” note that there's no oxybenzone or octinoxate, which has been in the news re: ocean preservation and the Hawaii ban. It's also super hydrating (hence the "serum" part), thanks to ingredients like glycerin, which attracts water to your skin. Don't fret about the white-ish color 'cause it instantly applies clear on skin. My skin doesn't feel tacky afterwards, but it definitely grips onto makeup super well. Get it from Flesh Beauty for $32. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Sephora, Sarah Han / BuzzFeedI actually prefer this over the cult-fave Color Correcting Treatment (see below), mostly texture-wise since it's lighter. I find that this gel cream also blurs any redness I have without feeling heavy, sticky, or taking a long time to absorb. I get redness around my nose and sometimes scattered on my cheeks, so this is a quick fix â€” and since it's a lot lighter than the treatment and hydrating enough for my skin type, I've been applying it day *and* night.Promising review: "I haven't really found something that calms redness but also doesn't make me break out from being too heavy, and then I got a sample of this with an order and was pretty happy with it. My skin was super soft, stayed clear, and looked slightly less red. Then, I went on vacation to New Hampshire. I spent four and a half hours hiking in 20 degree windy weather with snow and ice blowing in my face. My skin was bright red and stung from windburn. I put some of this on after I showered, and then a little more before I went to bed. After the first time I put it on my face, it no longer stung, and by morning, my skin wasn't red at all. Normally I would be red for a few days and then peeling afterwards. I am definitely going to purchase a full size of this, and I think it will be really helpful for the New England winter and beyond." â€”cayjayGet it from Sephora for $48. | Sarah Han / BuzzFeed / Via buzzfeed.comHow does it work its magic? Papaya and pineapple enzymes help loosen dead skin cells in preparation for removal, and then soft plant-based fibers act like ~micro-lint rollers~ to capture and roll away dirt and dry, flaky skin.Promising review: "Let me tell you! I've tried EVERYTHING, including Proactive and Rodan & Fields, and nothing has helped my skin in the way that this (and the cleansing collection) have! My skin is combination that reacts to EVERYTHING, but after two days of using this, my redness, peeling, and oily patches were GONE! I can't get over how much I love this! I actually enjoy taking care of my skin now because I can see almost immediately and feel how much of a difference this has made!" â€”AnonymousGet it from Target for $10.99 or Bliss for $12.99.Read my full review of the Bliss Jelly Glow Peel (#7) for more info! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Sarah HanIt doesn't contain your average ingredients either, but rather proven nourishing and brightening ingredients like saccharomyces ferment filtrate, bamboo water, algae extract, licorice root extract, centella asiatica leaf water â€” and absolutely no alcohol, parabens, or artificial fragrance.Promising review: "This essence is brilliant. The mist is so fine and it's so quick to use in the morning when I'm in a rush. Leaves my face feeling fresh and hydrated, and I feel like my skin has been producing way less oil than it usually does." â€”Alice B.Get it from Soko Glam for $24.P.S. This product was created as a result of the Acwell pH balancing toner's popularity/effectiveness, which is obviously great as well if you'd like to pair the two! | GlossierPromising review: "I am 47 and have some age spots/discoloration, as well as splotchiness and some monthly hormonal acne. This stuff is fantastic! From the first use I noticed a difference in my skin. My pores were tighter, my face was smoother, and makeup went on better. You do have to wear an SPF because of the exfoliation, but I wear one every day anyway. After a month of use, my skin is brighter, the discoloration has lightened, and even my hormonal acne decreased. If anyone has used the expensive and hard to find Recherche Biologique 1970 toner, Glossier solution works a lot like that, without the hefty price tag. I recommend this to anyone looking to achieve brighter, clearer, and healthier skin!" â€”KStern119Get it from Glossier for $24.Check out our full writeup (and reviews!) on Glossier Solution for more deets! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Dear Toilet Paper Hoarders: This Viral TikTok Proves That Stocking Up Makes No Sense
Short Description Sub Headline: If a person uses 20 sheets of toilet paper per poo, they would have to poop 182 times a day to use up four Costco-sized packs of TP.
Content Body: Health | Dear Toilet Paper Hoarders: This Viral TikTok Proves That Stocking Up Makes No Sense | If a person uses 20 sheets of toilet paper per poo, they would have to poop 182 times a day to use up four Costco-sized packs of TP. | Posted on March 24, 2020, 18:38 GMT | March 24, 2020, 18:38 GMT | Krista TorresBuzzFeed Staff | Farrah PennBuzzFeed Staff Writer | Melanie Korach@melanie_korach | Melanie Korach | @melanie_korach | I went to the grocery store tonight and still no toilet paper, no paper towels & no Kleenex. Makes me sad that the government is urging people not to hoard but many are still hoarding. I think we can do better than this. Please can we do better?ğŸ™#StarfishClub #Covid_19 | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | tiktok.com, Apple / BuzzFeed

El logotipo parece una imitaciÃ³n de un dispositivo Apple, pero esto fue 13 aÃ±os antes del lanzamiento del primer iPhone. Cuando un personaje escribe "Golpear a Martin" el Apple Newton PDA lo autocorrige como "Comer a Martha". La cosa es que el autocorrector se presentÃ³ por primera vez en el 2005 en la vida real. Los Simpson lo presentaron 11 aÃ±os antes de que sucediera. | 20th Century Fox, Tim Robberts / Getty ImagesEn 1995, Los Simpson presentaron un hÃ­brido de telÃ©fono y reloj en un episodio titulado "La boda de Lisa", 20 aÃ±os antes del lanzamiento del Apple Watch. | 20th Century Fox, ZyngaEn el episodio "Bart en la feria" de 1998, en Los Simpson se hizo una broma sobre niÃ±os jugando en un simulador de trabajo de campo. En ese momento, la idea parecÃ­a totalmente risible. Sin embargo, en 2009, 11 aÃ±os despuÃ©s del estreno del episodio, la gente de todo el mundo estaba obsesionada con un juego llamado FarmVille en el que podÃ­as arar, plantar y cosechar cultivos y Ã¡rboles. | 20th Century Fox, IPREn el especial de Halloween, "La casita del horror XIX", una mÃ¡quina para votar amaÃ±ada cambia los votos de Homero por Barack Obama por votos para John McCain varias veces. El episodio se estrenÃ³ en 2008 y cuatro aÃ±os despuÃ©s, en 2012, una mÃ¡quina electrÃ³nica para votar en Filadelfia seleccionaba a Mitt Romney incluso cuando los votantes intentaban elegir a Obama. | 20th Century Fox, FoxUna versiÃ³n simpsonizada de Lady Gaga actuÃ³ en el pueblo de Springfield colgando en el aire en el episodio de 2012, "Lisa y Lady Gaga". Cinco aÃ±os despuÃ©s, en 2017, el espectÃ¡culo de medio tiempo del Super Bowl mostrÃ³ a Gaga bajando desde lo alto del estadio con un cable. Â¿Gaga se inspirÃ³ en eso o simplemente Los Simpson lo sabÃ­an? | 20th Century Fox, HBOEn el episodio de 2017, "Los Siervson", las payasadas de Homero llevan a que un dragÃ³n incinere un pueblo completo. En 2019, dos aÃ±os despuÃ©s de que ese episodio de Los Simpson saliera al aire, en Game of Thrones (temporada 8, episodio 5) Daenerys y su dragÃ³n mataron a miles de personas inocentes con el fuego. | 20th Century Fox, 20th Century Fox/DisneyEn el episodio de 1998, "Cuando se anhela una estrella", un letrero enfrente del estudio de 20th Century Fox revela que es una divisiÃ³n de Walt Disney Co lo que no era verdad... en ese momento. En 2017, 19 aÃ±os despuÃ©s, Disney comprÃ³ 21st Century Fox. | 20th Century Fox, ABCEn el episodio de 1993, "$pringfield prÃ³spero, o el problema del juego", dos magos que actÃºan en un casino son atacados por un tigre blanco. Title Headline: 23 YA Books We Recommend That Are Specifically Tailored To Your Hogwarts House
Short Description Sub Headline: Consider this the shopping list that comes with every Hogwarts letter.
Content Body: 23 YA Books We Recommend That Are Specifically Tailored To Your Hogwarts House | Consider this the shopping list that comes with every Hogwarts letter. | Posted on March 29, 2020, 00:46 GMT | March 29, 2020, 00:46 GMT | Rachel StrolleBuzzFeed Contributor | Katherine Tegen Books, Via lylaleebooks.comRelease date: Jun. 16, 2020What it's about: Skye Shin has just made it into an internationally televised competition looking for the next K-pop star. Her spectacular voice earns her a spot in the singing portion of the competition, and despite what her mother has told her â€” that fat girls shouldn't dance, that they shouldn't draw attention to themselves â€” her incredible moves get her into the dance portion. But her mother isn't the only one whose fat-phobic standards Skye will have to overcome on her quest to become the world's first plus-sized K-pop star. Hufflepuffs will swoon hard over this book, and if you're thinking it's odd that a competition book is being sorted into the house that represents "loyalty," it's because no matter what, Skye always stays true to herself. Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Scholastic, Lens of LakhaniRelease date: Oct. 15, 2019What it's about: Nathaniel Fremont, the son of the settlement's tyrannical Commissioner, is determined to earn his father's respect. His plan? Capturing the Technician, who has been supplying black market medical technology to the sick and injured. What Nathaniel doesn't know is that the Technician is Anna Thatcher, a girl with an illegal clockwork heart. And as she attempts to evade capture, an assassin arrives to learn the Commissioner's secrets...at any cost. Slytherins will love this queer steampunk sci-fantasy as much as Draco Malfoy loves namedropping his father. Get it from Amazon for $14.26, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Salaam Reads, Azalia SuhaimiRelease date: Feb. 5, 2019What it's about: Melati Ahmad, a Malaysian 16-year-old, believes there is a djinn inside her. Unless she adheres to a ritual of counting and tapping, she's threatened with images of her mother's death. And in May of 1969, the worst case scenario arrives. Racial tensions in Kuala Lumpur boil over into riots between the Chinese and the Malays, and Melati and her mother are separated. Desperate to track down her mom, Melati can only rely on the strength and courage inside of herself (and a wee bit of help from a Chinese boy named Vincent) to reunite. Gryffindors will be eager to throw this book into the hands of everyone they know â€” after they cry a little bit. Get it from Amazon for $10.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Sourcebooks Fire, Via linseymiller.comRelease date: Feb. 4, 2020What it's about: Emilie des Marais is a noble lady who would prefer scalpels to embroidery needles. Anette Boucher wants to be trained in magic and gets the offer of a lifetime from a noble...to switch places. Annette attends finishing school as a noble lady to learn the art of divination, and Emelie enrolls to be a physician's assistant. The two must work together, however, when their nation instigates a war â€” a war based on lies. Ravenclaws will enjoy this magical story featuring two girls who literally go to great lengths to get the schooling they want. Get it from Amazon for $13.34, Barnes and Noble for $16.72, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, Levy Moroshan, Chris ReynoldsRelease date: Jul. 7, 2020What it's about: The last thing Iris (a secret witch) expects on her first day of school is to be taken in by a trio of other witches. Their coven includes soft-spoken Greta, musical Ridley, and fiery Binx...but they aren't the only coven in town. Since junior high, they've had a rivalry with The Triad, a group who uses their spells to punish their exes and break up happy couples for fun. But when someone's anti-witch ideology turns deadly, the two covens may need to band together. Gryffinclaws will love this one â€” their Ravenclaw side will love the mystery and their Gryffindor side will relate to having friends you'd walk through fire for.Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, London ShahRelease date: Oct. 29, 2019What it's about: In the last days of the twenty-first century, London is living underwater. When Leyla McQueen, a 16-year-old submersible racer, gets the chance to participate in the annual marathon, she knows it's her opportunity to save her father, who was arrested on false charges. But during the race, something unexpected occurs, leaving Leyla to defy a corrupt government determined to keep its secrets. Ravenclaws will adore watching optimistic Leyla use logic and determination to work her way through a series of impossible choices.Get it from Amazon for $8.99, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Crown Books, York WilsonRelease date: Jan. 21, 2020What it's about: Ever since phoenix horses were gifted to the Ashlords by their gods, they've raced them. These races evolved into a multi-day event, where elite riders fight to be crowned champion. Not only do the competitors need to be good at riding, they must be skilled at controlling the horses that are made of ash and alchemy. For every sunset, the horses burst into flame and rise from the ashes at sunrise. Racers must also find ways to keep their horses safe, for while murdering a rival's horse is outlawed, other forms of sabotage are not. Fiery Gryffindors will fall headfirst for this series starter as they follow the races through the eyes of a champion's daughter, a scholarship entrant, and a revolutionary's son. Get it from Amazon for $13.99, Barnes and Noble for $16.79, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Katherine Tegen, Via writeinbk.comRelease date: May 21, 2019What it's about: Brooklyn, 1998. After Steph is murdered, his friends Quadir and Jarrell come up with a plan to promote Steph's music. With the help of Steph's sister Jasmine, they create a demo and a new rap persona: the Architect. When that demo catches the ear of a music label rep, they must not only prove Steph's talent but also confront the truth about what really happened to Steph. Slytherins will devour this sublime piece of historical fiction and immediately reach for Jackson's other novels.Get it from Amazon for $12.77, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Razorbill, Via jenniferciacopelli.comRelease date: Feb. 18, 2020What it's about: A year ago, Audrey Lee was recovering from a spine surgery that could have paralyzed her. Now, she's on the United States' gymnastics team with her best friend, Emma, and getting ready for the Olympics. But when horrifying news emerges about one of their coaches, the team faces a new reality...one where they aren't all on the same side. Hufflepuffs will love the friendship between Audrey and Emma and will certainly cry at a few choice moments throughout the book. Get it from Amazon for $15.52, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Viking, Sue GrubmanRelease date: Apr. 21, 2020What it's about: Fitz Holton and Juniper Ramirez meet in Boston, on their first college tour, and they could not have more opposite ideas of the future. Fitz wants to stay close to home, maintaining the ability to care for his single mother as her early-onset Alzheimer's starts stealing her my memory. Juniper cannot wait to leave the zero privacy home that is crowded with five siblings. Fitz is on the college tour because his mother wants him to go, but Juniper planned hers herself against the wishes of her family. Slytherclaws will want to hold tight to the two leads as they meander towards one of their first adulting decisions. Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, Via ronnidavis.comRelease date: Nov. 12, 2020What it's about: Last summer, Devon fell in love with a boy named Ashton, only to have him break her heart at the end of the summer. Since then, she's put the pieces back together, but that plan veers off course when Ashton shows up on the first day of senior year. Davis masterfully wraps up a stunning love story and a carefully crafted portrayal of mental illness in a Gryffinpuff package. Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Simon & Schuster, Carter HasegawaRelease date: Jul. 30, 2019What it's about: Maren is on her way to steal a dragon and rescue her girlfriend. She would have been perfectly happy with a quiet life, but after the Aurati (prophetic agents of the emperor) abducted Kaia, Maren was forced to hatch a plan. To succeed, she must become an apprentice to the mysterious dragon trainer of the emperor, but she's unprepared for the dangerous secrets she uncovers. Time is running out, and Gryffindors will love every heart-pounding second. Get it from Amazon for $9.49, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Skyscape, Via victorialeewrites.comRelease date: Mar. 1, 2019What it's about: Noam Ãlvaro wakes up in a hospital bed with technopathic abilities, the only survivor of the viral magic that killed his family. He is quickly thrust into the attention of the minister of defense, who offers to teach him the science behind his magic. Noam has spent his life fighting for the rights of refugees fleeing magical outbreaks the nation of Carolinia, so he accepts the ministers offer. After all, he plans to use anything he learns to work against the government. Slytherins will devour Noam's story along with the recently released sequel, The Electric Heir, and then busy themselves reading the Webtoon adaptation. Get it from Amazon for $6.79, Barnes and Noble for $8.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Balzer + Bray, Via abdaddy.comRelease date: Jun. 4, 2019What it's about: For 3 teens in 1989, New York City, the world is changing. Reza, an Iranian boy, just moved to the city with his mother, and while Reza knows he is gay, all he knows of gay life are the media's images of men dying of AIDS. Judy is a plus-size aspiring fashion designer who has never dreamed of finding romance...until she and Reza start dating. Judy's best friend, Art, is the only out and proud teen at their school, who rebels against his conservative parents by documenting the AIDS crisis through photography. Hufflepuffs will tense as Art and Reza grow closer, as you desperately hope none of the wonderful characters get their hearts broken. Get it from Amazon for $8.29, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Margaret K. McElderry, Alice StallcupRelease date: Jun. 4, 2019What it's about: For as long as she has lived, Elisabeth has known one thing: all sorcerers are evil. She dreams of becoming a warden, charged with protecting the kingdom from the power of grimoires â€” tools of sorcery that rattle beneath chains and transform into beasts of ink and leather if provoked. When the most dangerous grimoire in the library is released during an act of sabotage, she must turn to a sorcerer, Nathaniel Thorn, and his mysterious demonic servant for help. If you are a Ravenclaw who grew up knowing that no gift would ever live up to the Beast gifting Belle the library, this is the book for you. Get it from Amazon for $11.59, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Simon Pulse, Sabreen LakhaniRelease date: Jan. 2, 2018What it's about: Twins Adina and Tovah are about to take a genetic test for Huntington's, the rare degenerative disease that has slowly been turning their Israeli mother into a stranger. Viola prodigy Adina wants to succeed as a soloist and hopes to convince her music teacher that he wants her in the way she wants him. Tovah dreams of becoming a surgeon and awaits an acceptance letter from Johns Hopkins. And when the test results arrive, one twin tests negative. The other tests positive. If you love ambition and emotion, you'll love this Slytherpuff book. Get it from Amazon for $7.99, Barnes and Noble for $11.69, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | HarperTeen, Kerem HanciRelease date: Feb. 18, 2020In case you haven't yet read book one, The Final Six: After erratic climate change renders Earth too dangerous, 24 teens are drafted into the International Space Training Camp in order to determine which six of them will be scouting a new planet. Among the 24 are Leo, an Italian championship swimmer who lost his family, and Naomi, an Iranian-American science genius who is suspicious of the ISTC. What it's about: As a part of the Final Six, Naomi is headed into space, away from Leo and on towards Europa. She is determined to find out if there is alien life there and to discover what happened to the last group of astronauts who attempted their mission. Leo is on Earth, working with a renegade scientist to warn Naomi and the others of what awaits on Europa. Ravenpuffs will crave the reunion of Naomi and Leo and the resolution to the mysteries of what truly lies beyond Earth. Get it from Amazon for $14.19, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Wednesday Books, Traci J BrooksRelease date: Jan. 21, 2020What it's about: Big League Burger just stole a grilled cheese recipe that belonged to Jack's grandmother. While he's always been a bit of a class clown and isn't super sure about his future within his family's deli, he knows he must defend the honor of the legendary grilled cheese...one tweet at a time. On the other side of the Big League Burger's Twitter account is Pepper â€” swim team captain, perfectionist, annoyed by Jack IRL. As the businesses end up in a viral Twitter war, neither Pepper nor Jack knows that the other is behind the rival account. And in real life, they're falling for each other on an anonymous chat app. Perhaps you are wondering, "Well, it seems like this book is pretty Slytherin, what with the manipulation of social media!" Might I remind you that the characters names are Pepper and Jack and the main conflict centers grilled cheese? 100% Hufflepuff. Get it from Amazon for $13.49, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, Becky ForsayethRelease date: Mar. 3, 2020What it's about: Dayna Walsh is focused on ascending and finally becoming a witch. Better to focus on that than on the fact that she was outed as bisexual in her conservative Irish town and is now attempting to cope with somatic OCD. Her focus is interrupted by the arrival of another coven, one that supposedly has a history with black magic, and with them comes Meiner King, the bewitchingly frustrating granddaughter of their coven leader. When a witch turns up murdered with the symbols of an infamous serial killer who was never caught, Dayna and Meiner find themselves at the center of a web of witches and gods. It takes a whole lot of cunning to catch a killer, and Slytherins will delight in the chase. Get it from Amazon for $15.36, Barnes and Noble for $18.76, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Knopf, Louisa WellsRelease date: Oct. 29, 2019What it's about: Simone Garcia-Hampton is at a new school, making sure that the fact that she was born HIV-positive stays under wraps. Starting over seems to be working out for her â€” making new friends, student directing Rent, and falling for a sweet boy named Miles â€” until she receives an anonymous note in her locker. If she doesn't break things off with Miles by Thanksgiving, everyone will know her secret. Though her instinct is to protect the information at all cost, she begins to wonder if the only way to rise above is to face the haters head on... Garrett's debut is full of brave choices, honest conversations, and an authenticity that only someone who wrote it while still a teenager could provide. Get it from Amazon for $14.31, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Tor Teen, Sasha LedneyRelease date: Feb. 5, 2019What it's about: Brynn Hilder has been recruited by Vale Hall, an elite academy that will provide her a welcome escape from her mom's loser boyfriend. But Vale is not a normal school â€” students are recruited based on their activities outside of class, such as Brynn's time spent conning rich North Shore kids out of their allowances. The school's mission is to rid the city of corrupt officials, a mission Brynn initially is on board with, but that's before she discovers the headmaster has his own secrets...secrets he'll protect at any cost. Though many of the characters within are certainly Slytherins, it's Ravenclaws who will appreciate piecing together the puzzle that Simmons gives to her readers.Get it from Amazon for $10.99, Barnes and Noble for $10.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Putnam, Via goodreads.comRelease date: May 24, 2016What it's about: Mercy Wong lives in Chinatown in 1906, San Fransisco, and she needs a break. Her best bet is an education at St. Clare's School for Girls â€” a school she'll have to bribe her way into, since it is off-limits to all but the wealthiest white girls. But getting in was the easy part, since April 18th brings with it a historic earthquake that destroys the school and Mercy's home. As martial law is enacted in the city, Mercy can't sit by while so many are suffering. Slytherdors with an equal dose of cunning and moxie will relate deeply to Mercy and will find a new favorite historical fiction in this book. Get it from Amazon for $7.89, Barnes and Noble for $9.89, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | The Parliament House, Daniel McCookRelease date: Jun. 25, 2019What it's about: In a world full of superheroes, one girl will do whatever it takes...to not get killed. Meg lives in Lunar City, where the near-daily battles between superhumans has led her to adopt a "background citizen" existence. But her entire strategy falls to pieces when she stumbles across the dead body of one of the supers, and his girlfriend coerces her into tracking down who killed him. Non-magical folks will find a kindred spirit in Meg and will be especially delighted by the fact that there is a rat whose name is Trashface. Get it from Amazon for $14.99 or from Barnes and Noble for $17.60.

Title Headline: 17 Easy Cocktails To Make Social Distancing Just A Little Bit More Fun
Short Description Sub Headline: It's not drinking alone. It's social distancing.
Content Body: Food | 17 Easy Cocktails To Make Social Distancing Just A Little Bit More Fun | It's not drinking alone. It's social distancing. | Posted on March 23, 2020, 19:00 GMT | March 23, 2020, 19:00 GMT | Hannah LoewentheilBuzzFeed Staff | Bev Cooks / Via bevcooks.comMade with just five ingredients, a sweet and zesty classic mojito will almost transport you to Havana. Start with muddled mint and sugar, then add fresh lime juice, rum, and a splash of club soda. Get the recipe for classic mojito here. | Sweet Phi / Via sweetphi.comAnother five-ingredient creation, the old fashioned cocktail gets a seasonal twist with the help of hard or soft apple cider and sliced apples for garnish. Get the recipe for apple cider old fashioned cocktail here. | Fork in The Kitchen / Via forkinthekitchen.com, Fork In The Kitchen / Via forkinthekitchen.comFast forward to summertime with this light and fresh sangria, made with rosÃ©, sugar or simple syrup, lemon, strawberry, and mint. You can get creative though and use whatever fruits and herbs are in your kitchen. Get the recipe for strawberry mint sangria here. | Blossom To Stem / Via blossomtostem.netDon't be intimidated by the idea of using egg white in a cocktail. It's actually so simple, and it turns your everyday drink into something that looks and tastes incredibly fancy. Get the recipe for Aperol sour cocktail here. | Cookie and Kate / Via cookieandkate.comThis cocktail might sound intricate and involved, but all you need is bourbon, lemon juice, maple syrup, and a pinch of cinnamon. Get the recipe for cinnamon maple whiskey sour here. | I Am A Food Blog / Via iamafoodblog.comThe classic negroni gets a makeover: Instead of bitter Campari, this version is made with sweet elderflower liqueur. Get the recipe for St. Germain negroni here. | The Sweetest Occasion / Via thesweetestoccasion.comUsing fruit jam in a cocktail recipe is simply genius if you ask us. With just peach jam, fresh peaches, iced tea, and whiskey, you can make a restaurant-quality cocktail at home. Get the recipe for peach whiskey smash cocktail here. | Drinking Hobby / Via drinkinghobby.comThis recipe calls for raspberry syrup, but don't worry if you don't have that. Muddled raspberries and classic simple syrup or agave will do the trick. Get the recipe for clover club cocktail here. | Gimme Some Oven / Via gimmesomeoven.comThe status of the world is basically spring break for everyone so if you're looking for a little something to get your morning going, we've got you covered. Get the recipe for tequila sunrise mimosas here. | Set The Table Blog / Via setthetableblog.comThis sophisticated drink comes together with gin, lemon juice, honey, and egg white. Throw everything into a cocktail shaker and strain into a coupe. Get the recipe for bee's knees cocktail here. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 16 Self-Isolating Tips For Parents That've Worked For My Kids So Far
Short Description Sub Headline: Self-isolating + parenting = a lot!
Content Body: Parents | 16 Self-Isolating Tips For Parents That've Worked For My Kids So Far | Self-isolating + parenting = a lot! | Posted on March 25, 2020, 16:15 GMT | March 25, 2020, 16:15 GMT | Mike SpohrBuzzFeed Staff | | | Universal, Warner Bros.My wife and I are â€˜80s kids, so we've used self-isolating as an opportunity to show Annie and James some of the classics from childhood. So far weâ€™ve watched the Back to the Future trilogy, The Goonies, Groundhog Day, and Ghostbusters. Seeing the kids enjoy these movies as much as we did as kids has been a blast.The best part of these movie nights, though â€” from a self-isolating perspective â€” is that it A) gives the kids something to look forward to all day, B) creates a bit of scheduled normalcy, and C) is family time when we can cuddle and focus on each other.

Title Headline: 16 Things To Do Now That You Can't Watch Your Favorite Sports
Short Description Sub Headline: Please, I just need to see a ball (any ball) score a point, goal, or run.
Content Body: Shopping | 16 Things To Do Now That You Can't Watch Your Favorite Sports | Please, I just need to see a ball (any ball) score a point, goal, or run. | Posted on March 24, 2020, 20:01 GMT | March 24, 2020, 20:01 GMT | John MihalyBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | | | Sony, XboxAs always, a new Major League Baseball season brings with it new video games (even when that season is postponed). Play out that entire162 game schedule with either MLB The Show 20 for PS4 ($59.99) or RBI Baseball 20 for Xbox ($29.99). | WalmartSince anything more than two-on-two is considered a gathering (and a really bad idea) you're going to have to take your game inside. Play some one-on-none with the Pro Mini Basketball Hoop ($24.99) and take a break from WFH to work on that long-distance jumper. And while the "spring-action break-away rim" encourages thunderous dunks, we encourage you to make sure no one is watching while you pretend to throw it down like Giannis. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Anyway, I didn't have to wait long to test out Wine Away's effectiveness as the first red wine spill happened a couple of weeks later on my wife's brand new, super expensive runner which we weren't supposed to be drinking anywhere near and, of course, is brilliant white. At this point, I had already given up all hope of covering up my tracks but figured I might as well try Wine Away as my last-ditch 'maybe I won't have to sleep on the couch' effort. To my amazement, upon spraying Wine Away on the stain, it immediately cleared up and left no residue or dullness behind. Honestly, I even called my wife in, told her what happened, and had her search for where the stain was and she couldn't find it. Simply amazing stuff. I am now a believer in Wine Away and have used it on not only wine spills but also pet stains on various fabrics and it's always stepped up to the challenge." â€”DerekGet it from Amazon for $6.67. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "These little guys work perfectly for dermaplaning! Promising review: "I have several houseplants that had stopped flowering so I put a few of these spikes in the pot. There are directions on the back of package for quantity and approximately a month after using these spikes, my peace lily had three flowers on it! My African violets plants all got several blooms on them! This worked wonders for my plants that don't flower also. I noticed that my ivy and cactus plants started growing faster and they became more green and healthy-looking. I am very happy with this product and I will buy it again." â€”ElizabethGet it from Amazon for $2.24 (available in a pack of 48). | AmazonAside from these bowls being gorg, they're also airtight, and dishwasher- and microwave-safe so you can tote your food without fear of it spilling. Peep what BuzzFeed writer Rachel Dunkel thinks of these bowls:"I use my Porter Bowl basically every time I bring my lunch to work. And it just feels nice to eat lunch out of a real piece of dishware, rather than flimsy plastic. I have the ceramic version and haven't had any problems with scratching. It's rubber coated, so it's easy to travel with and doesn't slide around. I would personally like more as gifts, please!"Get them from Amazon for $25+ (available in ceramic or plastic and in 10 colors). | AmazonPromising review: "I got the pink chair. ZacariasGet it from Amazon for $99.99 or two for $189.99 (available in six colors). | elf, BuzzFeed / Marquaysa BattleAlso: The brand is cruelty-free! Amazing success!!!" â€”Sophia P.Get it from Amazon for $24.95. | Olive and JunePromising review: "I love doing my own manicures but had to stop due to issues with mobility in my hands and fingers making it too difficult to hold onto the brushes. I purchased the pink one and it contrasts nicely with my dark espresso wooden desk. The mouse moves easy and steady on the surface and has made it much easier to write on my desk. Since the desk is wooden, it's collected small imperfections over the years, making writing on the desk sometimes difficult. I would definitely recommend for new or old desks. New to prevent nicks and dents, and for the old ones to cover them up. ğŸ™‚" â€”DeleahGet it from Amazon for $13.99+ (available in three sizes and nine colors). | amazon.comPromising review: "I rarely ever leave reviews, but THIS is amazing!! I have naturally frizzy hair that is also wavy and curly. I have a lot of breakage around the crown and this stuff sleeks it back but it doesnâ€™t make it look greasy or crunchy! I suggest taking the mascara wand and wiping off the excess on the tube before applying so you donâ€™t apply too much. When I apply too much all you have to do is let it dry and then scratch your fingernails from front to back to break it up and it still creates a sleek look without any crunchiness. I love this stuff so much I need to get another for my car on those days that my mom hair is looking terrible." â€”AdrianaGet it from Amazon for $7.98. | AmazonPromising review: "This chair is dazzling to the eyes. It goes well in my upscale office space. It's also fairly comfortable and more than I expected for the price. I love it!" â€”Best realtor everGet it from Novogratz on Amazon for $119.12 (available with free shipping). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Marquaysa Battle / BuzzFeed, Myro / Via mymyro.comPick your case. Pick your scent. Then, select your plan based on whether you want a one-time purchase or regular refill plan. Myro deodorants are cruelty-free but there's so much more to it than that. They're also aluminum-, paraben-, phthalate- and talc-free. Plus, they don't use baking soda, artificial colors, or synthetic fragrances which are known to be skin irritants. Tbh, I wasn't looking for environmentally friendly deodorant although I swear I love Mother Earth. My go-to fragrance-free deodorant was discontinued so I just desperately needed one that wouldn't irritate my sensitive underarm skin and would keep me smelling fresh. All the other natural deodorants I tried DEFINITELY DID NOT KEEP ME FRESH ğŸ™…ğŸ¿â€â™€ï¸. I had to re-up several times throughout the day just to avoid a sweaty smell which wasn't my norm and made me feel self-conscious. Finally, I stumbled upon the Myro deodorant and figured I'd just try it since I tried everything else (Native, Tom's, Almay, you name it). I was skeptical because it smelled so good and my severely sensitive skin typically doesn't play nice with scents. I guess since the product is truly natural, that's why it didn't irritate me. Fair warning: I peeped that the deodorant has low ratings on like two sites but it appears that the Myro brand listened to the people, as its website notes that it's upgraded the formula. I've been using it for about three weeks. I apply it once daily and don't have to break my schedule to re-up, haven't had any itchy patches develop under my arms, and FINALLY get to enjoy a great scented product again, which I haven't been able to do in years. BTW, the scent I have is the Chill Wave which smells like cucumber, jasmine, and spearmint ğŸ‘ƒğŸ¾â¤ï¸.Get the actual deodorant from Myro for $10 (available in seven scents) and the case for FREE (refill for $10 (available in seven colors). So, like, no brainer, am I right?? I love them. I feel confident that they aren't going to break every time I put them in as the pearls are woven together. I've worn them a couple of times now and love them. It's the easiest way to cover up the desperate need to wash your hair or make it look like you've actually tried." â€”Taylor GreenGet them from Amazon for $5.99 (available in a pack of four). | amazon.comThe barrel is designed to protect your fingers from getting burned so you enjoy an ouchless curling sesh. It also has an auto-shutoff feature and even a feature that pauses the iron if you put too much hair into the chamber to curl at once. Promising review: "Love it!! I have fine textured hair â€” very straight hair. I have trouble not only curling it, but keeping it curled. For example, the other day I left rollers in my hair for 45 minutes and got a minor wave that fell out in 10 minutes. This tool is easy and fast to use, adds shine, and the curl stays." â€”AlexandriaGet it from Amazon for $74.99+ (available in three colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I wear an 8 but ordered a half-size down because of suggestions from other customers. The 7.5 I ordered fits lovely! They are nice and snug and comfortable on my flat feet! I ordered three different pairs." â€”Alexis BecksGet them from Amazon for $28.84+ (available in sizes 5.5-11 and 70!!! color/style combinations).

Content Body: Music | BTS Are Releasing "Learn Korean With BTS" Videos To Help Fans Study And 7 Other Pieces Of K-Pop News You Should Know | Plus a bunch of new music to help you cope with the state of the world. | Posted on March 27, 2020, 18:16 GMT | March 27, 2020, 18:16 GMT | Sarah HanBuzzFeed Staff | Emlyn TravisBuzzFeed Staff | Chung Sung-jun / Getty Images, Hannah Foslien / Getty ImagesA star-studded lineup of celebs will be playing games and performing live, including Joe Jonas, Lauv, Charlie Puth, Jordin Sparks, and Aly Raisman.Viewers can donate during the stream or create a "supporting campaign" on Twitch's donation page, or you can also co-stream the Stream Aid on your own Twitch channel. Title Headline: 25 Things That'll Make Working From Home Suck A Whole Lot Less
Short Description Sub Headline: Coffee machines, indoor gardens, meditation headbands, and more!
Content Body: Shopping | 25 Things That'll Make Working From Home Suck A Whole Lot Less | Coffee machines, indoor gardens, meditation headbands, and more! | Posted on March 16, 2020, 16:45 GMT | March 16, 2020, 16:45 GMT | Victoria KuglinBuzzFeed Staff | | | | Amazon / Via amazon.caWith these, you can listen to your tunes for more than 30 hours on a single charge. And with a handy control knob, you can adjust the volume, skip tracks, and even take calls on the go.Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $91.03+ (available in nine colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caSetup is super easy, so you can go from unboxing to listening in minutes. It has built-in voice control, and works with Alexa, or you can also use the Sonos app or Apple Airplay to go completely hands-free. It can even pair with other speakers for a richer, more immersive sound. Get it on Amazon Canada for $247.77+ (available in two colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caEucalyptus is naturally antiseptic and antibacterial, and can be used to help with a number of sinus and respiratory conditions. It also makes a great yoga mat spray!Get it on Amazon Canada for $14.99+ (available in ten scents). | Amazon / Via amazon.caThe headband also connects to the Muse app, so tracking meditations and brain activity is super easy. Over time, you'll be able to see when your brain is tired, angry, or frustrated, and when you're feeling relaxed, happy, and content, and it'll be a lot easier to navigate your way back to a happier state!Get it on Amazon Canada for $237.36+ (available in two colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caThese 100% cotton joggers look great with a cropped sweater, and can take you from couch to coffee meeting in less time than it takes to say, "They're machine washable, too?"Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $24.23+ (available in five colours and in sizes S-3XL). | @everlasting_comfort / Via instagram.com, @everlasting_comfort / Via instagram.comUse it in your home office to help with things like sciatica, tailbone pain, and posture correction. Or take it with you to the next sporting event, camping trip, or picnic! With over 1,000 five-star reviews, this is one purchase you'll be comfortable with.Get it on Amazon Canada for $39.95. | @levoitlifestyle / Via instagram.com, @levoitlifestyle / Via instagram.comIt also has three fan speeds, so you know it's strong enough to address even the nastiest air conditions. It's also available in a compact size.Get it on Amazon Canada for $101.99 (available in two colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caTouch anywhere on the base to activate the lamp, adjust brightness, or cycle through the colours. You can also get a mini version here!Get it on Amazon Canada for $37.99. | @discovervibes / Via instagram.com, @discovervibes / Via instagram.comUnlike traditional earplugs, these ones still allow you to hear certain frequencies (like a ringing phone), so you won't be totally isolated. They're also great for parents of newborns, or for those with noise sensitivity. Each set comes with three interchangeable tips (small, medium, and large), so you know you'll get a perfect fit. Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $37.95. | Amazon / Via amazon.caThey can't guarantee that you'll get paid overtime, but the spring hinges and funky colours make them ultra comfortable and hella cute.Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $19.99+ (available in ten colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caIts sleek, tablet-like design is unobtrusive and versatile enough to pair with any decor style. Reviewers love its sunshine-y brightness that's powerful enough to deliver a hefty dose of vitamin D.Get it on Amazon Canada for $59.95. | Amazon / Via amazon.caThey're tough, versatile, and can be combined for bigger jobs. *Cut to me wrapping everything in my house in these*Get a multi-coloured pack of 50 on Amazon Canada for $11.89 (also available in black). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 36 Beauty Products You'll Probably Pat Yourself On The Back For Buying
Short Description Sub Headline: I support your decision to treat yourself to yet another lipstick you probably don't need but deserve.
Content Body: Shopping | | Beauty | 36 Beauty Products You'll Probably Pat Yourself On The Back For Buying | I support your decision to treat yourself to yet another lipstick you probably don't need but deserve. | Posted on March 15, 2020, 12:01 GMT | March 15, 2020, 12:01 GMT | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | | elfcosmetics / Via instagram.com, elfcosmetics / Via instagram.comThis concealer is made with a highly pigmented formula that still dries matte, feels lightweight, and won't settle into fine lines or creases.Get it from e.l.f. Cosmetics for $6 (available in 26 shades). | | amazon.comPromising review: "I rarely ever leave reviews, but THIS is amazing!! I have naturally frizzy hair that is also wavy and curly. I have a lot of breakage around the crown and this stuff sleeks it back but it doesnâ€™t make it look greasy or crunchy! I suggest taking the mascara wand and wiping off the excess on the tube before applying so you donâ€™t apply too much. When I apply too much all you have to do is let it dry and then scratch youâ€™re fingernails from front to back to break it up and it still creates a sleek look without any crunchiness. I love this stuff so much I need to get another for my car on those days that my mom hair is looking terrible." â€”AdrianaGet it from Amazon for $7.99. | Amazon, amazon.comAvarelle's pimple patches are formulated with tea tree oil and calendula, which is said to heal and shrink zits overnight. A single pack comes with 40 patches in a variety of sizes to fit any pimple you've got.Promising review: "Iâ€™ve tried so many brands of pimple spots, and these are hands-down the best on the market. Iâ€™m a performer at Walt Disney World, and a clear complexion is required. Last night, I put these on a few acne problems (a small cyst, a whitehead, and a pimple I shouldnâ€™t have picked and has been a bump for about three weeks now.) I just woke up and am writing this review in disbelief. THEY'RE FLAT! Gone! All of them! I could cry Iâ€™m so happy. The packaging is also ideal, because it allows you to conveniently and easily peel the stickers off without stretching them out or folding them back on themselves. Do yourself and your complexion a huge favor! Have these on hand for a stubborn zit when you really need help. Make sure you apply them to completely clean and dry skin." â€”CaitlynGet it from Amazon for $8.50. | GlossierMy coworker AnaMaria Glavan is passionate about this product. Here's what she had to say:"Believe the hype: this magic bottle is proof that not all heroes wear capes. The creamy formula, which comes in blond, black, clear, and brown (which is what I used!), goes on smoothly and doesnâ€™t require a lot of product to do the job. I used the wand to brush baby hairs in the beginning/middle of my brow upwards, and then brushed the longer, toddler-like hairs at the end of my eyebrows, sideways. And one coat was more than enough! Boy Brow does what exactly what the Glossier brand claims to do; it gives me a filled-in eyebrow that doesnâ€™t look filled in. The finish looks natural, which is exactly what I wanted â€” my facial caterpillars have never looked better."Get it from Glossier for $16 (available in four shades). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I absolutely LOVE this mascara. I have very sensitive eyes and am highly devoted to my trusted brands. When a friend suggested this mascara I was curious, as she loved it. For the price point and how good it looked on her eyes, I thought why not. Holy moly. I'm in love. It makes my lashes longer, â€” looks like I'm natural but better â€” and has a thinner formula so it looks like I have a billion gorgeous lashes, and looks the same all day long. I cannot recommend this enough. It doesn't rub during the day and give me that black eye look. It's wonderful. Must buy." â€”Katherine OchsmanGet it from Amazon for $12.95. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "My hair is very thin and curly. The ends are damaged from heat and color, causing my hair to look even more unruly. I do oil treatments once a week and only wash my hair two to three times a week but NOTHING has made my hair feel like this product does. There is an immediate difference as soon as this product touches my hair. It leaves my hair feeling so silky, even after I rinse it out and dry my hair." â€”Maegan W.Get it from Amazon for $12.95. | TartePromising review: "Best concealer till time!! Just love the consistency. Can be worn without powder to give a more dewy look! Love the travel size. Medium to high coverage! Would definitely recommend!" â€”Mehwish K.Get it from Tarte for $10 (available in 30 shades). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "These masks are amazing!!! Having 'ice pick' scars left over from acne I was told that I'd have to pay for expensive laser therapy because the body can't produce enough collagen to heal deep scars. I've been using these masks for two months and I've seen SIGNIFICANT reduction in my scars. They are almost completely gone!" â€”ShaunRead our full review of the Dermal Korea collagen sheet masks!Get them from Amazon for $9.99. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "I was lucky enough to have clear skin in high school so I never understood how awful acne really is. When I was about 21-22 years old, I switched to a birth control implant, and that thing wreaked havoc on my entire life. I suddenly had horrible cystic acne. Not only did it make me self conscious and uncomfortable, but it was actually so painful â€” laying on my pillow hurt my face! To top it all off, my skin was also dry, and irritated. I tried every skincare line on the market for about two to three years, with no, or very little, results. Finally, I found La Roche-Posay's skincare products. Within four days, the inflammation decreased, the redness was fading, and my skin felt less dry. By two weeks, my skin was practically clear! I have been using this product for about four to five years now, and I haven't had a single outbreak, EXCEPT for the time I wanted to try a different product to save money. Huge mistake, one I will not make again." â€”LadyHawkeGet it from Amazon for $14.99. | Thrive CausemeticsFor every product purchased Thrive Causemetics donates to help a woman *thrive*.Promising review: "This is honestly the best product. I use it on my eyes and lips and cheeks and it literally doesn't budge as eyeshadow. By the end of a 14-hour day it's still bright and beautiful. I mean it LASTS. I haven't found an eyeshadow that isn't gone by the end of the day or smudge. And it gives a beautiful glow to cheeks. WORTH IT!!" â€”Marcella C.Get it from Thrive Causemetics for $36 (available in four shades). | Kylie CosmeticsEven as a 27 year old, I own more than my fair share of Kylie Cosmetics. I'm talkin' lip kits and palettes for DAYS. Why you ask? Because Kylie Jenner makes a damn good product. Her packaging is among my favorite across all beauty brands and I love that she continues to reinvent the bottles, brushes, and boxes!Promising review: "This is my favorite gloss! I buy several high-end brands and this high gloss takes the cake! It even has the scent of cake! Iâ€™ve put it on and it keeps my lips hydrated all day! Itâ€™s not sticky like other brands tend to be. This was my first Kylie Cosmetics purchase and Iâ€™m extremely satisfied. Iâ€™m over 40 and thought, 'Is this even going to look good on me?' The answer is YES." â€”DebbieGet it from Kylie Cosmetics for $16. | Olive and JuneI've been doing my own nails for a long, long time. It always seemed smarter to me to spend money on a bottle of polish I can keep instead of a manicure that only lasts a week. It's a skill that took a while to work on but, luckily, for at-home manicurists like myself The Poppy has made doing my nails a lot less challenging. It pops right onto any bottle of nail polish (not just Olive and June colors) and provides you with a stronger grip and a more accurate swipe.Get it from Olive and June or Target for $16. | Amazon, amazon.comI have one of these babies and it really is wonderful. Not only does it make me feel like I'm really getting in there while I'm washing my hair, but it also recreates that feeling you get when your hairdresser massages your head while washing it. Ugh, so good.Promising review: "Love this product! About five days before I received it I dyed my hair at home. As some of you may know who do the same, itâ€™s difficult to get the hair dye out of your scalp. I scrubbed my hair for days with my fingers and it seemed like everything was gone because the water ran clear. When I received the product I was excited so I am immediately jumped in the shower to use it. To my surprise a ton of hair dye that was stuck on my head came off. Not only that, but my scalp feels breathable and clean. Definitely not greasy 24 hours later like regular shampooing would do for me. I would recommend this product." â€”Lisa AgroGet it from Amazon for $7.98+ (available in three colors). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I have never felt more compelled to write a product review before. This stuff is INCREDIBLE. I have tried almost everything to improve my skin. I continue to get acne in my mid-30s and literally everything else I've tried has not worked, including prescription topical cream and oral medication. This has saved my skin! I have had very few breakouts, and if anything pops up, this takes care of it quickly! My skin feels moisturized and looks smoother and healthier overall. This is truly one of the best purchases I've ever made. I'm thankful I stumbled upon this serum!" â€”J.C. DentonGet it from Amazon for $14.95. | oliveandjune / Via instagram.com, Olive & JuneI recently tried Olive and June's nail polish and was quite impressed. It went on very smoothly and didn't chip even after a week! I love how these colors will brighten up my nails for spring and summer (the mint is already calling my name!). This brand is also proudly 7-free, which means it doesn't contain harmful chemicals that most polishes do.Get it from Olive & June for $56. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "These eye masks are absolutely amazing! I have hereditary dark circles under my eyes, as well as slight bags from being a mother of four. Eye creams do absolutely nothing for me, and I gave these a try just on a whim, not really expecting much. But they really work! The results aren't permanent, but I put these on for about an hour in the evening while I relax and watch TV, and my under-eyes are much lighter and less puffy. I absolutely love these eye masks, and I will never be without them again." â€”Kate JohnsonGet a pack of 12 pairs from Amazon for $23.50. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedPromising review: "This hot air brush has made the biggest difference in my usually flat, frizzy hair! I now have more body and shine than I have had in years! I highly recommend this product. It is lightweight and easy to use. My hair holds a style longer and it is so much easier than trying to blow dry my hair while also using a round brush trying to style it. I wish I wouldâ€™ve discovered this hot air brush years ago! Love it!" â€”LRead our full review of the John Freida Hot Brush for more info!Get it from Amazon for $39.99+ (available in 1 and 1.5-inch versions). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "A must have in my makeup case! I have used plastic lash combs, metal ones, and flat ones, all of which just didnâ€™t get the job done. I always went back to a safety pin, WHICH I DO NOT ADVISE! This comb is metal and arched, which is much easier to use, and the teeth glide through lashes easily. NOTE: If your mascara is dry and clumped, ANY COMB COULD POTENTIALLY PULL OUT LASHES. JUST NO. DO NOT DO IT. I put on mascara, and while itâ€™s still wet, I glide the comb through the base and go up. Itâ€™s that simple. I was concerned about cleaning it with alcohol, but I asked customer service and was told it was safe." â€”ASConnerGet it from Amazon for $7.99. | Loops Beauty / Via instagram.com, Loops BeautyI recently gave this mask a go and was super impressed. Usually sheet masks slip and slide off of my face and I have to recline in an awkward position for 10 minutes â€” but no this one from Loops! It stays in place and includes great ingredients (pumpkin extract, white flower, and baobab oil) that left my face feeling super soft and hydrated. Oh, and the packaging is super cute.Get a five-pack from Loops Beauty for $30. | Glossier, Sarah Han / BuzzFeedMy colleague Sarah Han (as well as MANY other BuzzFeeders) is a big fan of this product. This is what she had to say:"I wasn't a blush person until I met Cloud Paint. Any other attempts at wearing blush always looked super unnatural and accented redness on my face that would, as you might guess, populate in the cheek areas. It was always too much or too little, no in between. Little did I know I needed to say goodbye to powder blushes and let ~gel-cream~ blush into my life. The gel-cream formula just blends so seamlessly, like no other blush I've ever used, and it's a piece of cake to use. It doesn't make pores look more apparent and just gliiiiides over your skin for a dewy-looking flush. And if I have too many glasses of wine, I can blame any flush on the blush."Get it from Glossier for $18 (available in six shades). | instagram.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I am lazy and hate doing my makeup, especially after a morning workout on a weekday. I wanted something I could throw in my bag and smear around my eyes in a couple of seconds, and to just add a little color without the fussiness. This fits the bill perfectly. It gives my eyes a little definition, but isn't super noticeable. The slight shimmer also makes me look awake on days where I'm dragging. It is not intensely shiny, though, which is important to me â€” I'm not a disco ball! It just reflects light and looks luminescent, not glittery. Because this is so easy to use, non-irritating, and is the exact color I was looking for, I expect that I will keep ordering it as long as it's available." â€”RachelGet it from Amazon for $4.50+ (available in 23 shades). | lovebeautyandplanet / Via instagram.com, AmazonI'm a sucker for anything made by Love, Beauty and Planet, so you can imagine how thrilled I was to try out this body scrub in my shower. This product is infused with organic coconut oil and Bulgarian roses. It smells AMAZING and leaves my body feeling like velvet â€” definitely a luxurious add-on for any shower experience. Then I'll top off the whole experience by covering myself in the equally-lovely lotion. Can't beat it!Get them from Amazon for $14.31. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 24 Vegan Baking Ideas For Anyone Who's Been Stress-Baking Lately
Short Description Sub Headline: Ideas from dairy-free donuts to classic chocolate chip cookies.
Content Body: Food | 24 Vegan Baking Ideas For Anyone Who's Been Stress-Baking Lately | Ideas from dairy-free donuts to classic chocolate chip cookies. | Posted on March 21, 2020, 15:46 GMT | March 21, 2020, 15:46 GMT | Whitney JeffersonBuzzFeed Staff | | Domestic Gothess / Via domesticgothess.comEveryone needs an ooey, gooey, melt-in-your-mouth chocolate chip recipe up their sleeve, and this one will deliver exactly that. | The Loopy Whisk / Via theloopywhisk.comIn times of stress, we could all use a little chocolate cake to calm our nerves. Luckily, this recipe is perfect for beginner bakers and fancy chefs alike. | Nora Cooks / Via noracooks.comThis recipe is a vegan spin on classic raspberry bars and is the perfect mix of sweet and savory. | Chocolate Covered Katie / Via chocolatecoveredkatie.comEspecially handy right now, this recipe for vegan lemon bread can be made with whatever flour you have on hand. | The Loopy Whisk / Via theloopywhisk.comThis chocolate babka recipe looks like an artistic masterpiece but is actually fairly simple to make. | Chocolate Covered Katie / Via chocolatecoveredkatie.comWhat's more comforting in the morning than cinnamon rolls all drenched in sugary icing? Try this recipe and find out. | The Big Man's World / Via thebigmansworld.com, Via thebigmansworld.comYes, you can make vegan donuts at home! This tasty recipe can also be modified to be keto and paleo, too. | Ela Vegan / elavegan.comThese brownies are vegan, gluten-free, and made with ease in a food processor. And to those of you who haven't baked with zucchini before, know that you won't taste any actual zucchini or "weird" flavors in the end result. | Short Girl Tall Order / Via shortgirltallorder.comNo baking list would be complete without a recipe for cupcakes. These are particularly fancy with their Earl Grey batter and blueberry whipped frosting! | Nora Cooks / Via noracooks.comWhat's better than s'mores? With this recipe, you can eat vegan cookie bars any day of the week. | Baker by Nature / Via bakerbynature.comIf you're anything like Larry David on Curb Your Enthusiasm, the hardness of your scone is a very important and personal preference. Learn how to make your own with this recipe. | Wee Little Vegans / Via weelittlevegans.comFrench toast is always a fun breakfast, but baking it into French toast cups is kinda next level, no? Just grab some syrup and go to town! | Lucy & Lentils / Via lucyandlentils.co.ukThis recipe for salted caramel shortbread combines dates, gluten-free flour, chocolate, and sugar for layers of goodness. | Strength and Sunshine / Via strengthandsunshine.comThis vegan coffee cake recipe is free of refined sugar and will please everyone at the breakfast table. | Okonomi Kitchen / Via okonomikitchen.comIf it's cake you're after, this recipe for banana snack cake is both easy to make and delicious. | Chocolate Covered Katie / Via chocolatecoveredkatie.comBaking classic sugar cookies is a great way to spend time at home. Use this recipe to make them vegan and get creative with any cookie cutters you have in your house. | Katarina Cermelj / Via theloopywhisk.comThis recipe for vegan banana bread has chocolate chips in it, so you know it'll be a crowd-pleaser. | Eat With Clarity / Via eatwithclarity.comThese soft, pumpkiny cookies have just the right amount of sweetness with icing and might feel a little reminiscent of fall. | The Simple Veganista / Via simple-veganista.comYes, with this recipe, you can make thumbprint cookies vegan and gluten-free using almond flour. | Livin' La Vegan Life / Via livinlaveganlife.com, Livin' La Vida Vegan Life / Via livinlaveganlife.comThe recipe for this delicious-looking marbleized cake is easier to do than you'd imagine just by looking at it. | Love From The Oven / Via lovefromtheoven.comIf you love to make pumpkin bread, try this veganized recipe â€” I dare you to taste a difference. | The Hidden Veggies / Via thehiddenveggies.comSpeaking of morning staples, this muffin recipe is something you can make ahead of time and then eat the muffins all week!

Title Headline: It's Been 15 Years Since "The Suite Life Of Zack & Cody" Premiered, So Here's What The Cast Looks Like Now
Short Description Sub Headline: Their lives are pretty ~sweet~.
Content Body: Celebrity | It's Been 15 Years Since "The Suite Life Of Zack & Cody" Premiered, So Here's What The Cast Looks Like Now | Their lives are pretty ~sweet~. | Posted on March 19, 2020, 17:46 GMT | March 19, 2020, 17:46 GMT | Lauren GarafanoBuzzFeed Staff | Disney Channel, Frazer Harrison / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Currently, Cole stars as Jughead Jones on The CW's Riverdale. Last year, he played Will Newman in the movie Five Feet Apart, and later this year he will be producing and starring in a fictional podcast called Borrasca. | Disney Channel, Theo Wargo / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Since Suite Life, Dylan has continued acting and has appeared in movies like Dismissed and Carte Blanche. He's also got a few movies coming up, including Banana Split, Tyger Tyger, Turandot, and After We Collided. Dylan's also the cofounder of a meadery called All-Wise Meadery. | Disney Channel, Phillip Faraone / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What she's up to now: Ashley has continued acting and recently starred on Netflix's Merry Happy Whatever, and she's currently starring on Carol's Second Act. Last year, Ashley also released her third studio album, Symptoms. | Disney Channel, David Livingston / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What she's up to now: Brenda also kept acting after Suite Life. Recently, she's been in a bunch of shows and movies, like Dollface, Secret Obsession, Amphibia, Changeland, and Station 19. | Disney Channel, Phill Lewis / cameo.comFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode: "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Phill has taken a break from acting, but he's started directing! He's directed episodes of Young & Hungry, Melissa & Joey, 2 Broke Girls, Indebted, and One Day At A Time. He's currently on Cameo too! | Disney Channel, @kimrhodes4reals / instagram.comFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What she's up to now: Kim continued acting in movies and TV. Aside from her role on Suite Life, she's also known for playing Sheriff Jody Mills on Supernatural. | Disney Channel, @adrianrmante / instagram.comFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "A Tale of Two Houses" (Season 3, Episode 15)What he's up to now: Since Suite Life, Adrian has appeared in Magnum P.I., Twice the Dream, The Haunt, Hawaii Five-0, and NCIS: Los Angeles. He also got married in 2018 and has two kids! | Disney Channel, Matt Winkelmeyer / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "The Prince & The Plunger" (Season 1, Episode 6)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Brian continued acting and has since been in movies like LBJ and Green Book. He currently has recurring roles in The Loud House and Young Sheldon, and has guest starred on shows like I'm Sorry, The Thundermans, and Longmire.

Content Body: Shopping | 19 Subscription Boxes That People Actually Swear By | Subscriptions for gardeners, teachers, pet parents, bakers, board game enthusiasts, and way more. | Posted on March 23, 2020, 14:11 GMT | March 23, 2020, 14:11 GMT | Harper HendricksonBuzzFeed Staff | | | | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll unpack four to six full-size, themed items for you and your pup. There will be toys and all-natural treats in every box for your pup, and all sorts of things for you â€” home decor items, healthy snacks, aromatherapy oils, tea, jewelry, books, bath and beauty products, crystals, and more!Promising review: "Fantastic Box! My puppy spent hours playing with the unicorn toys and loved the treats. I adored the necklace and candle and the blessing was so sweet. I am totally in love with this box and it's so reasonably priced! The items are very high quality. It was like present after present that my pup and I opened together. Loved it. Great job!" â€”Andrea H.Get it from Cratejoy for $39.95/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll receive all the pre-measured ingredients you need to make baking easy, quick, and fun! You'll also receive step-by-step instructions and video tutorials, and a new baking tool in every box. Each variety of treat makes up to 12-20 servings. Promising review: "My wife bought these boxes and I decided to try to make one on my own when she wasnâ€™t home. Itâ€™s very rare that I bake, but the directions were easy to follow and she was really surprised by how good I did. Maple pecan mini cakes came out great! And, the box made more mini cakes than it said it was going to. Update: Tried the Chai Tea Latte cupcakes and they came out perfect too. Our favorite of all the boxes we have tried so far." â€”Anthony M.Get it from Cratejoy for $30.99/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: Your kiddos will get a fun and engaging box that combines SELL (Social-Emotional Learning and Literacy) with monthly secret missions! These hands-on missions include projects, comic books, and stories of real heroes. This box promotes a mindfulness mindset and helps kids build skills like resilience, courage, and empathy.Promising review: "BRILLANT! I had high expectations when I purchased this as Christmas gifts for my two nieces (ages 5 and 6) and nephew (6). I wanted to give them something different. The lessons are deliberate and packaged as fun they can identify with. Who wouldnâ€™t want to be their own superhero? The kids (three different families) constantly send me videos of their projects and their parents all tell me it is the one gift they have been going back to after all the Christmas excitement has settled. The boxes are fun and unique. I love the learning that it's given the kids. As theyâ€™ve told me, 'Superheroes have feelings too!' This is a perfect product for modern times and will be my 'go-to' gift from here on out." â€”Celeste C. Get it from Cratejoy for $29.58/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll receive eco-conscious products to help reduce your carbon footprint, and information about global environmental problems such as plastic pollution, deforestation, ocean dead zones, and pollinator die-off. You'll also receive postcards, stamps, addresses, and talking points so you can inform family, friends, and neighbors about the issues affecting our world via snail mail. Promising review: "I got my first box last month. It's amazing! It had produce bags, really cool bamboo straws, pens and pencils and everything I need to send postcards about causes I care about. I love that I can do this with my family and teach them that change is possible and that it starts in our own home. I had all the neighborhood kids come over and write postcards. Not only did they participate, but they learned about the effects of having plastic in our national parks. This crate is fun and makes me feel good about myself." â€”Amber W.Get it from Cratejoy at $20/month. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF
