Title Headline: 35 Heavy-Duty Cleaning Products To Help You Tackle The Toughest Messes In Your Home
Short Description Sub Headline: They never even stood a chance.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 35 Heavy-Duty Cleaning Products To Help You Tackle The Toughest Messes In Your Home | They never even stood a chance. | Posted on March 18, 2020, 14:00 GMT | March 18, 2020, 14:00 GMT | Melanie AmanBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comPromising review: "I have very hard water that leaves hard water buildup and nasty stains. Itâ€™s embarrassing to have guests over because the toilets are so gross! I have tried so many products and cleaning solutions â€” from natural essential oils to harsh chemicals so strong I was lightheaded for the rest of the day. Well, I tried out this pumice stone after reading about it in a BuzzFeed article, and honestly the hype is real! It does take some elbow grease, but the after picture is from only 20 minutes of scrubbing, light enough that I didnâ€™t break a sweat! The stone does get used up, but I think this one should last me a couple years at least. So if you have embarrassing toilets, try this!" â€”Stephanie RayGet it from Amazon for $8.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "This stuff is amazing! After over 10 years of the grout not being cleaned, and a botched repair job, the bathroom floor in this house looked horrendous. Two pens covered the entire bathroom floor, with plenty left over in the second pen, even with applying two to three layers (which you will definitely need as the paint is a bit thin and also absorbs into the grout). Super easy to apply, works exactly like a regular paint marker. Be sure to press the pen tip on a separate (thick) cloth to activate it before actually using on the grout so you don't end up with a huge mess on the tile when the paint floods out at first. If you see the first side of the tip is getting frayed, just pull it out and turn it around to the other side." â€”regalleGet it from Amazon for $8.99+ (available in two sizes and three colors). | | amazon.comPromising review: "I recently moved into a home with hard water and the dishwasher needed cleaning. One cycle with this cleaner and it looks perfect! I will continue to use this product once a month as recommended. :-)" â€”MorgysMomGet a three-pack from Amazon for $19.99. | amazon.comIt's safe for unwaxed, non-oiled, polyurethane-finished wood flooring. Just spray it on wood and wipe with a mop or Swiffer.Promising review: "I moved into an apartment with absolutely disgusting wood floors. Whenever I would walk on it my feet would turn black. I used this product as well as a rag and a cleaning brush. It worked very well and now Iâ€™m not scared or grossed-out walking on my floors! The pictures are 'before' and 'afters' from cleaning." â€”fwkGet it from Amazon for $7.97. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "After running eufy for nearly two months now, I can confidently say I absolutely LOVE it! It is amazing on my hardwood floors. It picks up sooo much fine dust brought in by my two German Shepards! They shed year-round! And itâ€™s super effective with pet hair! Wow! I use Eufy once a day for a little more than hour, emptying and cleaning the brushes out about three to four times during use. It seriously has been life-changing, keeping my floors cleaner than sweeping! Great purchase and I would highly recommend!!" â€”Jacqueline MGet it from Amazon for $159.99 (originally $229; also available in white). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I had the previous Hoover carpet cleaner and it worked well, but I always dreaded using it because it was time consuming to wash, rinse, and dry. This Smartwash is incredible and so easy to use. I love that it does the wash when you push and the rinse/dry when you pull back. I finished in half the time!!!! I love that I can just use it as if itâ€™s a regular vacuum and it does all the hard work for me! I canâ€™t say enough good things!!!!" â€”John and MeganGet it from Amazon for $198 (originally $249.99). | amazon.comThis portable carpet cleaner will spray, brush, and suction up any stain, no adult supervision needed. It also comes with a hose and tool attachment if you'd prefer a more hands-on cleaning session.Promising review: "I have an older pug and he has always been good, but I knew one day this machine would be brought out. I had it nine months before my first use. He got sick one week, and I literally used the machine about 12 times in a week. All I can say is Bissell knocked it our of the park with this. Itâ€™s amazing. It cleans so well. It is the simplest machine I have ever used that does so much. It is well designed. Quick set up. And clean up. It does all the work for you. And it does a fantastic job. I love it. Worth every penny. Iâ€™ll never be without one. If you are on the fence, buy it. I canâ€™t believe how good this machine works. And the design is flawless. The tanks are so easy to fill. And clean for storage. And if it can clean 100% of what we had this week. It can clean anything!!! Like it never even happened. Thank you Bissell!!!" â€”DavidGet it from Amazon for $149 (originally $179.99). | amazon.comPromising review: "Throw away your other bathroom descalers and shower cleaners and use this. I get mineral spots on the glass wall and mineral buildup on the shower head causing the shower to spray water to the sides, and a quick soak in this product clears the shower head of minerals, cleans the glass completely, and leaves your shower looking brand new." â€”R. EnglishGet it from Amazon for $19.38. | amazon.comPromising review: "Holy crap!! Are you skeptical when it comes to buying stuff online? ME TOO! That's why I figured all of these rave reviews were a crock of crap. I've seriously bought every kind of vacuum out there, including the Roomba, which is about as intelligent as a cotton swab. But I have four cats and a golden retriever, so I was getting desperate! I believe the saying isâ€¦ a picture is worth a thousand words. Check mine out (above)! Of note â€” the 'before' picture was taken of my dog's bed AFTER it went through the washer and dryer. Look at all of that left-behind hair!!! And the 'after' picture was taken after only THREE MINUTES spent vacuuming her bed. I. Am. SOLD! BTW, I've NEVER taken the time to review a product before, just FYI." â€”Luka ChanGet it on Amazon for $30.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Our tub/shower has a grippy bottom, and scum and dirt cakes on it so easily. The only way I've been able to get it off before was literally scraping it inch by inch. I've spent hours and all it ever got was somewhat clean â€” never enough for me to want to take a real bath in it. This stuff is expensive but with the good reviews I decided to try it. It works amazingly!! I sprayed it on (it came with a great spray nozzle and a lid) and left it for about 15 to 20 minutes. Then I took a brush with hard plastic bristles (I believe a soft brush would have even worked) and with less than 20 minutes of scrubbing the entire tub and walls it was cleaner than when we moved in. The grime and scum almost like melted off. It smells pleasant. It's not crazy-strong smelling, but in an enclosed space I still felt the need to wear a mask while cleaning." â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $18.88. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Amazon, amazon.comIt comes with the brush spinner, charging station, eight rubber collars that securely connect the makeup brush to the spinner, a glass bowl, and a splash guard ring. Promising review: "I use my makeup brushes daily, and they get filthy. I've used other cleaners and this product wins hands down. The wand and the cleaner itself takes all the hard work and does it for you, not to mention the the brushes dry in seconds. This is the cleanest my brushes have ever been. Highly recommend." â€”ValerieGet it from Amazon for $49.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comThere's also a built-in squeegee for wiping up liquids or for cleaning glass. Plus, the handle extends from 36 to 60 inches so it can reach practically any mess.Promising review: "I bought this broom based on the tons of great reviews and I am not disappointed. I love this broom! It is lightweight but sturdy. I have used it on tile floors and carpet and it does a great job of getting the pet hair, lint, and dirt. I like this so much better than our traditional push broom. It is very easy to clean after use just using my hand, unlike our old broom. It also has a telescoping handle so that you can adjust it to whatever height you need. There is also a squeegee for doing the house windows and the car windows. I highly recommend it." â€”Joyce VGet it from Amazon for $14.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "I'll let my pictures (above) speak to how amazing this works. I had a stained mattress that I'd been covering with a mattress pad for years. As I was preparing for a move, I decided to give OxiClean a try and see if it could remove the stains that had been there for well over SEVEN YEARS. I honestly don't even know what caused the stains, but OxiClean removed them. I took before, during, and after pictures (after pictures show the outline of water because I took them immediately after rinsing. I honestly can't believe the results. I wish I'd done this sooner!" â€”Little GreekGet it from Amazon for $12.98. | amazon.comPromising review: "When we bought our home, there was no water softener and years of iron buildup. We tried so many things on our shower. Nothing worked. We were convinced weâ€™d be stuck until we renovated the bathroom. The Iron Out worked wonders. I still canâ€™t believe it. We had to let it sit for about an hour. It then dissolved and wiped right off. Definitely use in a ventilated area if possible." â€”M. GilardiGet it from Amazon for $3.80+ (available in two versions). | amazon.comPromising review: "Where has this been all my crazy cat-loving life? Sticky rollers work fine for clothes, but this is the only product that has ever COMPLETELY removed all the cat hair from my bed. I have a long-haired 20-pound tabby and if you run your hands up his back a few times and fling the hair everywhere, it looks like it's snowing â€” he never stops shedding no matter what I do. After using the ChomChom, I can put on a black dress and roll around on my bed and not get a single hair on me. It's absolutely amazing. Everyone is getting one for Christmas, even if they don't have a pet. I don't care, it's THAT good." â€”StephanieGet it from Amazon for $24.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "Something I didn't believe until I tried it. So easy to follow directions, written on Angry Mama. Was disappointed when I opened the microwave to see the filth still on it. Was wishing it would magically taken care of itself. But all it took was a quick swipe with a paper towel and GONE. Loosened everything, which is half the process. My microwave was sooooo white once cleaned!! Would buy as gifts." â€”max's mumGet it from Amazon for $9.58. | amazon.comWe recommend picking up some reusable cleaning gloves before you begin your disinfecting. If you want to save yourself from getting down on your hands and knees to scrub, one reviewer suggested using a broom so you can both stand *and* clean a larger surface area.Promising review: "Weâ€™re on a well so we have very hard water. Recently the water got super rusty and left horrible stains in the shower that would not come out. This was the only thing that worked and it worked GREAT! I just used a damp sponge to scrub it in and all of the rust stains came out. For the lighter spots it took maybe one swipe to clean which was incredible. For the super dark spots it took a little elbow grease but it got it out. I am absolutely amazed and will always use this from now on. I highly recommend it for tough-to-clean hard water stains." â€”Amanda A. Get it from Amazon for $8.28.Read our review of Bar Keepers Friend and how one writer used it to deep clean her new apartment. | amazon.comPromising review: "Our poor older pup started having some incontinence issues and had several accidents in the house. I was really frustrated until I found these. They work amazingly well. They're small, so if the area was larger I had to use two or three, but they pulled up stains and saved the house from being smelly. I even used one on an older stain (that I'm pretty sure wasn't pet related) and it came up after leaving it on for about 24 hours. I make sure to keep a supply of these in the house at all times now." â€”MCGet a pack of 20 from Amazon for $24.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Iâ€™ve been trying to switch all my cleaning products over to biodegradable or biocompatible, but I still expect them to work. I bought this because my shower stall doors are supposed to be transparent but were actually a mess of fog, hard water deposits, and other foul substances. Nothing I used cleaned the doors at all. I tried this and scrubbed my doors twice with it. Not only did it actually clean my doors but it lacks gross fumes and smells quite pleasant." â€”A. Via Get it from Amazon for $12.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "Be sure to use hot water; even though it won't foam as much it seems to do a lot better job. The first time I used these on a Contigo travel mug I used room-temp water, and it just came out OK. For the next travel mug, I used boiling water and the results were terrific. It looks new again. Then I used two cubes (and boiling water) in a large old pressure cooker that had become brown inside from years of making vegetable soups, and I'm amazed how clean it came out. That pressure cooker stain persisted throughout dozens of scrubbing sessions and dishwasher runs, so I figured the Bottle Bright wouldn't help either but it did." â€”MisterPlowGet 12 tablets from Amazon for $8. | amazon.comPromising review: "My shower floor is a bumpy, plastic material that has been a thorn in my side for a couple of years. I have used bleach, chlorine, tile cleaners, Soft Scrub, and Clorox bathroom spray (which usually cleans everything). I have even soaked cloths in bleach and let them sit on the area to see if that would work. None of them have removed the stains. I only had about 10 minutes before having to leave for work, so I only cleaned half so I could see the difference. It was amazing! I sprayed it on, let it sit for about five minutes (not sure if I needed to do that, but figured if bleach wouldn't clean it that nothing would), then used my usual cleaning brush. I didn't even have to scrub....just minimal circular motions and viola! The stains are gone! I couldn't be more pleased. The stains were there for over two years and with only five minutes of sitting and less than a minute of scrubbing, it looks like a new shower again. There are a couple of small areas that probably need a little more brushing, but like I said, I literally spent less than a minute with the brush. I highly recommend this product. And, no, I am not getting paid anything to say this. I very rarely review products unless I believe in them and this one is a keeper!" â€”MakadamiaGet it from Amazon for $5.51. | amazon.comPromising review: "I let my tub get extra dirty on purpose because I knew this brush set was coming. In five minutes my tub was sparkling clean. This item is no joke. The flat brushes are awesome for big surfaces and the cone brush hits the hard to reach corners. I liked them so much I bought a set for my mom." â€”Jason B.Get it from Amazon for $14.95+ (available in soft, medium, stiff, and ultra stiff bristles). | amazon.comPromising review: "This stuff is seriously amazing! I am relentless about cleaning my tub because I use it so often and always get grossed out if I donâ€™t. Before I purchased this, I used the typical homemade recipe of bleach and powdered dishwashing soap. Iâ€™d have to run two or three cycles to get it crystal clear. One cycle with this stuff, 15 minutes, and the results are amazing! The first photo (above) is with my tub running with the solution. Then I drained it (second photo) and wiped it down with a sponge. When I refilled the tub up, and reran the jets, I kid you not the water was CRYSTAL CLEAR! See for yourself in the last photo! Iâ€™m so impressed!" â€”ChelseaGet it from Amazon for $16.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "This stuff is incredible. My rental apartment has a white glass cooktop and it gets nasty even if you use very clean pots and pans on it. Before I found this stuff, I thought that for sure I would lose a big chunk of my security deposit, but I have yet to encounter a stain that this stuff cannot remove. Sometimes it takes a couple of tries alternating between the paste and the razor scraper, but even the most stubborn burned-on, carbonized food bits always come off." â€”MaxGet it from Amazon for $11.03. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "First, let me say I never clean my oven because hate it so much! It had years of baked-on drippings on the bottom and the usual brown crud that forms on the sides and shelves. After reading reviews, I decided to give it a try. It works wonders! My oven looks great and it was so easy. Follow the directions and all the bad stuff just wipes away! I've even used it on other stubborn stains on baking pans. Highly recommended!!" â€”E. NyquistGet it from Amazon for $6.44. | amazon.comPromising review: "Totally impressed! The unassuming generic packaging and label left me a bit skeptical but this stuff is almost as exciting as the wine I spilled! This cabernet stain sat on my ivory faux fur blanket for over a month before I tried this product. Completely gone in one try! Get this. Seriously. You wonâ€™t be disappointed." â€”PersianTessGet it from Amazon for $6.67. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Content Body: Shopping | 17 Tips & Products The BuzzFeed Shopping Team Swears By For Working From Home | From our couch to yours. | Posted on March 25, 2020, 18:01 GMT | March 25, 2020, 18:01 GMT | Maitland QuitmeyerBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | | | BuzzFeed / Heather Braga, Nordstrom"I do not work in PJs. I get dressed up like I'm actually about to head out for errands or something, including putting on comfy sneakers. It helps me get my mindset right." â€”Marquaysa Battle"I work in PJs when I WFH, BUT I change into clean PJs. Or if you have a 'good' set of PJs (like the stuff you wear on a group trip where other ppl see your PJs) slip into those. I'm never going to wear jeans while WFH but I'll put on clean pajama pants at least." â€”Elizabeth Lilly"I've had trouble with the 'dress as if you're going to work' advice (I wanna be comfy) so I tweaked it to be 'dress in a way you would never ever leave the house.' It motivates me to actually change clothes (I get to plan out a very weird outfit) and it'll be fun to see how out of control my outfits get by the end of the week. Today is head-to-toe buffalo check." â€”Bek O'Connell"Iâ€™m doing a Disney T-shirt challenge. Wearing a Disney shirt every single day I WFH as a fun way to see how much of a magical shirt collector I really amâ€¦" â€”Heather BragaThe tee Heather is wearing on the left is available at Fantasyland Apparel for $30 (available in sizes Sâ€“2X and in white). Title Headline: 23 Stress-Reducing Things For Your Workspace To Help You Calm Down A Little

Content Body: Shopping | 23 Stress-Reducing Things For Your Workspace To Help You Calm Down A Little | Whether your current workspace is a desk, a couch, a bed, or a kitchen table, you're gonna want these. | Posted on March 26, 2020, 14:00 GMT | March 26, 2020, 14:00 GMT | Katy HermanBuzzFeed Staff | Chronicle Books, Sarah Han/BuzzFeedGet it from Barnes & Noble for $15.72, Chronicle Books for $16.95, or from Bookshop (to support local booksellers) for $15.59. | | | HomesickGet the Grandma's Kitchen candle (with notes of apple and butter) for $29.95 and the Beach Cottage candle (with notes of bergamot and sandalwood) for $29.95, both from Homesick. | Knock KnockPromising review: "I use these daily to lift my mood and remind myself that I'm a badass!" â€”SyniGet a deck of 50 from Knock Knock for $14. | PrincetonPieces/Etsy, EmbellishMyWorld/EtsyGet the chonky hamster pen from PrincetonPieces on Etsy for $2.99 (available in four colors) and the narwhal pen from EmbellishMyWorld on Etsy for $2.25 (available in four colors). | Urban OutfittersPromising review: "I use these in my dorm since I have no control over the heater, and they really help in a pinch when my feet are cold as I'm writing essays." â€”odetteb Get them from Urban Outfitters for $35 (available in three colors). | Best BuyPromising review: "I spend A LOT of time at my desk so I decided I need to find the way to do some exercise. I found it. This product is very quiet â€” my coworkers sitting next to me don't even notice or hear a thing when I start pedaling. Easy and quick to assemble â€” it took me less than 30 minutes. Well-packaged out of the box and sturdy pedal straps. LCD monitor is removable and can be extended to be placed on top of a desk for display." â€”LityGet it from Best Buy for $139.99. | REIPromising review: "Although designed primarily for feet and hands, it can be used for arms, calves, neck, and even the quads, hamstrings, and hips. It really helped loosen all the tension and knots." â€”Golf nut in NoviGet it from REI for $24.95. | Pusheen ShopThe pages tear out easily, so you can turn your masterpieces into adorable workspace decor!Get it from Pusheen Shop for $7.80 or Barnes & Noble for $7.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | The Paper StoreGet the lemur or the avocado from The Paper Store for $19.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 20 Small Acts Of Kindness During The Coronavirus Quarantine That Will Restore Your Faith In Humanity
Short Description Sub Headline: People can be good.
Content Body: 20 Small Acts Of Kindness During The Coronavirus Quarantine That Will Restore Your Faith In Humanity | People can be good. | Posted on March 16, 2020, 19:14 GMT | March 16, 2020, 19:14 GMT | Farrah PennBuzzFeed Staff Writer | Jackie Borchardt@JMBorchardt | Jackie Borchardt | @JMBorchardt | My elderly neighbor is self-isolating. Title Headline: 45 Clever Little Ways To Store Almost Everything In Your Home
Short Description Sub Headline: Imagine a world where you open a drawer or cabinet and everything doesn't fall out.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 45 Clever Little Ways To Store Almost Everything In Your Home | Imagine a world where you open a drawer or cabinet and everything doesn't fall out. | Posted on January 24, 2020, 13:00 GMT | January 24, 2020, 13:00 GMT | Elena GarciaBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Wow! I can find my socks, hose, bras, and scarves again! Great organizers! It helps clear clutter and makes putting together great outfits so much easier! So glad I got them! I hope to order more! Also, no more solo socks!" â€”H.j.Get a set of four from Amazon for $12.97+ (available in seven colors). | | AmazonPromising review: "It was always a pain to reach down the side of my bed to reach my chargers, not to mention the wad of cables Iâ€™d have to sift through just to charge my phone. I finally searched for a solution and came across these. Theyâ€™re great! Theyâ€™re really easy to stick on and they stay in place. I havenâ€™t had an issue of them falling off. Whenever I need to charge a device theyâ€™re right next to me, easy to reach and untangled. I definitely recommend!" â€”Nelis PerezGet a pack of six from Amazon for $6.97. | amazon.comPromising review: "I love the crap out of this thing! I have so many camis that I use as undershirts for work and they were always being folded up and crammed into a drawer, taking up way too much space. After putting away half of my shirts on this two-pack, I knew I needed to buy another pack! It's so easy to take the shirts on and off without messing around with any of the others. This organizer is perfect for my needs in freeing up a drawer and taking up little space in my closet." â€”TessaGet a two-pack from Amazon for $9.99+. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Exactly as advertised! I've got mine on the counter, with the feet on it, but I'm considering taking them off and sliding it in the cupboard. Right now the novelty and organizational prettiness of it has me smitten. I'd say it's pretty much exactly worth the price, and this was the best price everywhere I looked, even including places where I could have used a 20% coupon." â€”Gigi Marie Get it from Amazon for $9.99+ (available in black, red and white). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "These come with their hangers and will add considerable storage. I put one on the inside of our pantry door and the second on the back of the door going from laundry room to garage. I initially was interested in getting one for the pantry, but the second was a nice bonus and it makes a great place to hold cleaning supplies. Well-made, excellent price." â€”KimberleeGet a two-pack from Amazon for $12.97. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "Sturdy! The weight limit says 30 lbs., but I'm 99% sure I'm over that and the bar is still straight as a board. I recommend measuring the distance from your main closet bar, the average length of the clothes, and seeing if the remaining length leaves enough room for the second row to hang without touching the floor (unless you don't mind it)." â€”M. GeeGet it from Amazon for $22.04. | AmazonPop them right out when you need to clean them!Promising review: "This is one of my favorite things I've ever purchased from Amazon! The fact that they are so customizable allows you to cut them for any drawer size! I think this will be my go-to gift for all of my friends who love cooking as much as I do! Freeing up cabinet space and having something that can easily be rinsed off in the sink makes this a for-sure buy!" â€”momononoGet a pack of six on Amazon for $15.99. | AmazonPromising review: "THESE ARE SO MUCH BIGGER AND NICER IN PERSON!! Really, they are so great! I love them! And yes, I am a grown-up but I thought they would make storing stuff at my office more fun and they stack easily. I WAS RIGHT!! SO MUCH FUN AND REALLY HANDY! Whether you buy them for your kids or you buy them for yourself, they are GREAT for storage and stack just like giant Legos and are SO WORTH THE MONEY!!" â€”Sean T. FlynnGet them from Amazon for $10.49+ (available in small, medium, and large sizes and in a variety of colors). | AmazonPromising review: "It is so great to have a high-quality knife set. The pieces have a very nice weight to them. The various knives make easy work when cutting/slicing both uncooked and meats, seafood, bread, tomatoes, onions â€” heck, everything I've cut thus far has been a breeze. Also, the knife block continually sharpens the pieces. Literally the best set I've owned. Love them." â€”MeSharonnaGet a 15-piece set from Amazon for $112.99. | AmazonPromising review (for the over-the-door organizer): "Oh my goodness, I should've gotten something like this long ago. Everything is available at a glance and it's all organized. I don't have to take everything out of my cupboard just to find the one I'm looking for. And it doesn't take up tons of space in my coat closet. I can do a quick inventory of what I'm running out of. It's also a great place to keep a pair of scissors and tape high up out of the reach of my toddlers." â€”daiseyworldGet the organizer from Amazon for $8.14 and the over-the-door organizer for $13.32. There's also a really great gift bag organizer if that's more your jam. | AmazonPromising review: "Love these sooo much I bought three! I use them to hold rice, homemade breadcrumbs, and coconut flour. The caps make a nice airtight lid and they're very convenient to use, always right where you need them to be. The sizing on the bin itself is a little tall, so I store these lying down in my cabinets, otherwise, they don't fit. If you are looking for something to store your grains/powders/crumbs/seeds/cereal/whatever in, these bins are AWESOME." â€”ChrisGet it from Amazon for $12.95. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I love it!! I wanted to do a huge apartment cleanse and finally get everything organized and orderly. My apartment's shelving and cabinets are awkward but this product does the trick and allows me to utilize the dead space underneath my sink. Now I don't have to sift around when I need something, I can see where it is! One of the shelves did have a minor dent when it arrived, but I don't really care since it's an under-the-sink shelving unit. It has not comprised the quality or function of this product." â€”XtinaGet it from Amazon for $19.87+ (available in three finishes). | AmazonPromising review: "It actually fits my size 13 shoes! Not a fan of the color but when something this useful comes along for me, who cares? I mean, it is behind the closet door. I recommend this for anyone who has large feet and is looking for an over-the-door shoe organizer." â€”C. CurateGet it from Amazon for $24.95 (available in two colors). | marthastewart.com, AmazonGet the storage container from Amazon for $11.99+ (available in four colors). | AmazonPromising review: "They have been working wonderfully. Having lots of vegetables chopped up and easily accessible without opening several containers has really sped up our morning lunch preparation time." â€”Magen R.Get a set of two from Amazon for $29.65+. | AmazonPromising review: "Just purchased my second set of these â€” they are perfect! I use them to protect my good frying pans, my Dutch ovens, nice glass bowls â€” anything where stacking is needed for space but I was worried about scratching. I love the neutral color, but with a cute, all-over pattern, and the size is great for deep bowls to protect the sides or large pans. Plus they are definitely the most cost-effective ones out there. I plan to buy more and also use as an add-on gift when giving cookware." â€”Sno-cone loverGet a set of six from Amazon for $9.69+ (available in six sizes). | AmazonPromising review: "This is the product I didnâ€™t know always needed. The little map is so cute and both my 1-year-old and 4-year-old enjoy playing. The best part is when theyâ€™re done I just pull the drawstring and clean up is over. It makes moving the play space and cleaning up so easy. I wish I found this before. Highly recommend." â€”AnonymousGet it from Amazon for $39.99. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "The perfect thing for all the remotes! Attractive, sturdy, plus well-made and stylish. Just ordered two more." â€”DPGet it from Amazon for $10.99. | AmazonGet it from Amazon for $125+ (available in black and brown). | amazon.comGet it from Amazon for $18.69+ (available in three sizes and in black, white, and green). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 52 Valentine's Day Gifts For When You're Totally In Love, But Broke

Content Body: Shopping | | Gift Ideas | Under $50 | 52 Valentine's Day Gifts For When You're Totally In Love, But Broke | I hate how much I love Valentine's Day. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 01:01 GMT | January 31, 2020, 01:01 GMT | Mallory MowerBuzzFeed Staff | | | AmazonThe box includes 100 unique conversation starters ranging from basic and lighthearted to more serious situations. Promising review: "This game, if we should call it a game, is so wonderful. We opened the box and just randomly started choosing out cards. Some of the cards were quick and straightforward, while other were more thought provoking. We got some good laughs out of this and it was truly a refreshing change compared to our previous casual conversations. I see this can being very useful for couples who want to get to know each other but also for couples like us, who are so busy in our day-to-day with the work and kids. It gave us something different to talk about outside the typical operational 'how was your day' type of conversations." â€”OritGet it from Amazon for $18.95. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This adventure book is really cute. I bought this because my boyfriend and I just moved into our first apartment together! It's a very exciting time for us and this adventure book was the perfect start to our new adventure. The brown pages are big enough to fit a good amount on each page. There are no plastic protectors. It is more like a scrapbook than a photo album. I love it. It looks just like the one from Up. Promising review: "I love these. I also received confirmation from her that they work wonders and truly provide an airtight seal." â€”ThomasGet a set of six from Amazon for $16.97. | AmazonPromising review: "This was a little bit of a gag gift for some friends but they absolutely adore it. Title Headline: 48 Practical Things To Buy That'll Help You Feel More Like A Grown-Up
Short Description Sub Headline: See, Mom? I'm Tom Hanks in Sleepless In Seattle, not Tom Hanks in Big.
Content Body: Shopping | 48 Practical Things To Buy That'll Help You Feel More Like A Grown-Up | See, Mom? I'm Tom Hanks in Sleepless In Seattle, not Tom Hanks in Big. | Posted on January 22, 2020, 14:01 GMT | January 22, 2020, 14:01 GMT | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Heather Braga / BuzzFeed, AmazonI'm obsessed with candles, so it was a no-brainer for my husband to gift me this surprisingly super fun gadget for Christmas. It's really simple to use and charge, and it really works! I'll never have to buy another lighter again.Promising review: "This is seriously the coolest device of my winter holiday. It makes lighting candles a breeze. Yes, there is a weird crackling noise, but that's a super minor annoyance. It's a super intuitive device. Plus the lighter with the USB (included), charge for a bit, then pop it open and light ALL THE THINGS; well, candles. I don't know how well it lights cigarettes or whatever. However, for my personal intended use, it's awesome!" â€”Jee WGet it from Amazon for $13.99. | AmazonPromising review: "I ordered this planner because it had everything I required of my weekly planner: Month at a glance; week at a glance; section at the end of each month for notes; mission board and even a straight edge ruler was included! The binding is very sturdy, like a hardcover book and not flimsy like many other planners being sold. There's also a section with pockets to hold my stickers. After many years of using Outlook, CRM, etc, sometimes it's just nice to go back to what has always worked well since the beginning of time! Why complicate things right? I also believe it's much better to write instead of type when it comes to goals and tasks. It helps our brains work better in the long run." â€”Pershing140Get it from Amazon for $14.99+ (available in two styles). | | AmazonPromising review: "These work amazingly well. I was surprised that you can charge and use them at the same time. I use them on planes to listen to the in-flight entertainment with my AirPods. I also use them to listen to music on my laptop with my AirPods. They work really well. Now, I don't have to carry my wired earbuds with me when I travel anymore. They really work as advertised. I have not had any issues with them since I started using them." â€”RPLGet it from Amazon for $40.49+ (available in three options). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Abby Kass / BuzzFeed, AmazonIt's the thinnest and lightest Kindle Amazon has released to date! And â€” as is made abundantly clear by the photo above â€” it's 100% waterproof. Promising review: "I love the fact that I can read on this Kindle in both daylight and dim light conditions. It is so light and compact, which makes it easy to hold, easy to travel with, and the battery lasts forever. I love it." â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $129.99.And check out our full breakdown of the Kindle Paperwhite here. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Billie / Via instagram.com, BillieBillie is a fantastic subscription service that let's you choose how often you need your razor refills then delivers them right to your doorstep. I recently tried my first Billie razor and, OMG, my legs have never been smoother. They seriously have a handle style for everyone â€” including their new "Glow" razor that, you guessed it, glows in the dark! My coworker Rachel Dunkel is also a BIG fan of Billie razors and their other products. Here's what she had to say:"For the last five years or so, I haven't cared that much about shaving. I'd let my legs and pits grow into a (beautiful!) forest, but whenever I craved a nice, smooth shave and picked up a razor from the drugstore, I'd end up disappointed. Even with more expensive razor brands, I'd still be prickly and end up regretting ever shaving in the first place. I have never, ever had that problem with Billie. Ever since trying their razors and shave cream, I've actually *wanted* to keep up with shaving. You get a ridiculously smooth result on the first go, even if your hair is super grown out. But most importantly, it STAYS that way for way longer than with other brands. With Billie, it actually feels worth the time and money to shave, something that I could never say about any other razor."Check out our full review on the Billie razor subscription here.Get it from Billie for $9+ (available in six colors). | amazon.com, AmazonHonestly, no matter which version of the Dyson stick vacuum you purchase, I can promise you'll be satisfied with the results. I've used a variety of 'em and I can't say enough good things about the product. It doesn't hurt my back to use for an extended period of the time, the battery lasts long enough to clean my entire apartment, and it simply just WORKS. We have ours mounted in a narrow spot alongside our fridge â€” it's really easy to keep in plain sight without being an eyesore.Promising review: "I love this vacuum. The V10 doesn't disappoint. While it's weird to get used to holding this tiny piece of machinery, it really does an amazing job. It was incredible how much dog fur it picked up! I was pretty grossed out to be honest, to think I lived in this atmosphere for this long 'thinking' it was clean is nuts! I love all the attachments too, they are all top notch and well made. I feel like I can tackle my entire house with this bad boy. AND it's lightweight! I use it on the lowest setting and it still picks up a ton. I don't think I'll ever need the high or medium setting. But I did try the highest setting for a few seconds and literally felt like the vacuum was ATTACHED to the floor, that's how hard it sucked (in a good way)!" â€”Matthew MintunGet the V10 from Amazon for $349+ (available in three styles). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedMy fellow BuzzFeed editor Maitland Quitmeyer loves this thing. Here's what she had to say:"The acne scars on my cheeks from a series of breakouts are fading fast, and I get new acne very rarely â€” they're more like a pimple here and there occasionally when I have to fly somewhere (curse you, dry airplanes) or get stressed or.... who even knows why my skin freaks out sometimes. Never thought I'd ever put a no-makeup selfie on the internet, but that's how much I love this thing." Check out our full review of the FOREO LUNA Mini 2 here!Get it from Amazon for $139+ (available in six colors). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising Review: "LOVE THESE! They are a beautiful shade of gray, well-made and a perfect price! I ordered these to help protect against hair-breakage and I've already noticed a huge difference!!!" â€”shawnellnewberryGet them from Amazon for $9.98 (available in three sizes and 16 colors) | AmazonPromising review: "These are wonderful socks. Soft and warm and not itchy at all like socks with such a high percentage of wool can be. They fit perfectly, hugging your foot instead of slipping around like a sloppy mess. Love the muted colors as well. Thinking about getting more in other colors!" â€”Debra A. ScottGet a five-pair pack from Amazon for $11.99 (available in 11 styles). | AmazonPromising review: "I was kind of shocked at how good quality these straws are! They come in a neat little baggie that you can store them in, and the straw cleaner as well! I don't usually leave reviews on products (even if I really like them), but they donate 100% of the proceeds of your order to OCEANA if you leave a review, and that's a HUGE plus for me. So not only do I really like the product, I get to share the good news through this review AND my payment gets donated to OCEANA. I really really appreciate that. 10/10 product!" â€”Amazon CustomerGet a pack of 10 from Amazon for $8.95. | amazon.comMy sister bought this for me and I'm obsessed with it â€” which is why I know it's awesome! It's my favorite thing to start my pampering with, but I also use it in the morning before I apply any makeup. All you have to do is pop the separate roller piece into your freezer and you'll be ready to de-puff in no time.Promising review: "Extremely affordable and feels great on my face right when I wake up in the morning!! I can feel the difference after a couple of rolls along my puffy eyes and face. It soothes my puffiness with the cold but bearable feeling. And it does stay cool for a good amount of time. Best thing is its not a watery mess." â€”Tammy N.Get it from Amazon for $11.99 (available in eight colors). | AmazonI have this little foam roller and use it almost every night. I roll my spine over it and it releases all the tension in a series of very satisfying cracks. Get one â€” add it into your pre-bedtime ritual!Promising review: "My chiropractor recommended I buy the 36" version of this for some daily routine back stretching to do at home. This product has been amazing for stretching, and massaging sore muscles throughout my back and shoulders. I feel very supported by this roller and have had no issues with it thus far. I weigh 200 pounds and have yet to damage this roller after weeks of use. Overall very pleased with this product. And at such a great price, I honestly can't find a single negative remark to note about it." â€”Luke MarrsGet it from Amazon for $8.45+ (available in four sizes and seven styles). | AmazonYou can even pop these in the washing machine for a thorough cleaning.Promising review: "After my husband sliced his finger on our mandolin I decided to check out these gloves. We are both very impressed with how well they work. The company who sells these is also wonderful â€” they sent a follow-up email to ensure that we liked the gloves and would have replaced or refunded our money if we weren't happy. The only thing I was concerned about when I ordered the gloves was if I was buying the right size. My husband and I have different hand sizes, but the medium is working well for both of us. And knowing that they would send a different size free of charge was wonderful. Now we don't have to worry about slicing off our fingers!" â€”That Author Guy's WifeGet them from Amazon for $11.49 (available in sizes Sâ€”XL). | amazon.comPromising review: "Love how little space these take up. My closet is pretty small so getting these types of hangers was a must. Clothes donâ€™t slip from the hangers which is nice because with the plastic ones, my tank tops and dresses would always fall off. You can even hang pants too. " â€”AmazonianCheck out our deep dive on the AmazonBasics Velvet Suit Hangers here!Get them from Amazon for $14.99+ (available in packs of 30, 50, or 100 and three colors) | Amazon, amazon.comI have one of these cool cups and have been really impressed with it. I recently used it early one morning when I was craving a cup of hot tea but had to run some errands. It pops open really easily, feels very durable, and keeps my drink hot.Promising review: "Love this cup. I was originally turned off to it due to the size of the top section, however it's not as big as it looks online and it's the perfect size. It will fit most purses but not likely women's pant pockets. After filling it with water I shook the cup and there was no leaking. Even after I finished my latte and collapsed the cup there was no residue leakage at all. The cup didn't get excessively hot either. The cup also had mL markers on the inside which is wonderful. I highly recommend this product!" â€”HRGet it from Amazon for $15 (available in 4 sizes and 16 colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I have incredibly fine hair that's super thick and frizzy. It's kind of a nightmare. My hair is prone to monster knots- I came back from summer camp once with a mat in my hair like a dog. Other hair brushes tend to rip my hair out because of the knotty-ness and fine strands. This brush is fantastic. The only thing I don't like about it is it took me 25 years to find it. I can actually brush my hair with minimal pain and hair loss. It works like a charm and I can brush my hair quicker and more thoroughly than with any other brush I've used." â€”Amazon CustomerGet a set of two from Amazon for $14.47+ (available in three styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comThis seemingly average little cleaning pen is filled with a high-performance formula that cleans jewelry like nothing I've ever experienced. It contains micro-fine cleansers, polishing agents, and a polymer that will make your gems so shiny they'll nearly blind you. I've used it on my diamond rings, but it also works wonders on my cubic zirconia earrings. Check out my full review of the Connoisseurs 1050 Diamond Dazzle Stick.Promising review: "The center stone of my ring (an oval white sapphire) has been cloudy since shortly after I got it. I have to use a lot of hand sanitizer at work, which gets under the stone. This product was easy to use. The little brush gets under the stone really well (much better than a toothbrush). My ring looks like new." â€”FintanCatGet it from Amazon for $8.78. | MadewellI've gotten one of these as a gift and have given one to my sister as well. It's my favorite bag to date! It has a small pocket inside you can pop your phone into (or anything else you'd be looking to grab in a hurry) and has so much space. I've even fit my laptop into it! The straps are sturdy and I love that this version also has a chic suede stripe down the middle. The best part? You can add your initials for an extra special touch.Get it from Madewell for $158 (available in three colors). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Food52Promising review: "I love this apron! Iâ€™m a petite 5â€™3â€ and get why some similar sized people may feel itâ€™s too big but I love the way it fits. Itâ€™s a heavier weight which makes it feel like a lot on my small frame at first but I donâ€™t mind the extra length and feel very protected. Pot holder pockets still work length-wise for me and I have not gotten a stain or ruined my actual clothing since I got this. Maybe Iâ€™m a messier cook than most but other thinner, smaller aprons didnâ€™t provide the same protection. Itâ€™s a bonus that it fits my tall husband too." â€”Caroline F.Get it from Food52 for $45 (available in one size and five colors). | Amazon, amazon.comMy dog personally hates the car, so taking all 80 pounds of him to the groomer is often a struggle (to say the least). By using this attachment he can clean up without feeling anxious. The unique wand is curved to provide full coverage while washing your pet. It also has an 8-foot-long flexible hose for extended reach and be used indoors or outdoors.Promising review: "Owners of long-haired/thick-coated breeds: This is what you've been looking for. I've waited over 20 years for this and have used everything from custom heads to kitchen wash heads. The water flow from this even at low pressure (40 psi) is excellent, adjustment on handle are well-thought-out, and this WILL get right through a thick undercoat." â€”Animal DoctorGet it from Amazon for $33.01. | shophavly / Via instagram.com, HavlyI recently picked up one of these towels and it is unbelievably soft. It's thicker than most of my towels but seemingly takes up less space. The loop to hang it seems super sturdy which is an added bonus. Definitely pick up a set for each of your parents.Get it from Havly for $44 (available in five styles). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "After multiple containers for my brown sugar and continuously throwing my brown sugar away due to giant hard lumps, I began to wonder why our brown sugar never lumped as a child. That's when I remembered a weird brown bear in our sugar, After a quick Google search I found this! I soaked it in water for 30 minutes and then added to my lumpy brown sugar...two days later there is not a single lump in my sugar! Yay!" â€”SneezeloafGet it from Amazon for $5.61. | quip / Via instagram.com, quip / Via instagram.comDoes you boast about being a minimalist? Or maybe you just have ZERO counter space? Then the Quip might just be the toothbrush of their dreams. It has a three-month battery life, comes with a wall mount and travel case, and is super quiet during use. I own one myself (as do my mom, mother-in-law, and father-in-law) and love how it encourages me to brush thoroughly.Promising review: "I truly love this toothbrush, feels great when done. Like the fact that it tells you when to move to the next quadrant. People in general do not take the two minutes to brush their teeth, much less concentrate on each quadrant and change the brush every three months. Anyway, I love it and will recommend it." â€”Maria S.Check out our full review of the Quip here.Get it from Quip for $25+ (available in eight colors and a variety of subscription plans). | amazon.com, AmazonIt combines six kitchen appliances in one, including a pressure cooker, slow cooker, rice cooker, sautÃ©, steamer, and warmer.Promising review: "Of all of the purchases that I've ever made to add to my kitchen's efficiency and fun, this is the one thing I could not do without. I ordered it after making a decision to cook with fresh ingredients in order to make my meals healthier. It took me awhile to gather data from online forums and various cookbooks and 'how to' resources before I actually opened the box and began my discovery journey. It's been a delicious one, indeed, not to mention how much time I am saving in the process." â€”DarleneGet it from Amazon for $59+ (available in 3, 6, and 8 quarts). | Amazon, amazon.comOne little machine that can whip up hard-boiled eggs, poached eggs, scrambled eggs, and omelettes? Sounds magical! And let me tell you â€” it is. Get one of these egg-cellent appliances ASAP. Read our deep dive into the Dash Rapid Egg Cooker.Promising review: "If you are on the fence about getting one of these, GET ONE. It really is as easy as it sounds to have a perfectly cooked egg, no guesswork. Just have an ice bath ready next to the cooker and let the eggs sit for a minute or two in there...peels come right off :) Makes healthy eating a breeze in the morning! Where has this been all my life!??!?" â€”rebeccaGet it from Amazon for $17.35+ (available in five colors). | Amazon, amazon.comI have one of these bad boys and can validate that it is SO easy to use. I pop my phone into it when I get in the shower and click the lil' button on the front to start the cleaning process. You can also charge your phone while it's inside the machine. Fellow germaphobes â€” you can thank me later.Promising review: "Bought this along with a set of agar plates to test it for ourselves. We swabbed my daughter's and husband's phones before and after use. It does work. We are very happy with the product." â€”GingerGet it from Amazon for $79.95+ (available in 10 colors). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 40 Cheap Things You Can Enjoy At Home While You're Getting Your Money's Worth On Rent
Short Description Sub Headline: Here's to avoiding spending lots of money on social interactions you didn't want to participate in anyway.
Content Body: Shopping | | Under $50 | 40 Cheap Things You Can Enjoy At Home While You're Getting Your Money's Worth On Rent | Here's to avoiding spending lots of money on social interactions you didn't want to participate in anyway. | Posted on January 29, 2020, 03:00 GMT | January 29, 2020, 03:00 GMT | Elizabeth LillyBuzzFeed Staff | | | | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review (for the diffuser): "I loved this product! As you can see the light button has rubbed off a bit because I use it so much! It has all colors of the rainbow, it goes for 11 hours, is easy to clean, and it looks great. Other diffusers I just couldnâ€™t say the same about. The only thing that I do have to warn is that you need to be careful about the oils you put in it or it can be ruined (from experience). This has lasted me sooo long and I am going to buy again! My sister bought first then I did she was bummed when hers no longer worked (from the bad oils)! Definitely recommend!!" â€”Happy Mom of 3Get them from Amazon: diffuser for $15.99+ (available in four colors) and eight essential oils for $14.95 | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "These masks are amazing!!! Having 'ice pick' scars left over from acne I was told that I'd have to pay for expensive laser therapy because the body can't produce enough collagen to heal deep scars. I've been using these masks for two months and I've seen SIGNIFICANT reduction in my scars. They are almost completely gone!" â€”ShaunGet them from Amazon for $10.99. | amazon.com, AmazonGet it from Amazon for $9.59+ (available in seven styles).Though if you're more into The Office, check out some versions with Prison Mike and Dwight wearing the CPR dummy mask. | AmazonGet three pens of varying brush sizes from Amazon for $6.99. | AmazonGet them from Amazon for $5.99+ (available in gold or black). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "Our son has been into comic drawing lately and he would draw his own lines/boxes on paper he stapled together! I saw this book while Christmas shopping and thought it would be great for him. He loves it!" â€”Ebiel and Erica CamachoGet it from Amazon for $5.99. | Amazon, amazon.comBTW, lots of reviewers have found success mixing this powder mask with organic ACV.Promising review: "I use the clay mask along with apple cider vinegar and let it sit on my face for 20â€“30 mins. I have been using it every single day but if you have sensitive skin, I don't recommend that. Tbh I have not been eating healthy 24/7 but it still works. Some days I forgot to put in on but in total I have used this mask over 10x. Just be patient and give it time." â€”Delandia StevensonGet it from Amazon for $9.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I have two cats, tried a de-shedder brush but they hate it and hide the second I take it out, so I was looking for other options and saw these gloves â€” it turned out to be a life-changer! To my surprise, cats absolutely love it! They even purr and roll around to make sure I didn't miss a spot. The layer of fur is easy to peel off from the glove and the more you collect the easier it gets. Now I am able to bruÂ­sh my cats every othÂ­er day, since they enjoy it so much, which means less fur on my clothes and everywhÂ­ere else. Very satisfied with this product and would recommend it to cat owners." â€”YanaGet a pair from Amazon for $12.99 (available in two colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I use this whenever I feel tired, and always after Iâ€™ve cleansed my face. I use rubbing alcohol to clean it after use and then put it back in the freezer in its own ziplock. I notice itâ€™s helped with the redness in my face and it also helped when Iâ€™ve had migraines. It starts behind my eye so I roll it over whichever side of my head is in pain and it seems to help." â€”maihiroGet it from Amazon for $11.99+ (available in eight color combos).

Title Headline: 42 Of The Best Valentine's Day Gifts For Men
Short Description Sub Headline: Love language: gift giving.
Content Body: Shopping | | Gift Ideas | 42 Of The Best Valentine's Day Gifts For Men | Love language: gift giving. | Posted on January 30, 2020, 10:00 GMT | January 30, 2020, 10:00 GMT | Alexandra NapoliBuzzFeed Staff | | Hill CitySince it's on the thinner side, it can be packed easily for any and every vacay you two take together.Promising review: "This jacket will remain a featured item in my wardrobe for a long time. Well-fitting and flexible to be worn for active use or while out and about. I've worked out in this jacket, worn it to work events, and slipped it on for a cool evening out with the family. It's lightweight, easily packable, looks cool, and keeps you dry in a downpour. You can't ask for more in a lightweight rain jacket." â€”Luke513Get it from Hill City for $148 (available in sizes Sâ€“XXL and three colors). | Hill CityPromising review: "They have been my go-to weekend pants, went for a casual bike ride, went to museums, to the playground with my son and I'm taking them running as well. I can't think of anything that performs better; I love that they feel windproof and just the right temperature to have while doing some light exercise; I love how they come tight on the ankles which makes them perfect for biking around since the pants won't get stuck or stained with the bike chain." â€”gossler88Get them from Hill City for $98 (available in sizes Sâ€“XXL and three colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comHere's what a past BuzzFeed writer has to say about it: â€œIâ€™ve had my Timex easy reader watch for close to two years now and it is STILL ticking along with no issues. The expandable band makes it super easy to put on and take off. And the gold tone still looks stunning after so many wears â€” because I rock it multiple times a week. It is simple to set the date and time, and the night-light feature is useful whenever I need a little assistance seeing the watchâ€™s face. If you are looking for an affordable watch that is still super stylish, this is the PERFECT choice.â€ â€”Treye Green â€¨Get it from Amazon for $35.75+ (available in three finishes). | AmazonPromising review: "I ordered two of these to display our record collection, which was stacked under our buffet. I no longer wanted our vinyl stacked and I was sick and tired of others flipping through them on the floor and then leaving them in a state of chaos. I have to say, we absolutely love these and will likely be purchasing more in the near future! They have exceeded my expectations. I love the practical, minimalist design. And my friends can now easily flip through our collection and play records without using our floor." â€”Kaci B.Get it from Amazon for $25+ (available in six finishes and two sizes). | NisoloPromising review: "I got these for my husband for Christmas and he's worn them almost every day. He loves the character of the waxed canvas and how it looks over time. They've broken in and fit him like a glove. The soles are super durable and great when he's caught in unexpected rain." â€”Sarah C.Get them from Nisolo for $288 (available in sizes 8â€“13 and five colors). | Uncommon GoodsThis kit makes 1 gallon and includes 100% malt extract, world-class specialty grains, fresh hop pellets, and high-quality yeast. This malty ale has a light copper hue, subtle bitterness from its Perle and Mt. Hood hops, caramel sweetness, and a clean, dry finish. Promising review: "My brother has always been interested in beer. This kit will allow him to easily create his own first batch; he will be so proud that he made his own beer at home!" â€”AdamGet it from Uncommon Goods for $45. | AmazonPromising review: "I like meditation but usually do it lying down. However, I recently got a puppy and decided to try this meditation pillow in order to relieve the back and neck pain I always experience while sitting on the floor for any reason. It worked wonders! I have tried other pillows like this in the past with no success. This one is superior in design, construction, height, and support. I will now also use it for meditation as well as for interacting with my puppy while playing on the floor with him. An attractive, fantastic pillow!" â€”Barbara CutreraGet it from Amazon for $29.99+ (available in six colors and two sizes).And check out our picks for the best meditation cushions on BuzzFeed Reviews! | Men's WarehousePromising review: "Exactly what I needed to add to and complement my wardrobe! The color, fit, and style of this jacket catches the eye and turns heads whenever I wear it." â€”Robert LGet it from Men's Warehouse for $72 (originally $179; available in sizes Sâ€“XXL and three colors). | AmazonPromising review: "This isa very solid piece. It's well-constructed and easily allows for straight lines. It comes with a useful guide with illustrations and is in an impressive package altogether. Overall great value for the price." â€”C in KSGet it from Amazon for $13.90. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "If you have the snow raining on your shirt every day from your amazing manly beard then you need to buy this stuff. It really helped hydrate and get my beard to a place where there is no beard dandruff to speak of. Keep your beard happy. Your shirt will thank you." â€”Colt and MissyGet it from Amazon for $12.22. | TicketmasterWhether your love likes to jam out to music or cheer in the stands of their favorite sport team's stadium, this a gift card will have you covered.Get it from Ticketmaster for $5â€“$500 (available as a digital or physical card). | Kayla Suazo/BuzzFeedHe can receive bags biweekly or monthly, with a selection from over 50+ countries. All ingredients are sourced via sustainable farming practices and as soon as you place the order, the beans are roasted, meaning he'll always get a fresh batch. AKA, Atlas is the subscription he's been dreaming of.Promising review: "My first observation after opening the box was the smell. It smells FAN-FREAKIN'-TASTIC. It also comes with sweet postcards from the cities where the batches are from, so the entire experience feels so lovely and personal. As for the coffee itself, it's heavenly. I am used to store-bought coffee â€” which yes, is fine â€” but both of these tasted incredibly fresh and different from each other. The Peruvian coffee has this dark, almost chocolate taste to it, so I imagine it would be delicious with a morning sweet treat (maybe I should start eating pie every day?). The Colombian batch, on the other hand, was a little lighter roast-wise but still had delicious notes of rich sweetness. TL;DR: both of them were incredible both in taste and quality." â€”Kayla SuazoGet a subscription from Atlas for $9+/month.And check out our full review of the Atlas coffee subscription here. | YetiPromising review: "Perfect for my daily lunch. I work road construction and it fits all my goodies and keeps them cool. Love the magnetic closure so nothing sneaks out when it gets moved or tossed around." â€”KayKay4Get it from Yeti for $79.99 (available in three colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: â€œI ordered a size 9, as there was no size 8.5. It fit just like an 8.5, which was perfect! My husband says that these shoes are extremely comfortable. Normally when buying a new pair of shoes, the heel can be stiff or too thin. These shoes have padding where the heal is to give you that extra bit of comfort.â€ â€”BH&Hâ€¨â€¨Get them from Amazon for $19.99+ (available in sizes 6-12.5 and 20 colors). | amazon.com, Hannah Loewentheil/BuzzFeedOne kit gets you garlic, kashmiri chili powder, crushed red pepper, cinnamon powder, smoked paprika, cumin seed, oregano, rosemary, cloves, turmeric, granulated onion, dark chili powder, ground yellow mustard, green cardamom powder, coriander seed, herbs de provence, fennel seed, and ground ginger.Promising review: "The variety and quality of each spice is amazing. I havenâ€™t been able to try every one yet, but the red pepper was amazing, the smoked paprika really popped, and our oatmeal was brought to another level with the cinnamon. I'm looking forward to using all these spices and the branding is so cute." â€”Hamilton M.Get the kit from Amazon for $95. And check out our review on the Spicewalla essential spices kit! | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I've been wearing these as my black dress shoes for almost a year. These have seen business meetings, the dance floor, snow, rain, broken glass, and just about any condition short of mountain hiking. They've held up very well and still look new after a polishing. Scuffs buff out very easily and the shoe doesn't have any creases from where my toe bends. It's a very high quality shoe." â€”Amazon CustomerGet them from Amazon for $68+ (available in sizes 7â€“17 and four colors; wide sizes also available). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Abby Kass / BuzzFeed, AmazonIt's the thinnest and lightest Kindle Amazon has released to date! And â€” as is made abundantly clear by the photo above â€” it's 100% waterproof. Promising review: "I love the fact that I can read on this Kindle in both daylight and dim light conditions. It is so light and compact, which makes it easy to hold, easy to travel with, and the battery lasts forever. I love it." â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $129.99+ (available in two colors).And check out our full breakdown of the Kindle Paperwhite here. | JCrewGet it from J.Crew for $148 (available in sizes XSâ€“XXL and three colors). | AmazonPromising review: "Bought this for my boyfriend and he loves it! It's thin so it fits into pant pockets more suitably. Has multiple compartments for cash and IDs. Tight enough fit in the compartments where you won't loose any thing you put in it." â€”RachelGet it from Amazon for $34. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

I really like the cross-cut feature because it utilizes more bin space. This means that itâ€™ll be able to hold more shreds of paper. Itâ€™s powerful and reliable, and I havenâ€™t had any problems with it since. I use it quite often and have only had to empty it once (out of the four months Iâ€™ve had it for). Its compact size makes it perfect for storing in tight spaces." â€”HandsONPrice: $36.99 | AmazonPromising review: "Best product I have bought in a long time. Keeps the kitchen cabinet so organized, you don't have to spend an hour searching for the right lid for a container." â€”DebbyPrice: $34.93 (set of 12) | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I absolutely love these baskets! They are a great storage solution for a smaller bathrooms or honestly any room. My toilet paper rolls fit well. It can do three across with a little room. Not quite long enough for four but thatâ€™s fine. It was nice it came with all the hardware to hang them all you needed was a drill or screwdriver." â€”MeganFromLVPrice: $35.21 | AmazonPlus, it has a snap-lock lid to keep odor to a minimum. Title Headline: 31 Gadgets You'll Probably Want To Try In 2020
Short Description Sub Headline: Inspector Gadget's got nothin' on you.
Content Body: Shopping | 31 Gadgets You'll Probably Want To Try In 2020 | Inspector Gadget's got nothin' on you. | Posted on January 06, 2020, 18:13 GMT | January 06, 2020, 18:13 GMT | Kat AngusBuzzFeed Staff, Canada | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Heather Braga / BuzzFeed, Amazon / Via amazon.caI'm obsessed with candles, so it was a no-brainer for my husband to gift me this surprisingly super fun gadget for Christmas. It's really simple to use and charge, and it really works! I'll never have to buy another lighter again.Get it from Amazon Canada for $37.56. | Amazon / Via amazon.caWe've all been there â€” making our coffee or tea only to set it down and forget about until it's cooled down completely. Thanks to this mug warmer none of us ever have to suffer through another cold cup of caffeine again! Get it from Amazon Canada for $27.25. | | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Amazon / Via amazon.ca, BuzzFeedCheck out our full review of the John Frieda hot brush for more info!Get it from Amazon Canada for $38.79. | AmazonGet it from Amazon Canada for $50.61+ (available in two options). | Amazon / Via amazon.caIncludes a Fujifilm Instax Mini 9 Camera (with a selfie mirror!), 20 sheets of film, 10 sheets of rainbow film, 20 sticker frames, and a leather carrying case.Get it from Amazon Canada for $139.99+ (available in five colour combos; also available with just the camera). | Amazon / Via amazon.caI have one of these bad boys and can validate that it is SO easy to use. I pop my phone into it when I get in the shower and click the lil' button on the front to start the cleaning process. You can also charge your phone while it's inside the machine. Fellow germaphobes â€” you can thank me later.Get it from Amazon Canada for $105.45 (available in nine colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $29.99. | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $75.30. | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $68.99. | Amazon / Via amazon.caIt can be used as a pressure cooker, slow cooker, rice cooker, and egg cooker, with the ability to sautÃ©, steam, and warm. Read all about why the Instant Pot is changing how we cook in my BuzzFeed coworker's review. Get it from Amazon Canada for $79.97+ (available in three sizes). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Abby Kass / BuzzFeed, Amazon / Via amazon.caIt's the thinnest and lightest Kindle Amazon has released to date! And â€” as is made abundantly clear by the photo above â€” it's 100% waterproof. Get it from Amazon Canada for $139.99+ (also available with 32GB of memory).And check out our full breakdown of the Kindle Paperwhite here. | Amazon / Via amazon.caThis is the number one thing on my wish list right now â€” it's so cool and I'm constantly staring at it in stores. I love that it has the ability to transform into a piece of art but also act as a room's main source of entertainment.Get it from Amazon Canada for $1297.99+ (available in four sizes). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedMy fellow BuzzFeed editor Maitland Quitmeyer loves this thing. Here's what she had to say:"The acne scars on my cheeks from a series of breakouts are fading fast, and I get new acne very rarely â€” they're more like a pimple here and there occasionally when I have to fly somewhere (curse you, dry airplanes) or get stressed or.... who even knows why my skin freaks out sometimes. Never thought I'd ever put a no-makeup selfie on the internet, but that's how much I love this thing." Check out our full review of the FOREO LUNA Mini 2 here!Get it from Amazon Canada for $179 (available in six colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caEvery gamer needs a fancy mouse! This one has light features that can be customized to WHATEVER colour they want, seven programmable mouse buttons, five default DPI levels, and four adjusting polling rate levels. Even if you have no idea what that means, the gamer in your home will simply be in awe over the features.Available from Amazon Canada for $20.29 (available in three styles). | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $29.91. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Heather Braga / BuzzFeed, Amazon / Via amazon.caFrom the moment I put the headset over my eyes I thought "Wow, I never have to leave the house again!!!" I'm personally more introverted, but I still enjoy spending time with family and friends. The Quest has been a great way for me to have a good time interacting with my loved ones without feeling overwhelmed by TOO much chatter. I brought it to Thanksgiving and we had a blast taking turns playing with it. More recently my sister and her boyfriend came over and we spent hours giggling watching one another play. Super fun!Get it from Amazon Canada for $199.99. | instagram.com / Via virzoom, instagram.com / Via virzoomGet it from Amazon Canada for $148.25. | Amazon / Via amazon.caMy dad and I tested out this watch and let me tell you â€” it's INTENSE. I workout regularly and this bad boy will definitely keep me in check going forward. It syncs up to an app on your phone that provides you with very detailed statistics on your cardio load, muscle load, and more. It has TONS of workouts you can track ranging from an outdoor walk and golfing to indoor cycling and long distance running. If you're looking to take your workouts to the next level, this will be quickly become part of your routine.Get it from Amazon Canada for $337.75+ (available in sizes Sâ€“L and five colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caHonestly, no matter which version of the Dyson stick vacuum you purchase, I can promise you'll be satisfied with the results. I've used a variety of 'em and I can't say enough good things about the product. It doesn't hurt my back to use for an extended period of the time, the battery lasts long enough to clean my entire apartment, and it simply just WORKS. We have ours mounted in a narrow spot alongside our fridge â€” it's really easy to keep in plain sight without being an eyesore.Get the V10 from Amazon Canada for $599.97. | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $144.49. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF
