Title Headline: 35 Things Reviewers Say Are Actually So Comfortable
Short Description Sub Headline: Honestly, I'm at the point in my life where I don't even want to buy something if it's not comfortable.
Content Body: Shopping | | Clothing | 35 Things Reviewers Say Are Actually So Comfortable | Honestly, I'm at the point in my life where I don't even want to buy something if it's not comfortable. | Posted on January 06, 2020, 11:01 GMT | January 06, 2020, 11:01 GMT | Abby KassBuzzFeed Staff | | | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I LOVE this top. Iâ€™m 5â€™7 148 lbs (athletic build) 34DD, and I ordered a small. Itâ€™s oversized, so the small is perfect. Iâ€™d recommend sizing down one from your usual size. It's super comfortable, and since I ordered the white short sleeve, I can continue to wear it through spring. Iâ€™ll be ordering more colors!' â€”JoyGet it from Amazon for $18.99 (available in sizes S-2X and in 27 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This dress was everything! Iâ€™m a plus-size woman and generally wear a size 18. I bought a 2XL, and it fits perfectly. The material was very comfortable, even though it was on the cheaper end of the spectrum (which is expected because of the price). It's a beautiful dress, and I recommend it to all looking for an expensive classy dress" â€”Selena PooleGet it from Amazon for $26.99 (available in sizes S-3X and in 14 colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I love this skirt so much! I got a large (150lb, 5'4) and it fits me perfectly. I've had this black skirt for around nine months now and it has become a staple in my wardrobe! It has very VERY small pockets but pockets nonetheless, and it's very comfortable. The zipper is high quality, the material feels expensive, and I haven't noticed any fabric shrinkage or color fading! For me, it hits around mid-thigh." â€“livGet it from Amazon for $18.99 (available in sizes XS-2XL and 20 styles). | amazon.com, AmazonReviewers recommend ordering a half size down. Promising review: "These shoes are affordable, comfortable, and really cute! I had been looking for a loafer shoe, and these looked promising. They have a tiny heel that's just right, so not completely flat and not too high. The pointed toe makes these more modern and dressy. I took into consideration other reviews on size. I normally wear an 8 1/2 up to a 9, especially in dress shoes. I went with an 8 and they fit perfect, despite having a wider width foot. I plan on regularly wearing them to work. I'll update my review if they don't hold up, but they seem decently made." â€”VansGet them from Amazon for $34.99 (available in sizes 6-11 and in 35 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This is probably the most comfortable jacket I have ever owned! Itâ€™s soft and very warm! I survived 33 degrees New Mexico weather just fine in it!" â€”Ashley DranguetGet it from Amazon for $31.59 (available in sizes S-3X and in 15 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I love these leggings. I now have two pairs and will continue to buy from this brand. They fit perfectly and don't slide down or ride up as I work out. They also do well with wicking moisture and staying dryâ€”no puddles of sweat to make me uncomfortable! I can't tell you how many times I've worn and washed them and they hold up perfectly. They're perfectly opaque too. No panty lines and definitely no patterns on my underwear showing through. I'm so impressed with 90 Degree by Reflex, especially for the price. They're my go-to workout leggings!" â€”IrvyGet them from Amazon for $22.99 (available in sizes XS-XL and in 27 styles).Read more about how great these leggings are here. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I love these jeans! So comfortable, so cuteâ€”just enough stretch so you can move around easily, without that saggy, baggy butt look after a few hours, lol. This is the first time I purchased this brand, so I didn't know how they would fit, but they are true to size. You can go by the size chart. I will definitely be purchasing more!" â€”tradergirl31Get them from Amazon for $16.50 (available in sizes 0-20 and in three styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I LOVE this wrap dress! The material is so soft and comfortable, and the dress is a perfect fit. It accentuates my curves and is super flattering. I always try to find dresses that would be work appropriate and also cute to wear if going out after work and on the weekends, and this fits the bill. It doesn't show too much cleavage and is the perfect length- a few inches above my knee." â€”TaylorGet it from Amazon for $24.99 (available in sizes S-XXL and in 22 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I really love this dress. It is very beautiful. It fit just right. I ordered an XL, and I am 203lbs, and I am busty, so the boob area was very comfortable. The dress itself was comfortable!! It did fall a little below my knees, which was a great length. It had a zipper on the side, but I didnâ€™t use it because I didnâ€™t even notice it had a zipper because the dress was stretchy. I will be buying again in other colors. I wore it for a wedding and received many compliments!!!!" â€”Joevonder JonesGet it from Amazon for $38.99 (available in sizes XS-3X and in 42 styles). | Nordstrom, Abby Kass / BuzzFeedPromising review: "I absolutely love these leggings. They're so comfortable, keep you tight, they are warm. Super stylish. I always get compliments on them." â€”Absolutely loveGet them from Nordstrom for $98 (available in sizes XS-XL, XS-XL petite, and 2X) or Spanx for $98+ (available in sizes XS-3X and in petite or regular). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "These are the most comfortable pants Iâ€™ve ever owned. I wear them to work, and people constantly ask where I got them from. The belt is a super cute touch. I bought several pairs in different colors, and they also have shorts that are just as cute! You wonâ€™t regret this buy!" â€”drdogmomGet it from Amazon for $24.99 (available in sizes XS-3X and in 35 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This dress is very comfortable. It fit like a glove. I loved that I could dress it up or down. It could be a light spring dress or a winter dress. I love it" â€”LMSAGet it from Amazon for $36.99 (available in sizes XS-XXL and in 12 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comReviewers recommend ordering a half size down.Promising review: "These are cute and comfortable! I took the advice from other reviews and sized down. I am usually a 6.5 but got a 6, and they fit perfectly. I have wide feet, and these adjusted very well. I highly recommend to anyone looking for a simple but cute shoe." â€”ESGFGet it from Amazon for $35.99 (available in sizes 5.5-11 and in 57 colors and styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I could wear this every day. It's so soft and comfortable. I love these dresses, and I will be buying more but in different colors. It's great for date nights or for dressing up but also being comfortable. On windy days, be sure to wear leggings or shorts because it will blow up." â€”AubrieGet it from Amazon for $11.55 (available in sizes XS-3X and in 37 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This is a beautiful dress and great quality for the price. I received lots of compliments, and Iâ€™m tempted to buy it in every color! The material has a bit of stretch that makes for a flattering fit. For reference, Iâ€™m 5â€™4â€ 125 lbs, and the small fit perfect and was very comfortable. The color was great!!!!" â€”WineymamaGet it from Amazon for $28.99 (available in sizes XS-XXL and in six colors). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "The more that you wear these shoes, the comfier they get! I can walk around in them all day, and I get a ton of compliments on them. I usually feel frumpy wearing flats, but that's certainly not the case with these â€” I just ordered the beige color, and I might get the leopard print. I ABSOLUTELY LOVE THESE SHOES!" â€”Amazon CustomerGet them from Amazon for $15.98 (available in sizes 5.5-11 and 35 styles). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 28 Gorgeous Pieces Of Furniture That Are Perfect For Small Spaces | New year, new furniture for your tiny but perfect home. | Posted on January 18, 2020, 15:01 GMT | January 18, 2020, 15:01 GMT | Yi YangBuzzFeed Staff | | | | Urban OutfittersPromising review: "So cute and functional! Fits three of my fluffy blankets and two small pillows!" â€”kkerr22Get it from Urban Outfitters for $129. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I wasn't even planning on getting a kitchen table because I didn't want to lose anymore square footage. The way my apartment is set up, a table will be in the way no matter where it sits. But when I ran across this little gem, I changed my mind. When they say space saving, they really mean it. I especially love that the stools tuck under the table!The stools are NOT bar stools, so they are short, but that's to line up with the table. I also use them as TV trays sometime, so I REALLY love this table! So many uses. If you're looking for an arts and crafts table or need to save space like me, do yourself a favor and pick this thing up!" â€”JDGet it from Amazon for $118. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "For $200, this is a five-star product. It was really easy to put together. It's a little firmer than what I usually like, but it's not uncomfortable. I even took a nap on it the other day. It was even a little bigger than I thought it would be. My family of three has plenty of room when we all sit on it." â€”Lindy M.Get it from Novogratz on Amazon for $316.48 (available in eight colors). | WalmartPromising review: "Great value for the money! Title Headline: Here Are 11 Of The Best Diaries And Journals To Try In 2020
Short Description Sub Headline: New year, new notebook, new you.
Content Body: Shopping | Here Are 11 Of The Best Diaries And Journals To Try In 2020 | New year, new notebook, new you. | Posted on January 03, 2020, 12:00 GMT | January 03, 2020, 12:00 GMT | Amy GloverBuzzFeed Staff | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukSmall but practical, this lil' A5 diary is bursting with handy features from storage pockets to holiday planners. It comes with a whopping 288 stickers (yes, please), moveable dividers, a useful holiday planner that's perfect for organising big events in advance, and to-do lists (did we mention there's a separate address book, too?). You can easily see your weekly schedule at a glance with this diary, and the monthly planner section means you can set mid-term goals as well as documenting and organising your daily plans. Price: Â£11.49. | | | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukConnect to the accompanying app to upload everything from this notebook to the cloud, which you can then send directly to places like Slack, Dropbox, Google Docs, and more! Just write what you need to on its pages, save them to the cloud, wipe your words away, and start again. The app is available for both iOS and Android, making this next-level notebook the perfect futuristic tool for diarists and students alike. Price: Â£20.57. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukIf you're after a no-frills (but still pretty) journalling experience, this one-page-a-day diary is perfect. It does more or less what it says on the tin â€“ you get given one page for each day of the year that you can fill with as much or as little writing as you'd like, and while there are some fun extras (like a gorge ribbon page marker and a handy yearly calendar), it's essentially a straightforward journal done well. An incredible buy for keen journallers or just someone who doesn't really go for all the bells and whistles, this diary is simple and beautiful! Price: Â£12. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThe pages of this (pretty adorable) diary are dotted, giving you an easy guide to create your own grids, columns, and margins without restricting your space to doodle. Its genius pen-test page allows you to get your writing tools working without destroying a perfectly good sheet of writing paper (yesss), and there are key code pages and index pages too which will help you make sense of your notes. The diary comes with two colour-coded bookmarks, an expandable pocket, a pen loop, and its ethically-sourced vegan leather cover is bound durably enough to the notebook that it'll last the owner literally years. Ideal for doodlers, visual thinkers, or just anyone who wants to have more fun with their journalling, this diary can be used for low-key entries and Instagrammable artworks alike! It's available in teal, olive, charcoal, and pastel pink. Price: Â£18.97. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukWith plenty of space to map out each day of the week and a spare box to fill in your notes, this diary is a great way to keep on top of your schedule in style (and seeing as it's got a monthly goals section, it could even help you keep your new year's resolutions too!). The paper is thick enough to feel highly *luxurious* when you're writing on it, and there's a handy pocket at the back to help you store keepsakes like tickets or more practical stuff, like receipts. Price: Â£20.01. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThis bad boy really has it all â€“ blank tear-out lists, note pages, fill-in calendars, four useful pockets, and a pen loop. It gives you an overview of the week with plenty of room to fill in everything you need to do, and customers say there's space to write your reminders in too. The A6 size makes it incredibly portable, and it's so pretty it'll basically become decor when you put it on your desk! Available in two different designs, this incredibly well-reviewed diary is great for the busy person on the go. Price: Â£18.97. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukKeep track of your life and your garden with this beautifully-illustrated journal, which gives you space to track the things you've planted, gardening tips, and has loads of room for notes, too. Customers say it's given them everything they need to keep their plants on top form, and it's got a daily planner too, which you can use either for tracking growth or for writing down how your day went (or both!). Price: Â£14.08. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThe design of this diary is stunning, and the recipes inside are pretty great too! With stickers, plenty of writing space, a selection of recipes ranging from desserts to mid-week meals, and some pages to help you plan out big events like birthdays and Christmas, this lil' guy seems to more or less do it all. Extras like conversions (great if you're baking) and contact pages make this gorgeous diary an absolute standout! Price: Â£11.08.

Title Headline: 12 Stylish Things That'll Have You Breaking Hearts On Valentine's Day
Short Description Sub Headline: You'd look cute in sweats, but just in case.
Content Body: Shopping | 12 Stylish Things That'll Have You Breaking Hearts On Valentine's Day | You'd look cute in sweats, but just in case. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 02:28 GMT | January 31, 2020, 02:28 GMT | Mariela SummerhaysBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Mariela Summerhays / BuzzFeed, The IconicThe sweetheart neckline, elasticised puffed sleeves, thigh-high centre slit and fabric-covered buttons â€” it's all just so dreamy. Made of pure linen with cotton lining, it's the perfect thing for your summer night date. Promising review: "This is my new favourite dress. I wear it to work in contrasting, bright slides â€” and at night, keep my face bare and sandals nude for the ultimate ethereal, romantic look. I get compliments on the blush colour and sweet sleeves all the time. It is linen â€” so crushes easily â€” but you get past that quickly enough for such a sweet dress."â€”Mariela SummerhaysOriginally $139 / Buy now for $69.50 from The Iconic. | Third FormYou've never owned a slip dress like this. Featuring adjustable tie-up straps, I've seen this dress worn slightly looser, like the above photos, making for a more relaxed silhouette â€” and tighter, creating a more figure-hugging shape and higher hemline. The timeless black colour, classic satin construction, keyhole detail to bust and ribbon back feature â€” 100% a dress to wear over and over again.Buy for $220 from Amazon Australia. | The IconicSo, not the only linen item on the list â€” and really, can you blame me when it's been so hot lately? These high-waisted, relaxed fit cropped pants feature sweet gathered detail to the cuffs and a pistachio hue that wouldn't look out of place on your date or work come Monday. Buy for $99.95 from The Iconic. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Natalia Krslovic / BuzzFeedI recently dressed my friend, Nat, in this dress for a style swap challenge video you can watch here. Of the form-fitting, midi-length dress with asymmetrical sleeve, she said:Promising review: "When I first saw this dress, I was simultaneously excited and scared. I love an asymmetrical sleeve, but I don't often go for anything this figure-hugging for fear of it not flattering my body.Turns out, I had nothing to worry about. This dress was sexy, comfortable and showed off all my curves â€” while still looking elegant and classy. I really felt super glam and I loved it. I was initially worried that some of my rolls were showing through, but once I'd gotten over my own insecurities, I was really vibing this look."-Natalia KrslovicOriginally $111.96 / Buy now for $83.97 from Amazon Australia. | @thirdform / Via instagram.com, AmazonThis excellent trouser from Third Form features a high-waist, wide leg, ankle-baring hemline â€” and perhaps my favourite detail, a tonal paisley pattern throughout. Lining from waist to seat ensures it will last you for years (no wearing down at the thighs!). Wear with its matching jacket closed, black stilettos and nothing else at all.Promising review: "Honestly, one of the best pair of pants I've ever owned. Figure-hugging in all the right spots but balanced with a loose-fit in the legs â€”which makes them suitable for both the office and date-night. Love the subtle pattern on the fabric too, and the side zip. But if I'm being real, it's all about the ass in these pants and I am liviinnggg for it."â€”Julia WillingBuy for $200 from Amazon Australia. | Mariela Summerhays / BuzzFeed, MyerPromising review: "I'm a big fan of statement earrings as part of an everyday outfit. I wear these with a double denim look and bare face, all the time. I love everything about this â€” the gold and pearl detail is just so decadent. Plus, considering the quality, it's so affordable â€” I buy something from Bling Bar whenever I need to gift my friends something."â€”Mariela SummerhaysBuy for $55 from Myer. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF In recent years, slip dresses have come back from their '90s hey day, and I for one, am here for it. Not all slip dresses are made equal though â€” cheap material, unflattering cuts â€” but this one here is the crÃ¨me de la crÃ¨me. Cut from pure silk in a form-flattering silhouette, its midi-length hem means it can be worn wherever without it looking like you've just run away from bridesmaid duties.Originally $250 / Buy now for $175 from The Iconic. | If, like me, you're challenged when it comes to styling your hair for special occasions, few things come as handy as a headband. These particular ones are fashioned from lush velvet, are embellished with pearl-like beads and have a knot design to centre. You'll look like a duchess â€” without the prince or intense public scrutiny.Buy a set of three for $17.99 from Amazon Australia. | Mariela Summerhays / BuzzFeed, SportsgirlI am literally wearing these now at my desk, as I type this. Unlike my usual heels, these are so comfortable. Their block midi-heels mean I can happily walk around everywhere and their classic black hue and minimalist design mean they have slotted easily into my existing wardrobe â€” date night or otherwise.Buy for $79.95 from Sportsgirl. | Ugh, it's just so pretty. An illusion neckline, lace overlay, asymmetrical hemline â€” this gorgeous dress wouldn't look out of place in Sophia Loren's wardrobe. Add a red lip and braid crown for a gorgeous ~romantic vibe~.Buy from $41.17 from Amazon Australia. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 21 Ten-Minute Cleaning Products You'll Probably Wish You'd Known About Sooner
Short Description Sub Headline: Resolve your cleaning conundrums, quickly.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 21 Ten-Minute Cleaning Products You'll Probably Wish You'd Known About Sooner | Resolve your cleaning conundrums, quickly. | Posted on January 22, 2020, 12:56 GMT | January 22, 2020, 12:56 GMT | Natalie BrownBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comIt works on both old and new stains (including red wine!), and on any color-safe fabric that you can safely wet with water (read: not dyed silk or wool, probs, or anything that says "dry clean only"). Promising review: "I had terrible rust and oil stains all over the seats of my car. I tried other cleaners to get them out, but they actually made the stains darker. I took it to the dealership to see if they could get it out and they flat out told me no, so I gave up and lived with it for almost five years. Then I tried this after it was recommended by a friend. I sprayed it on and literally watched the stain run right off my seat. It was amazing! I thought I was going to have to pay hundreds of dollars to replace the seats in my car because nothing else would work. This stuff really is awesome!" â€”BrittanyGet a bottle on Amazon for $11.45. | | | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF amazon.com, Scrubbing Bubbles / youtube.comYou just press it beneath the rim (after a regular toilet cleaning, of course!) and let it get to work. You'll have to re-stamp every 12 days or so, depending on how often the toilet's flushed. Oh, and make sure to stamp it somewhere it won't become a, well, "target" and get sprayed off before its time. Promising review: "A lazy housekeepers best friend â€” these are amazing and I'm bummed I haven't tried them until now! Warning: possible TMI! We're big fans of the 'if it's yellow, let it mellow' potty practice in our home as it conserves a serious amount of water if you flush every 3-4 tinkles vs every time....anyways! These little gems are easy to use and with our limited flushing, one application tends to last around two weeks before it starts to lose its smell and effectiveness. But it has kept our bowls clean and the bathroom smelling fresh." â€”StephanieGet it in packs that last for up to 20 weeks from Amazon: the "fresh" scent for $10.32 or the "rainshower" scent for $8.34. | amazon.com, amazon.comIt allows you to firmly grab two blinds at a time, so you could easily make one window's blinds look basically brand new in under 10 minutes. Plus it comes with five microfiber sleeves, which means you can finish all the blinds in your home without stopping to clean it off over and over â€” you just pop all the covers in the wash when you're done. Promising review: "A super time saver. It legitimately used to take us hours to clean all the blinds. My wife now does all the faux-wood Venetian blinds in the house in about one hour. It's really nice that it comes with some spare cloths for it, and it's cheap enough to buy a whole additional set so we can make more than one kid do this chore at the same time." â€”R.D.Get one on Amazon for $7.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comYou simply twist its base to dispense the solution into the bristles, brush it over your gems, rinse with water, and voila! Your ring will sparkle like a thousand stars, and you can toss the Stik back in your purse, ready for the next time you notice a little dinginess. (It works with pretty much every gem and metal except pearls.) Promising review: "I was a bit skeptical about this product and the fact that it's under $10 but once I opened and used it... OMG! I have a rose de France amethyst wedding ring and the stone was so cloudy it looked terrible. I kept trying to clean it with a toothbrush and warm water/mild soap as I was instructed when it was purchased. It would get clean but I couldn't get behind the stone so it would never really look clean. I used this product and once it was rinsed and dry it looked just like the day I received it. I was so excited! Fell back in love with my ring again and can't stop looking at it. The bristles on the brush really get into the tiny holes behind the ring setting which allows for an actual scrub on the back of the stone to remove the buildup. This product is amazing." â€”KY ActonGet it on Amazon for $8.78. | amazon.comPromising review: "I used it on our tubs, toilets, sinks, and shower. It took one bottle of this stuff to achieve the same result as three bottles of other brands. I will buy this again hands down. I just sprayed, walk away for a few minutes, and wiped and rinsed." â€”Carrie D.Get a bottle on Amazon for $4.98. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | amazon.comPromising review: "Works extremely well. We haven't done any cleaning on our dishwasher in five years, and the sliding trays were tough to pull out and push in, there was detergent build up all over the inside, and there was a milky film on all our cups. I bought this, ran the dishwasher with two tablets while it was empty, and the difference was astounding. There was still some build up and I figured it would require another cycle, so I popped another two tablets in, ran the machine a second time, and now it looks and sounds brand new. No more film on the glasses, no more dirty dishes from clogged sprayers, no more odors, and no more build-up around the door seals." â€”MartouneGet a box of six tablets on Amazon for $3.15. | amazon.comNote that it's best if your garbage disposal's just generally smell and not actually clogged â€” if it's clogged, definitely call a plumber. Promising review: "Do you have a stinky garbage disposal? If so, get some of these. They are cheap, smell nice. and the foaming action really provides you with a visual they are cleaning the drain. After using these the garbage disposal seems smoother (fewer strange noises, like it's been lubricated). I'd recommend these over Plinks any day as I feel the Plinks only hide smells whereas these foaming packets actually clean the disposal."â€”SugacookieGet a pack of four on Amazon for $5.08. | amazon.comIt's basically a small piece of metal chain mail (yes, like the knights wore!) that's dishwasher safe and doesn't require soap to scrub off all the remnants of burgers, eggs, and veggies lingering on your favorite pan. Just don't use it on any non-stick pans, of course â€” metal scratches 'em!Promising review: "This has completely changed the way I use my cast iron pan. I can cook whatever I want and know the pan will be as good as new. For people that worry about the seasoning on the pan, this definitely won't hurt a thing. Once I'm done cleaning, I'll shake off any excess water and then heat it on the stove top for a minute until its completely dry. I'll then put a a very light coating of oil on it and heat it up again and the pan will be good to go for the next use. My pan has never cooked better." â€”JoshGet it on Amazon for $15.99. And if you do get it, I recommend reading this review â€” I know it's long, but they offer some excellent advice on how to make the most of it. | amazon.comI've been using these for years, so I know: all they need is a little water, and they truly do erase all kinds of dirt and grime like it was never there! Promising review: "I can't believe how clean I could get my non-porcelain sink with this product. I was so disgusted with trying all types of cleansers, with very mixed results. But just a wipe or two and the sink was sparkling! Next, I tackled the tub â€” once, no doubt, a lovely porcelain fixture but now with worn-down porcelain that wants to hold onto every smudge of dirt or stain. Again, the sponge worked! It really did clean up, if not so sparkly white. I even considered taking a bath again, which I hated to do before." â€”PeninaGet a pack of eight on Amazon for $10. | amazon.comBecause it doesn't rely on adhesive paper, you only have to buy it once and use it forever â€” cleaning the hair off the brush when it gets clogged, of course! Promising review: "We live in a household that contains two humans, two dogs, and two cats. It's a real Noah's Ark furnished with a black sectional couch. Our dogs absolutely hate the vacuum. So much so they will attack the cleaner head with their vicious bite even before we power it on. This makes the task of cleaning our couch extremely unpleasant and nearly impossible. Thanks to Chom Chom, we no longer have this problem! With a simple, quick, SOUNDLESS sweep, we're able to keep our couch pet-hair-free in blissful peace. This tool does an amazing job picking up pet hair but not so much with crumbs. We were so impressed, we gifted these as Christmas presents for all of our pet-loving friends." â€”MagpieGet one on Amazon for $24.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "These towels are awesome for so many things. They are large and very sturdy, so they work well for household cleaning. The real benefit for me, though, is having a wipe that works for things like the grill, the oven, the dashboard of my car, muddy shoes, chairs and umbrellas that go to soccer games and practices, and lawn furniture. I frequently wipe something down, rinse the towel, and wipe again. The wipes are heavy enough to go through three to four rinses and wipes and still hold up. The smell is mild and doesn't linger on my hands or what I've wiped down. Because the canister is heavier than most, and the lid fits well, it's easy to throw one of these in the trunk or cargo area without worrying about leaks. The canister's recyclable when the towels are gone â€” an added bonus." â€”COMomGet a tub on Amazon for $11.75. | amazon.comPromising review: "I have a 19-year-old master bathroom toilet that had accumulated some nasty stains over time which regular toilet brushes and cleaning products just would not remove. Pumice stone worked like a charm! Given the nature and severity of the stains, it required some elbow grease, but 10 minutes later I have a new-looking bowl, and I see no signs of scratching. Am very happy with this purchase...well worth the very low price!" â€”Happy RetireeGet one on Amazon for $7.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 16 Horror Movie Details And Easter Eggs That Are Scarily Awesome
Short Description Sub Headline: "Oh, cool!" â€”Me catching these details while watching the movies through my fingers.
Content Body: TV and Movies | 16 Horror Movie Details And Easter Eggs That Are Scarily Awesome | "Oh, cool!" â€”Me catching these details while watching the movies through my fingers. | Posted on January 25, 2020, 01:45 GMT | January 25, 2020, 01:45 GMT | Allie HayesBuzzFeed Staff | A24"In an early scene, while Dani and Christian are arguing in Daniâ€™s apartment, thereâ€™s a painting in the background of a girl wearing a crown who is kissing a bear, which outright foreshadows both of their fates at the end of the film."â€”corinneldwyer | | Universal Pictures"When Tiffany goes to the evidence locker to get the remains of Chucky, they also have Jason Voorheesâ€™s hockey mask, Freddy Kruegerâ€™s glove, Michael Myersâ€™ mask, Leatherfaceâ€™s chainsaw, and even the puppets from Puppet Master locked up."â€”t413c16c57 | Buena Vista Pictures Distribution"I actually had a theory the first time I saw this that you could tell that Malcolm was dead from the beginning of the movie because, if you pay attention, he's wearing the same shirt he was shot in the entire movie."â€”stacieb46da63d87 | DreamWorks Pictures"Thereâ€™s a scene where Naomi Wattsâ€™s character is riding on a ferry boat, notices a horse that is also being transported, and tries to pet the horse. There is a closeup of the horseâ€™s eye, and it's a reference to the closeup that appears on the creepy cassette tape that she, her son, and her ex all watched that doomed them all. It was such a cool moment of foreshadowing!"â€”kminfl | Paramount PicturesIn the remake, during Ellie's birthday party, Jud can be heard in the background saying, 'There was a big Saint Bernard who got rabies..." which is a direct reference to Cujo, another work of Stephen King's."â€”caitlinm18 | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | New Line Cinema, Embassy Communications"Nancy is watching a trailer for Evil Dead while trying to stay awake so, in Evil Dead 2, the director (Sam Raimi) returned the favor by hanging Freddy's razor glove on the wall of the toolshed when Ash uses the chainsaw."â€”suspiciouscake

Title Headline: Just 9 Things To Try In January
Short Description Sub Headline: Because we tried them for you in December.
Content Body: Shopping | Just 9 Things To Try In January | Because we tried them for you in December. | Posted on January 06, 2020, 12:20 GMT | January 06, 2020, 12:20 GMT | Maitland QuitmeyerBuzzFeed Staff | BuzzFeed / Anna Kopsky"I have been carrying my laptop in a backpack for the last five years, because I really haven't found a laptop bag that is cute, comfortable, AND within my price range... until this beaut. Not only is it extremely adorable, but it also has survived plenty of walks in the rain and still looks like it's in the same condition as the day I got it. Best of all, I can throw everything I need for the day into the bag and there always still seems to be more room for more items. Just this week, I tossed everything in the image above in my bag like I do every morning before work, before realizing I also needed to bring extra hairspray, deodorant, and my makeup bag. All of those things also fit in this bag, and it was so nice to not have to carry a bunch of bags around on my commute! I really recommend this laptop bag for a stylish option that is well within anyone's budget. Woo!" â€”Anna KopskyGet it from Amazon for $25.99+ (available in four colors). | "If youâ€™re familiar with the pearly world of teeth whitening, then you already know itâ€™s a sensitive process. And if you see your dentist and go the professional route, it can also be an expensive one. That's why I decided to try GlowUp when I noticed my teeth looking a little yellow. It's an LED whitening kit that is fully customized to your mouth. To start, you take a comprehensive quiz, answering questions about your brushing habits and how discolored your chompers currently are. Once you're done, you get a specific formula shipped to you.Glowup costs $60 for a one-time kit, or $30 if you sign up for a bimonthly subscription, which is around what youâ€™ll spend for most at-home whitening kits. A treatment takes only 10 minutes (compared with overnight trays or strips you keep on for 30 minutes to an hour). My blend included hydrogen peroxide (the whitening ingredient commonly used by dentists), menthol (to provide a refreshing minty sensation), and cellulose gum (to fight off irritation and discomfort). For anyone whoâ€™s all about natural ingredients, Glowup also utilizes pomegranate seed extract, chamomile flower, and aloe leaf juice to remove bacteria and disinfect breath.I love a schedule: setting one and keeping one. So brushing my teeth at night and using the kit was a cinch. Iâ€™d apply my custom gel to the mouthguard, set a timer for 10 minutes, and plug the cord directly into my iPhoneâ€™s charging port. It truly was that easy. For such a mindless process, I saw a significant difference in the color of my teeth after a week of daily use. Seeing that Iâ€™ve never used a whitening light before, I was skeptical. But the results were obvious and I now have refill gels shipped to me for touchups." â€”Alexandra Napoli Get a kit from Glowup for $60, or $30 if you sign up for a subscription (with refills for $10). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Kaysey Davis/BuzzFeed"I love a good sheet mask, and the Garnier Moisture Bomb sheet mask is one of my absolute favourites. Unlike other masks that are made of microgel, cellulose, or foil, this mask is made out of cotton, which is not only super soft, but more environmentally friendly. The cotton has a bit of stretch to it, so it's easier to fit it around my face, nose, and lips than other masks. It's also very gentle on the skin and less irritating than other mask materials, so it's great for anyone with sensitive skin. I have oily/combination skin, so my cheeks and chin tend to be drier than the T-zone. I love using the Pomegranate sheet mask to boost the moisture levels in my skin, but all the different types of masks are equal when it comes to hydration. I can just sit back and relax while my skin soaks up all the liquid goodness. Even after I remove the mask, there is so much product left on my skin and in the package that I use it the excess serum on my neck. I can immediately see brighter, smoother, and more hydrated skin after just 15 minutes on my face. I use them a couple times a week before I go to bed, so I wake up with my skin at its best." â€”Kaysey DavisGet a six-pack from Amazon for $14.94 (also available in four other varieties). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Content Body: Shopping | | Amazon | 33 Amazon Products That Convinced Skeptical Shoppers To Hit "Add To Cart" | You can't argue with those results. | Posted on January 30, 2020, 15:00 GMT | January 30, 2020, 15:00 GMT | Melanie AmanBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comThe brush has special vents that allow air to flow so hair dries faster. Plus, it's quicker than using a dryer and then a flat iron or curling iron, which equals less heat damage. Promising review: "Just wow! I was skeptical at first. I wish I would have bought this sooner! After showering I get all the moisture I can out of my hair. And leave it to kind of air dry while Iâ€™m getting ready, having coffee, or whatever Iâ€™m doing that morning. It takes me about seven minutes to dry my hair if that! I have very thick naturally curly hair. Itâ€™s is a fabulous tool to have in your arsenal! May be the only one I have to use. No flat iron needed as of yet! Would buy again in a heartbeat!" â€”D.KGet it from Amazon for $27+ (available in four colors). | | | amazon.comPromising review: "I was skeptical at first but fully committed now.+ only 1/4 of the bottle in and my skin looks better+ feels smooth+ no redness and less acne scars+ little to no breakout even during my cycle+ absorb fast+ moisturizingI used it in the morning and before sleeping at night ğŸ˜" â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $7.70. | amazon.comPromising review: "Holy crap!! Are you skeptical when it comes to buying stuff online? ME TOO! That's why I figured all of these rave reviews were a crock of crap. I've seriously bought every kind of vacuum out there, including the Rumba, which is about as intelligent as a cotton swab. But I have four cats and a golden retriever, so I was getting desperate! I believe the saying isâ€¦ a picture is worth a thousand words. Check mine out (above)! Of note â€” the 'before' picture was taken of my dog's bed AFTER it went through the washer and dryer. Look at all of that left-behind hair!!! And the 'after' picture was taken after only THREE MINUTES spent vacuuming her bed. I. Am. SOLD! BTW, I've NEVER taken the time to review a product before, just FYI." â€”Luka ChanGet it from Amazon for $30.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "A perfect dupe for Drunk Elephant's Babyfacial!!! This is a fraction of the $80 price tag of Babyfacial. This brand is a godsend!!! Science does not lie. I was skeptical at first because it's so inexpensive, but it's real and it works!!!! Invest the time and make a routine based on your skin type, The Ordinary makes it easy, and you won't need to invest a lot money but you will get the results!!" â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $13.30. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I was so skeptical that my dog would actually wear these, but I put them on and immediately took him out to play fetch. Once he realized that he could run and jump with them on, he was sold. It snowed a few days later and we put them on again and ended up walking six miles without any sore or red spots on his feet after. I did make it a point to not laugh at him and only put them on for fun stuff. Heâ€™s getting to the point where he knows they mean fun and will even give me his paws so I can put them on. You have to make sure that you tighten them enough, but once they are on, they should stay. I will be ordering another pair if these get run through." â€”emilieyGet it from Amazon for $29.99+ (available in seven sizes, two colors, and two styles). | amazon.comPromising review: "I looove this thing. Itâ€™s so much easier than ironing and faster. I also really appreciate the glove and the storage bag that comes with it. I was skeptical at first when I saw how small the steamer is, but it heats up almost instantly and produces a good steady steam." â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $17.17.My colleague tested and reviewed the PurSteam Elite Mini Steamer, saying, "wrinkles, you have met your match!" | AmazonPromising review: "I bought this for my elderly mom who loves grilled cheese sandwiches. I was skeptical that this bag on the toaster would work but it did! The only thing I would suggest is after you toast the sandwich, let it sit for a few minutes so the cheese melts better. I prepared it and gave it to her straight away. Bread was toasted on the outside. Clean up was easy. All in all impressive!" â€”Amazon CustomerGet a set of four from Amazon for $6.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer/BuzzFeedPromising review: "I was very skeptical about this product, but I read a lot of great positive reviews on how well it works and decided to give it a try since the idea of not having to purchase brush head replacements highly appealed to me. I work in cosmetics and wear a lot of makeup daily; this machine did wonders for my skin. It removed about 90% of the makeup with maybe a tiny residue left that I easily went over with a waterproof makeup remover. I am sold on the Foreo and now recommend it to everyone. I even purchased a second one for my husband." â€”Andrea SandovalGet it from Amazon for $119+ (available in eight colors).Read our in-depth review of the Foreo Luna Mini 2 for more deets. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I was skeptical like many others, but this bag is magical, I think! The cats fought over who got to sit/sleep on it straight out of the package, and they don't mind being zipped up in it at all! I used it two days ago to cut their nails â€” first time I was able to cut them by myself! There are two Velcro slots at the front on each side for their paws to come out. This morning, I used the bag to apply medicine to their ears by myself...super easy! It's made of a heavyweight-type fabric that keeps their feet secure so they don't run away, and protects you from their sharp nails. No, it doesn't protect you from biting, but I don't know of anything reasonable that does. But for normal cats, who just don't like to be 'fiddled' with, this bag is a godsend. I highly recommend it!" â€”K. ZaineaGet it from Amazon for $38.95+ (available in sizes Sâ€“XL and eight colors). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I was a bit skeptical about this because I thought it was just a glorified metal stick for $7. My tongue would be pretty dirty and white, and could never really be fully cleaned with a toothbrush. After purchasing and using it, I only wish I got it sooner, and it's one of my best purchases. It is just a single piece of metal but it has a an edge that's just sharp enough to scrape all the nasty stuff off without hurting. It takes a few days to get used to but I don't have much problem using it to clean deep in the back of my tongue. It's easy to clean and all the dirt rinses right off. I would highly recommend this; there's really nothing else that has done a good as a job cleaning my tongue." â€”AlanGet it from Amazon for $6.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "I was skeptical of products like this, but I figured it was cheap enough to try. I'm SO glad I did! I always have what I call 'fluh fluhs' coming out of the part on my head and no matter how many times I wet them down they stick straight up again. This product sticks them down and they stay down! The only caution I would give is that there's a little learning curve of how hard to press the wand to your hair. I find that I need a very light touch or I get too much of the product in my hair, which then looks a little greasy. If you wipe the brush as you pull it out you should be ok â€” just like mascara! Great buy!" â€”tinyntuffGet it from Amazon for $7.98. | amazon.comPromising review: "Totally impressed! The unassuming generic packaging and label left me a bit skeptical but this stuff is almost as exciting as the wine I spilled! This cabernet stain sat on my ivory faux fur blanket for over a month before I tried this product. Completely gone in one try! Get this. Seriously. You wonâ€™t be disappointed." â€”PersianTessGet it from Amazon for $6.67. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF instagram.com, youtube.comPromising review: "I LOVE this exfoliator! I was skeptical but it really cleans my skin and doesnâ€™t dry me out or burn my skin. I have combo skin and it is great. It makes my makeup blend easier on my skin. I love it so much, I tried it on my husbandâ€™s oily skin and he was impressed. I will be buying more from this line for sure." â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $28. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I was highly skeptical given A. This is just shampoo B. Most of the reviews mentioned fleas and not ticks C. My dog was FULL of ticks... I mean at least 15-20 that I could see. I would have to warn you, that after using this shampoo, keep your dog OUTSIDE for 24 to 48 hours. I did not. In fact, I came home to a plethora of dead ticks in my living room. Dead ticks EVERYWHERE. I counted at least 10 little ones.. and the big ones... dear god... my dog found them before i could and burst them... leaving blood everywhere. That day will forever be known as the Tick Massacre of 2016." â€”sharon atkinsGet it from Amazon for $9.79. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This product is amazing. I have tried the regular strength Easy-Off and was disappointed so when I came across this I was skeptical, but after reading the views, I decided to give it a try. I'm glad I did; this did wonders for my oven. Cleaned all the stuck-on spots that other cleaners missed with ease. I let it sit for two hours and tested a small section and I was pleased with the results so far so i let it sit overnight and almost all of it came off with no problem. I did have to scrub some off but not like other products. This is a life saver." â€”trisha skubiszGet it from Amazon for $5.99. | AmazonPromising review: "This stuff works! My silver lab was losing fur on both sides of his torso (color dilute alopecia) so I researched a bit and found this item. He had lost so much fur on his sides that you could see his skin. I was skeptical it would live up to all the good reviews but I was desperate. Not only did it work, but it exceeded my expectations! After about three weeks of daily use I started to notice a difference. After six weeks, not only had his fur totally grown back, but it was thicker and shinier than ever. People have started commenting on how soft and shiny his fur is! I canâ€™t recommend this product strongly enough!" â€”Michelle ElliottGet it from Amazon for $15.77. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This is amazing quality; I'm surprised it worked especially with the price. I was so scared and skeptical since I have extremely sensitive teeth! The first few times you feel like some stains were lifted and others weren't, so you think it looks blotchy. Don't be scared; its lifting the really bad stains first!! And the blotchiness you feel is there but goes away after the next treatment. It worked in four days; i saw the difference in my teeth. No Photoshop needed! I'm continuing to use it and reordering refills :)" â€”Angela G â™¡Get it from Amazon for $39.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I was initially skeptical of how well this kit would work (I mean, it was only $20!) and I wasnâ€™t sure if the foggy-ness on my headlights was inside the lens or on the outside. But after seeing it for myself, I am now a believer! Seriously though, for $20, it makes it look like you basically have a brand new pair of lights! It is *so* worth the purchase. Iâ€™d highly recommend it, and whenever it wears off, I will certainly be purchasing another kit and doing this again." â€”KysondraGet it from Amazon for $19.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Itâ€™s been great to use for tons of things other than fungal problems. I was a little skeptical essential oils would do the trick, but this pushed me to do a little more research. The tea tree oil is at a high enough concentration that it is a very mild analgesic and overall it seems to help my skin recover, so Iâ€™ve been using it on cuts/scrapes once theyâ€™ve started closing. Iâ€™ve also had some luck using it to control underarm odor that is usually pretty difficult to control (I usually need to use products with aluminum). Title Headline: 14 Ocean Creatures That Show Just How Wild The Earth Actually Is
Short Description Sub Headline: Nature is beautiful and terrifying.
Content Body: 14 Ocean Creatures That Show Just How Wild The Earth Actually Is | Nature is beautiful and terrifying. | Posted on January 24, 2020, 13:03 GMT | January 24, 2020, 13:03 GMT | Ben ArmsonBuzzFeed Staff | | By Wildestanimal / Getty Images, Aldorado10 / Getty ImagesPhysalia physalis, more commonly known as the "Portuguese man o' war" is often mistaken as a jellyfish, but is in fact a siphonophore. A siphonophore is an animal that is made up of a colony of organisms working together, meaning that the man o' war is in fact a group of animals!The man o' war get its name from its uppermost polyp, which is a gas-filled bladder that floats above the water, resembling an old warship. The man o' war's tentacles can grow to 165 feet in length and deliver a venom that can kill small fish and other small creatures. Although it can't kill humans it will give you a nasty sting, if your like me and you do kind of want to know what that weirdly beautiful gas-bag feels like, maybe think twice. | Mookmook / Getty Images, BBCThe Giant Trevally which is located in the Indo-Pacific region, is an apex predator â€“ meaning that it is basically the bad bitch of the sea. It can grow up to 170cm in length and feeds mainly on fish and crustaceans, but can also be found feeding on birds too. It is so skilled as a hunter that it can be seen leaping out of the water to grab birds as they fly close to the water to feed. Land or sea no animal is safe from this fish!

Title Headline: 36 Ways To Make Cleaning Your Whole House Easier
Short Description Sub Headline: The faster you clean, the faster you can reunite with your couch.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 36 Ways To Make Cleaning Your Whole House Easier | The faster you clean, the faster you can reunite with your couch. | Posted on January 24, 2020, 12:01 GMT | January 24, 2020, 12:01 GMT | Emma McAnawBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comPromising review: "I fell in love with this product some 15 years ago and I am so very happy that it's still available in the same wonderful formula as ever. It has a fantastic citrus scent. This takes care of any stain so fast and efficiently, it's become a party trick. I have seriously poured red wine over a white comforter to demonstrate how great it is. It is a miracle in a bottle! We use it for all sorts of cleaning on materials around the house, and one bottle has lasted us years! This is definitely a product every home should have." â€”Melanie NolenGet it from Amazon for $6.67.Check out other "14 Stain Removal Hacks We Know Actually Work Because We Tried Them" to avoid future freak-outs! | | | amazon.com, amazon.comThis comes as a starter kit: one sweeper, seven dry sweeping cloths, and three wet mop cleaning solution cloths!Promising review: "This product saved me â€” I have arthritis in my back and knees, and normal mopping and ringing out were such a chore and pain to my joints. The Swiffer is so easy: no bending, no rinsing out, no wringing. I just put a wet pad on, run it over the floors, and they come out clean. When the pad gets dirty, you just change it. I recommend this great product to everyone if they want a truly clean floor with no hassle." â€”Frank PaolucciGet it from Amazon for $11.97. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | amazon.comPlus it feeds your wood protective carnauba wax and beeswax to give it some ~luster~ and extend its lifetime.Promising review: "OMG! This is the most AMAZING product! We inherited some antique furniture from the '30s that had been in storage forever. It was dry, dirty, and not much to look at. I used this product on it and the oak wood literally came alive, showing the beautiful grain and texture of the wood. I have since used it on my oak kitchen cabinets and they look AMAZING! I will never use anything else other than this product on my wood surfaces! No greasy feel, just a fantastic smell!" â€”Tiffany SadowskiGet it from Amazon for $8.48.To learn more, check out "This Wood Polish's Before-And-After Photos Will Make You A Believer". | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | amazon.comPromising review: "I've seen the commercials for years and thought it was another gimmick. Our dog has been bringing in mud and jumping on our bed right after. Washing with detergent alone didn't remove the stains very well. I washed it with some of this stuff and all of it came out. I couldn't see where the stains previously were. Needless to say, I started doing a bunch of loads of white clothes to get them all whiter!" â€”KristyGet it from Amazon for $12.89+ | amazon.comIts natural rubber bristles attract pet hair on multiple surfaces, like carpet, tile, hardwood, and linoleum AND has a built-in rubber squeegee (aka the thing you use on your windshield) for cleaning windows and spills. Promising review: "I bought this broom two years ago and it is still going strong! I have four large breed dogs and we have fur EVERYWHERE! This works so, so well! I came back and purchased one for my neighbor and sent one to my favorite pet rescue down south. I am always amazed at what this picks up even after I just ran the vacuum. I also use it to get dust and cobwebs off the floors and ceilings. It truly is a super tool." â€”RoseannGet it from Amazon for $13.33 | amazon.comDid I mention it's lemon-scented?Promising review: "I'm a little embarrassed to write this review; it's been six years since my last oven cleaning. After seeing the results, I couldn't help but spread the word. Sure, it took some beer, a little John Mayer, and a lot of elbow grease, but I got the job done, thanks to this handy little product. It did require two treatments; however, given the circumstances, this product accomplished quite a feat in just an hour. The attached pictures (above) speak for themselves." â€”William FredericksGet it from Amazon for $5.99. | Caroline Miller / Nifty / BuzzFeedGet a can of hairspray from Amazon for $3.59.To learn more, check out "14 Cleaning Hacks We Know Actually Work Because We Tried Them". | Amazon, amazon.comThey're great for windows or any glassware, too!Promising review: "I couldn't get my windows clean using cleaning solution, newsprint, and a lot of elbow grease. There were always streaks and dirt left behind. Enter these things. One quick cleaning, and I do mean quick, and my windows are now cleaner than any windows I've ever cleaned. It's simply amazing. We were all standing around in utter shock and delight before running around trying the cloths on other stuff: the TV, the picture glass, etc. I know it sounds corny, but I couldn't wait to get up this morning, because I woke up in the middle of the night excitedly thinking about trying it on the car today. They are truly, truly amazing." â€”Amazon CustomerGet a pack of eight from Amazon for $14.98. | amazon.comEach application lasts about 12 days! Refills have six gel stamp uses, and each box has two refills.Promising review: "Love these. They keep the toilet clean. So you squeeze this thick, nice smelling gel stuff onto the inside of your toilet bowl using the dispenser that comes with â€” easy. It lasts a few weeks according to how often your toilet is flushed. Each time you flush, water runs over the gel, cleaning the bowl and dispensing a fresh scent. I've watched as, ahem, dirty stuff stuck on the inside of the bowl gets washed away as the cleaner works its magic. I've used these for years and highly recommend." â€”Johnny's girlGet a pack of two from Amazon for $9.99. | One Good ThingPromising review (for the lavender essential oil): "I am absolutely in love with this! I use it for many different things around my home. I use it to keep my mattress, pillows and down comforter fresh. It helps me get a better night sleep, since the lavender is a calming solution." â€”kimmyGet them from Amazon: baking soda for $3.08 and lavender essential oil for $7.99.Check out more from One Good Thing for "How To Clean A Mattress". | amazon.comAnd it's lightweight so lifting it isn't a *chore*. Promising review: "Have long hair? Have you killed other vacuums with your (slightly worrying amount) of shedding? Then look no further. We bought a another Bissell vacuum a year ago, and it didn't take long for my long hair to just kill the little vacuum. Now, we have this vacuum and our apartment is actually clean because my hair is not too much for it. The bristles have grooves that prevent hair from caking on, and it's very easy to clean. The brushes are also adjustable, so you can really get into the carpet if you want. It's also pretty light for something so heavy duty. For the price, it's a great vacuum and would really work if your place isn't very big, as the cord isn't super long." â€”J. HallerGet it from Amazon for $92.70. | amazon.comPromising review: "This works extremely well. We haven't done any cleaning on our dishwasher in five years, and the sliding dish trays were tough to pull out or push in, there was detergent build-up all over the inside, and there was a milky film on all our cups. I bought Affresh, ran the dishwasher with two tablets while it was empty, and the difference was astounding. There was still some build-up and I figured it would require another cycle, so I popped another two tablets in, ran the machine a second time, and now it looks and sounds brand-new. No more film on the glasses, no more dirty dishes from clogged sprayers, no more odors, or build-up around the door seals. I'm going to be buying Affresh from now on, and hopefully it will extend the life of my dishwasher." â€”MartouneGet it from Amazon for $3.71. | amazon.comPromising review: "I used it on our tubs, toilets, sinks, and shower. It took one bottle of this stuff to achieve the same result as three bottles of other brands. I will buy this again hands down. I just sprayed, walked away for a few minutes, and wiped and rinsed." â€”Carrie D.Get it from Amazon $4.98. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Just 14 Things Under $20 That'll Probably Make A Big, Big Difference
Short Description Sub Headline: Big difference for very little coin.
Content Body: Shopping | Just 14 Things Under $20 That'll Probably Make A Big, Big Difference | Big difference for very little coin. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 05:40 GMT | January 31, 2020, 05:40 GMT | Mariela SummerhaysBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Bunnings, Timbermate / Via youtube.comI am not a handy person, so I've kind of just accepted the scratches and dents my home and furniture are slowly accumulating *eyes my tiny humans and cat*. This brilliant little tool, which comes in every conceivable hue of wood, can be rubbed into the surface of your furniture or heated to fill larger dents. You can even mix more than one stick to get your desired colour! Now anyone can be a home renovator.Buy a single stick for $6.55 from Bunnings. | | | AmazonThese patches are made of hydrocolloid, a wound-healing material that protects against bacteria. Ultra-thin and complete with a matte finish, they can be worn on top of inflamed and acne-prone skin, and under foundation (!). A few hours later, your zits will have shrunk noticeably. No wonder people are buying these in bulk.Buy a pack of 18 patches for $5.20 from Amazon Australia. | AmazonLook, can't relate. But I've seen the benches y'all are sitting on for hours on end and they can't be great for your back. This water-resistant seat can be used to provide back support â€” or unfolded, as cushioning for both you and a mate. It's easily rolled up, comes in three different colours (blue, red, black) and even has a mesh pocket to keep your cold ones close at hand.Buy for $15.90 from Amazon Australia. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Lush / Via au.lush.com, @lushcosmetics / Via instagram.comI will continue to write about this lotion until someone physically restrains me. This combination of oatmeal, lavender oil and organic cocoa butter is almost solely responsible for the solid eight hours I get every night. It smells heavenly and feels like a warm hug on freshly-showered skin.Plus, Lush only purchases from suppliers that don't test on animals, so you can feel good about where you're putting your dollars.Buy a 95g jar for $17.95 from Lush. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | AmazonCast iron skillets are the preferred pans of many professional chefs, due to the even distribution of heat across the entire surface and unparalleled heat retention. This one features lips on either side for easy pouring and at 3.5" in diameter, is perfect for cooking a sweet dessert for one or two.If you're looking for inspiration on what you can make your date with your cast iron skillet, here are 21 recipes you can start with.Buy for $19.95 from Amazon Australia. | AmazonReviewers say that this stamp makes the perfect winged eye every time â€” infinitely easier than trying to get even lines freehand. Each set comes with two pens â€” one for your left eye, one for right â€” and is water-resistant and smudge-proof.Buy for $11.57 from Amazon Australia. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: We've Gathered 14 Of This Week's Best Deals You'll Want To Throw Your Wallet At
Short Description Sub Headline: Fashion, tech and homewares, oh my!
Content Body: Shopping | We've Gathered 14 Of This Week's Best Deals You'll Want To Throw Your Wallet At | Fashion, tech and homewares, oh my! | Posted on January 20, 2020, 00:20 GMT | January 20, 2020, 00:20 GMT | Mariela SummerhaysBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF @silklaundry / Via instagram.com, THE ICONICOriginally $250/ Buy now for $175 from THE ICONIC.In recent years, slip dresses have come back from their '90s hey day, and I for one, am here for it. Not all slip dresses are made equal though â€” cheap material, unflattering cuts â€” but this one here is the crÃ¨me de la crÃ¨me. Cut from pure silk in a form-flattering silhouette, its midi-length hem means it can be worn wherever without it looking like you've just run away from bridesmaid duties. | LoverOriginally $450 / Buy now for $270 from Amazon Australia.So it has the hallmarks of every conservative family-friendly garment â€” subdued colours, thick shoulder straps, midi-length, A-line skirt. But, being from brilliant Aussie label Lover, the Eden Midi-Dress also features a lace-up, rope corset to the waist. Something for Nanna, something for you. | AmazonOriginally $529 / Buy now for $329 from Amazon Australia.Valid until January 29.Maybe you're an e-reader cynic, as I once was. But there comes a point when your back aches from carrying three different books in your shoulder bag and your bank account looks a bit sad from your impulse buys â€” at which point an e-reader starts to look like an attractive option. If that's where you are now, the Kindle Oasis has a glare-free screen, adaptive front lights (no need to stop reading as the sun goes down!), is waterproof, holds thousands of books and a single charge lasts weeks! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Natalia Krslovic / BuzzFeedOriginally $111.96 / Buy now for $83.97 from Amazon Australia.I recently dressed my friend, Nat, in this dress for a style swap challenge video you can watch here. Of the form-fitting, midi-length dress with asymmetrical sleeve, she said:Promising review: "When I first saw this dress, I was simultaneously excited and scared. I love an asymmetrical sleeve, but I don't often go for anything this figure-hugging for fear of it not flattering my body.Turns out, I had nothing to worry about. This dress was sexy, comfortable and showed off all my curves â€” while still looking elegant and classy. I really felt super glam and I loved it. I was initially worried that some of my rolls were showing through, but once I'd gotten over my own insecurities, I was really vibing this look."-Natalia Krslovic | Harris Scarfe, TontineOriginally $209.99 / Buy now for $104.99 from Harris Scarfe.As you may have heard, Aussie retailer, Harris Scarfe, entered into voluntary administration last month and has begun the process of closing its doors. That being said, there are a bunch of great deals to pick up this week, including this King-sized, Aussie wool doona, that you can wash â€” which is great, because you're not quite sure that airing your doona out does very much at all. | Originally $39.07 / Buy now for $29.31 from Amazon Australia.Valid until February 8.Yes, I know you keep your appointments in your phone and it's been working well for you so far. But take it from someone who has just made the move back to journals, your productivity is going to go off. Research indicates that writing down your goals immediately gives you a greater chance of achieving them â€” and if not now, then when? This one comes with monthly calendar grids and space for daily to-do lists or hourly appointments.Not feeling this one? Browse up to 25% off Moleskine Notebooks here. | TIgerlilyOriginally $129 / Buy for $77.40 from Amazon Australia.If a stinking hot Aussie summer is the question, these lightweight, cotton pants here are the answer. Featuring the most extravagant bell-bottom legs with gathered, frilled hem, they're basically a built-in cooling system around your calves. If that didn't already convince you of their comfort â€” elastic waist and side pockets. THE DREAM. | Originally $59.99 / Buy now for $29 from THE ICONIC.I went to Rome when I was a teenager and I kid you not, the only souvenir I brought home with me were heels that looked exactly like these. Everything â€” from the red, patent finish, the croc-embossed detail, ankle strap and pointed toe â€” oozes Italian glamour. Beautiful thing about the chunky heel means you can wear it with jeans during the day, as easily as with a dress at night. | JB Hi-FiOriginally $329 / Buy now for $164 from JB Hi-Fi.So by now you've probably lost your obscenely expensive earbuds or worn down the cable on your infinitely-old corded earphones. Enter these over-ear wireless headphones. The best of both worlds, it gives powerful sound, is intuitive to use and takes up little room in your bag. Most importantly, it has the best in active noise cancellation, so you can shut the world out when necessary. | IKEAOriginally $249 / Buy now for $179 from IKEA.Right, so one of these babies entered my life for the first time recently and now I'm angry at myself for not getting one sooner. Chances are you, like me, sit for hours in one spot, shoulders up to your ears, everything but your fingers completely immobile. When standing at your desk, you can't help but shift your weight, move around to pick up things still at your waist's level etc etc. Move from sitting to standing with only the simple rotations of a crank handle.It might've cut my remedial massage bills in half, but let's be honest, I'm still going just as often, regardless. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF
