Title Headline: 46 Products That Might Make You Want To Exercise More This Year
Short Description Sub Headline: Don't sweat it â€” you're about to get super motivated.
Content Body: Shopping | 46 Products That Might Make You Want To Exercise More This Year | Don't sweat it â€” you're about to get super motivated. | Posted on January 21, 2020, 04:09 GMT | January 21, 2020, 04:09 GMT | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | AmazonI've also been using this game as a way to supplement my trips to the gym. This may seem like a childish adventure from Nintendo, but JEEZ within moments I'm sweating my butt off. To play, you'll place a JoyCon into both the ring con and a leg strap so your movements are monitored. To move through each level you have to physically run in place and each time you "battle" an enemy you have to do 15 reps of an exercise of your choosing. For example, each time I complete a squat the enemy receives a "kick." It's so fun I don't realize I'm working out until the game reminds me to take a break and have some water. It even monitors your heart rate for you. It's more intense than you'd expect!Get it from Amazon for $79.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Arrived today. Very easy to set up. I had it up on the wall in less than an hour. Looks great! I love that the medals can be hung below the bibs. I have 11 hung in total, which take up the entire rack. My only complaint is that I have 42 bibs hung and it is getting rather full-looking. Looks like I'll be ordering another bib display shortly... or run less races (and that's not happening). ;) Happy running, all!" â€”RocknRunnerGet it from Amazon for $34.99. | AmazonThis book truly transformed my workout mentality. It made me want to get up super early and run before the chaos of the day began. I started right after finishing her book and have continued ever since! If Khloe can do it, why can't we?Promising review: "I bought this book not knowing much about it, except it was written by a Kardashian and I have a weakness sometimes of binge-watching their show. This book not only makes me see Khloe completely different, but this book is one of the most inspiring and motivating things I've read! After reading a chapter I found myself wanting to immediately work out, and become a kinder and driven person. I just happen to be a new mom working hard to lose the baby weight and stay positive, and this was the perfect book to keep me going when the going got tough and motivated me to not give up and push myself harder! HIGHLY recommend this awesome book!!!!" â€”Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $26.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Love this belt! It is super comfortable and sturdy. I bought the belt to hold my iPhone 8 Plus and keys while I run. The iPhone 8 Plus is a tight squeeze but fits even in its OtterBox case. I love the hook to snap my keys on so they stay in place and I donâ€™t have to worry about them falling out. I did not even find the need to flip the belt as my phone and keys felt secure and I wanted easier access to my phone. It fits snugly on my hip and the belt did not bounce around on my run even with my heavy phone inside. All in all super happy with this purchase. Worth every penny!" â€”Elise V. RydingGet it from Amazon for $22.99+ (available in sizes 2XSâ€“2XL and in nine colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comIn my opinion, the hardest part about exercising is finding a workout that you find fun and actually want to spend time doing. Enter: the Simply Fit Board. You can use it to balance during planks, as support for push-ups, or to strengthen your core. You're gonna love it!Promising review: "Love this board! I use every day and it is a great workout. It's transportable, durable, and highly effective! My abs look amazing! You can work cardio, core, upper body and lower body in a great variety of workouts on YouTube designed for the Simply Fit Board â€” can't give higher praise for this one!" â€”Heidi HoganGet it from Amazon for $14.80 (available in four colors). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "Great! Fun way to mix it up for home workouts and travel. The dice are big and chunky and easy to read. Recommended!" â€”Kirsten B.Get it from Amazon for $13.41. | Hill CityPromising review: "This is a neat bag that doesn't look too high brow for the gym, looks rather government-issue. It does have some nice features, the zippers and the water repellency are neat adds. The build quality is still suspect but as long as the stitching for the handles have been done with some stress testing at the plant, it looks pretty strong." â€”McFlyGet it from Hill City for $148. | NintendoI admittedly am someone who thrives while working out at the gym, but there are many exercises I've been dying to try and don't because I don't want to embarrass myself. Boxing is one of them. Luckily, I can start practicing my skills (and break a decent sweat!) at home while playing this super-fun game on the Nintendo Switch. I use this game as a way to mix up my exercises / when I don't feel like venturing out to the gym. I have to say, it's a SERIOUS workout. I'm usually sore for days after and have burnt up to 300 calories in 30 minutes! If you get tired of the provided songs, mute your TV and turn on your favorite workout playlist â€” a great hack, if you ask me!Get it from Nintendo for $49.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I don't honestly know if there are enough words to express how much I love these gloves! They are seriously the most comfortable gloves in the world. They have awesome quality and construction, these will last a long time. I went with the 10 oz. ones and it was the perfect match. They fit snugly with wraps on, which is exactly how I like them. I use these regularly both on the bag and in sparring matches and love them for both! Can't beat them!!!" â€”RyanGet them from Amazon for $19.99+ (available in sizes 8 oz.â€“16 oz. and in eight styles). | mobotnation / Via instagram.com, NordstromPromising review: "This is the best water bottle ever! Iâ€™ve been looking for a good straw water bottle and this one is perfect. Others sound funny and donâ€™t get a good suction. This one comes with a plastic and stainless straw. I also canâ€™t believe how awesome the quality of the foam roller is and actually use it way more often than I thought I would. Also, love products made by woman!" â€”ajgreenGet it from Nordstrom for $49.99 (available in four styles). | Outdoor VoicesYou can choose from three different bra styles and four types of leggings to put together your perfect workout ~look~. While one pair of leggings usually costs $75, when you by Outdoor Voices' Rec Kit you'll get a full outfit for $95. Not bad, I tell ya ;)Get it from Outdoor Voices for $95 (both bras and leggings available in sizes XSâ€“XL and in eight colors). | Good AmericanGet it from Good American for $59 (available in sizes 0â€“7 and in three styles). | AthletaPromising review: "I love this bra! I was hesitant about the straps on the back being functional, while they are very cute; but it fits well and holds up fine during yoga (although I won't be using this for any more intensive training). I have the matching leggings and I really like the pattern, and the Powervita fabric is so nice!" â€”kr2107Get it from Athleta for $39.99 (available in sizes 2XSâ€“XL and two styles). | BuzzFeed, amazon.comNothing pisses me off more than when I'm working out and the wire from my headphones gets stuck on something and they get RIPPED out of my ears. I need to step out of the Stone Age and upgrade to a wireless pair like these.Promising review: "Fantastic headphones! They stay charged FOREVER! I had them fully charged and used them for an hour on average 6 times a week and did not need to charge them again for a month! The only complaints I have is when doing certain exercises they tend to slide off my head a little so I have to adjust them a few times." â€”Jessica JohnstonGet it from Amazon for $29.99+ (available in eight colors).This is also one of our BuzzFeed Reviews picks for the best wireless headphones! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Mallory Mower / BuzzFeed, Heather Braga / BuzzFeedAh, the magic of technology. From boxing and speed skating to dodgeball and combat fighting, there are tons of simulation games for the Oculus Quest that'll help you work up a sweat at home.Get them from Oculus: Rift for $399.99, Quest for $399.99.And check out one BuzzFeed writer's full review of the Oculus Rift here. | AmazonPromising review: "I love mine! I am still fascinated with checking my info frequently and it works to motivate me on sluggish days. I wasn't sure I could get 10,000 steps a day in so I set it to 8,000 steps a day but I am managing to exceed the 10,000 on most days as I am averaging more than that. I have started running in addition to doing my 2x/ week weight workouts and still occasionally doing my at home DVD workouts. It also helps to make sure I am drinking enough water (although this requires that you log in how much you drink). I love the reminders! It buzzes me to let me know when I have hit my goal and to remind me to get my 250 steps in per hour. I also can log what i am eating and I was surprised to see I eat more calories than I thought. I am not currently trying to lose weight as I am breastfeeding my baby so I am not worried about that for the moment but I do want to keep working out to get back in shape. This is great for motivation, for tracking so I can see how I am doing and then when I go back in the log I can see how well I have done." â€”DeliaGet it from Amazon for $143.99+ (available in two sizes and seven colors). | PelotonI am SO interested in trying out one of these bad boys. I'm a sucker for the commercials and have even gone as far as downloading the Peloton app in an attempt to recreate the classes on a stationary bike at my gym â€” but it's just not the same as being in your own home. If you already own one of these bikes, can I come over and give it a go? Kthanks.Promising review: "Peloton, you have taken things to the next level... so happy I have a variety of classes, not only spinning. Iâ€™ve owned my bike for two years and my only complaint (at that time) was variety beyond the bike. I now have a new love for bootcamp, running, strength, stretching and yoga, and of course spinning. We dropped our family gym membership just a month ago and we have dedicated space in our house to have our tread, bike, and free weights. This was a game-changer! Thank you for offering what we all need." â€”AnonymousGet it from Peloton for $2,245+ (available in four packages). | amazon.com, amazon.comKacey Musgraves even posted about having/loving this exact water bottle! So, you can be both *happy* you're drinking lots of water and *sad* you always have to pee. Such is life!Promising review: "I'm in love with this bottle! Why? Because I only need to fill it ONCE and have my hydration requirements are met. The design is trendy, the motivational quotes help me stay on track AND it's pretty much portable. I'd recommend using the hand bar instead of the little rope thing because a full bottle IS HEAVY! Love it and would recommend it for my fellow water laggers :) Enjoy!" â€”AnisaGet it from Amazon for $13.95+ (available in 3 sizes and 35 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comA few years ago I broke my foot and found I needed major support from my sneakers, not just for working out but for everyday use. I bought my first pair of Asics and never looked back. They are cushioned, comfortable, and exactly what you'd want in a sneaker â€” and over 3.7K Amazon customers agree!Promising review: "I love these shoes! I am hard to please due to plantar fasciitis, fallen arches, and lots of screws in my ankle. Great arch support and really beautifully designed shoe. The photo doesn't do them justice. They make me happy looking at them and wearing them. I only wear them to work out and they feel great! Great price too!!" â€”T. DiscosolaGet them from Amazon: women's sizes for $59.95+ (available in sizes 6â€“11 and in 10 styles) or men's sizes for $54.50+ (available in sizes 6â€“15 and in 16 styles) | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I absolutely LOVE these running shoes. They are extremely lightweight, feels like you are running on air yet with support. Super cute, look exactly as pictured and are true to size. I always wear a 6 and the 6 fit me perfectly. I would order these 100 times over, actually contemplating getting another pair in a different color just because these are so perfect. Iâ€™ve had them for over two months and they have not worn out at all. Wipes clean and doesnâ€™t stain which is amazing!! I regularly run outside so I destroy my running shoes, these Iâ€™ve just taken a wet paper towel to and they are good as new! Sooo so happy with this purchase!" â€”KatGet them from Amazon for $45.99+ (available in women's sizes 5â€“11 and 25 styles). | Amazon, amazon.comHow CUTE are these? They are technically weights to add additional resistance to your workout, but they are also very stylish! You can wear them on your wrists or around your ankles during at-home yoga for an extra boost during your routine.Promising review: "These weights are incredible â€“ absolutely stunning! Such great quality too. I got them for walking and yoga but I think I am going to wear them everywhere! They are very comfy and soft to the touch. And I LOVE the packaging. They come with a free bag to carry them in. I am definitely going to buy more colors." â€”JackieGet them from Amazon for $49 (available in four colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comI have one of these yoga mats and it has been a game-changer. Whether I'm taking it to an actual class or using it to follow a workout on YouTube at home, I know I'm not going to slip and hurt myself (can you tell I'm accident-prone?). Its many cute style options are for sure an added bonus!Promising review: "Love love love love this!! I'm 5'10" with LONG legs, so regular mats don't work for me. I step off them and they're not big enough. This one is amazing...nice and thick. Once I washed/prepped it, there's not slippage. You do have to wash/scrub it or it starts out pretty slick. But totally worth the money. I haven't used any other of my mats since. Thinking about getting another one to leave at my office." â€”CareyidahoGet it from Amazon for $22.48+ (available in 34 styles). | amazon.com, AmazonI was first introduced to this product via watching the Kardashians work out on Instagram (yes, really) and I've grown to love it! It's really simple to use â€” I like to do my crunches on it, as it gives me more back support. There are tons of other ways to break a sweat using this, so def consider adding it to your shopping cart.Promising review: "Omg...I love this. I just did 5k race with my son and his friends, it's called The Inflatable5k, meaning you run 3 miles while having inflatable obstacles to run, jump, or climb upon. I did it, but I have to say it was harder then I thought to balance on a balloon! I bought this wanting to improve, but I was not expecting all this FUN. I really love it! It's so easy on my joints â€” in fact when I use this in place of my step for aerobics DVDs, my knee pain is gone...for real! Unexpected bonus!!" â€”KatGet it from Amazon for $99.99+ (available in 11 styles). | Amazon, amazon.comThis is a prime example of something my gym has that I've always been too scared to try (for fear of quite literally falling on my face). The sliding technique used with this workout tool is great for building up your core â€” and actually looks kinda...fun? I'm gonna order a pair of these gliding discs to test out on my wood floors in the privacy of my own home. Who's with me?!Promising review: "This seems like a simple idea, but I would never have thought of it. I like the ability to exercise arms, back, chest, and core in so many variations. You can cater movement based on how you position yourself and move the gliders; the nuance of movement is near limitless. I tried it on my hardwood floor, but prefer the easier gliding on carpet. I compare it to my ab roller and find it to be an interesting alternative. I can keep my hands with palms downward open flat or place my fists on it for slightly different stressing of the hand and forearm muscles." â€”CharlieGet a set of two from Amazon for $10.97. | amazon.com, AmazonEssentially a tire with handles, this item is going to roll right into your workout routine. It's great for strengthening your abs, shoulder, arms, and back â€” which is pretty unbelievable based on how compact it is. Sign me UP.Promising review: "The little ab wheel is deceptively simple and sturdy. It looks like a kid's toy, but with proper daily use, it will give you a serious workout. It will strengthen not only your core (abs and lower back) but your arms, shoulders, legs, and entire body as well. In addition, it will give you an aerobic workout, because your heart and lungs will want to join in the fun!" â€”WhizzetsGet it from Amazon for $13.50+ (available in two colors). | Amazon, amazon.comDon't believe me? Order one of these and give it a try. This seemingly harmless workout tool makes for a serious strength-training sesh.Promising review: "This is actually a great kettlebell for the price. It's also much smaller than other coated kettlebells I have, so great space-wise. The handle is a perfect size for two hand grabbing, not all of my kettlebells are. I was worried the handle might not be smooth, but it is powder coated and has a great feel when I swing it. I'm going to order more before they disappear." â€”The Great BuzzwamiGet it from Amazon for $13.99+ (available in 5â€“50 pounds). | amazon.com, amazon.comExercise balls are a must-have for any home workout! You can use them to improve your core, for overall balance, alongside a Pilates video, and much more. Not to mention they're pretty fun to just bounce on.Promising review: "I can't even begin to say enough good things about this stability ball! My back has gotten so much stronger since I started using it as an office chair for one or two hours per day! I work from home and my back had gotten incredibly weak, to the point that I could only walk 1/4 mile before the pain would get EXTREMELY bad and unbearable. After two weeks of using the ball, I can now walk 1 mile before pain begins â€” that is a HUGE improvement and has made an even bigger impact on my happiness and quality of life. I might add that it is REALLY fun to bounce on it! I having been having a ball with it (pardon the pun)." â€”ValerieGet it from Amazon for $18.90+ (available in 3 sizes and 10 colors). | caliabycarrie / Via instagram.com, CALIAI have a pair of leggings from Calia by Carrie Underwood and they are one of my favorites to work out in. The material is unbelievably soft and do a really great job at wicking away sweat during even the most intense workouts. I've worn them to spin classes, to run, and while exercising at home. They're definitely a splurge-worthy pair you'll be happy you invested in â€” I mean, they have POCKETS!Get them from CALIA by Carrie Underwood for $70 (available in sizes XSâ€“XL). | amazon.com, AmazonDon't act like you don't know exactly what I'm referring to! Anyways, this body workout bar can transform any doorway into a personal gym. Promising review: "I live by this iron gym. If you ever need a way to build confidence before embarrassing yourself at the gym with wrong form and two measly pull-ups, grind it out in your home and watch the improvement with this product. Itâ€™s affordable and very stable. I weigh about 205 lbs and it holds my weight perfectly! I started out doing maybe two pull-ups and I practiced and Iâ€™m now doing 20 a clip. Iâ€™ve done it and you can too!" â€”MarcusGet it from Amazon for $36.49. | Amazon, amazon.comUh, hello, there's a skull and crossbones on the handles of this jump rope! So freakin' cool! It is ideal for those interested in cardio training and is very lightweight â€” great for storing in your junk drawer and busting out when you're ready to sweat. Plus, it has 4.9K five-star reviews on Amazon, so you know it's legit.Promising review: "Very good-quality materials are used, starting from the steel rope, which is encased in some sort of heavy-duty, slightly clear plastic to the smooth bearings. The finish of the rope is very slick and seems like it'll hold up a long time. If you grab the handle and spin it, the bearing will go 10 revolutions easily, speaking to the quality of the bearings. I've only had it a couple of weeks and it is holding up great. For $10, probably one of the best ropes you can get. And from what I read about the owners of the company and their warranty, seems like these folks will be more than happy to get a new rope over to you ASAP if your current one breaks for whatever reason." â€”RomanGet it from Amazon for $10. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "With a new baby I found myself doing a lot of upper body exercises while holding my little one. While this is a great upper-body and potentially full-body workout, I found the baby to be a little too squirmy to be effective so I decided to pick up this medicine ball. It was a great choice. It's grippy, compact, and effective. It also doesn't have a tendency to spit up on me while doing chest presses, which is a big plus. Best part â€” this ball doesn't complain if I accidentally drop it. Honestly â€” this is a great basic medicine ball. The rubber skin provides great grip. No 'heavy spots,' with the weight evenly distributed across the ball. There are plenty of quick exercises you can do at home to do a full-body workout with the benefit of building both slow-twitch and fast-twitch muscle. Ball seems plenty durable and should last a good long time. Great purchase. Thinking of buying another in a different weight." â€”Todd W.Get it from Amazon for $28.50+ (available in 10 weights). | Amazon, amazon.comYou can work out SO many different parts of your body using these stretchy little guys â€” and you don't even have to leave your bedroom.Promising review: "I have had these for a few weeks now and I must say I'm thoroughly impressed with the packaging and quality of these bands. You get everything you see in the product pictures and it is exactly as advertised. There is an instructional pamphlet that details several different exercises possible with these bands with images of the different setups. The foam bars are sturdy and I had no trouble getting a good workout from using the bands with the bars. There isn't really anything I can fault this product on. It is truly a terrific exercise product that will get you results if you put in the effort of using it. A plus is that it is so mobile and compact in the storage bag that I leave it by the television set so that I can get in a little exercise while I am watching" â€”W. KwokGet it from Amazon for $20.98. | PatagoniaPromising review: "This is my all time favorite jacket. Goes with me everywhere I go, itâ€™s packable enough to not even second guess myself if I should bring it or not. I use it mainly for bike rides around town and any trips I might need a shell to go over some insulation. Works awesome for how minimal this jacket is." â€”MartiGet it from Patagonia for $99 (available in men's sizes XSâ€“XXL and in seven styles and in women's sizes XSâ€“XL and in eight styles).Or check out a similar jacket on Amazon for $39.25+ (available in women's sizes XSâ€“3XL and in 14 styles). | AmazonPromising review: "I really like how bright they are when I'm out on my early morning runs. I've purchased other lights in the past and they just don't compare. I haven't had to change them yet and I run three to four mornings a week for the last month and a half." â€”SpeedyGet them from Amazon for $11.99 (available in two colors). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Estas experiencias retratan la situaciÃ³n que se vive en los terribles incendios de Australia
Short Description Sub Headline: "Todo estaba en llamas. Tres casas ya no estaban y el fuego estaba a punto de llegar a nuestro Ãºnico lugar de refugio".
Content Body: Estas experiencias retratan la situaciÃ³n que se vive en los terribles incendios de Australia | "Todo estaba en llamas. Tres casas ya no estaban y el fuego estaba a punto de llegar a nuestro Ãºnico lugar de refugio". | publicado January 09, 2020, 16:57 GMT | January 09, 2020, 16:57 GMT | Clare AstonBuzzFeed Staff | Ruth Ellis / BuzzFeedMi ciudad natal se habÃ­a vuelto oscura por el humo de los incendios en la zona. Mis redes sociales repentinamente estaban llenas de historias y publicaciones de viejos amigos y miembros de la comunidad que se preparaban para arriesgar sus vidas por defender sus hogares. Al momento de escribir esto, algunos todavÃ­a lo siguen haciendo. | Siobhan Threlfall / BuzzFeedâ€œMe despertÃ© la maÃ±ana del 31 de diciembre alrededor de las 2:30 porque mi madre gritaba mi nombre. El cielo detrÃ¡s de la casa de mis padres era solo un gran resplandor de color rojo, junto con el rugido del fuego haciendo eco en el valle. Mi mamÃ¡ y nuestros dos perros evacuaron la ciudad. Mi papÃ¡, el jefe de bomberos voluntario de Nerrugundah; mi hermano, Caden; mi hermana, Skye, y yo nos quedamos para proteger la ciudad. Miembros ya estaban llegando al hangar de bomberos para cuando Caden y papÃ¡ llegaron ahÃ­. Inmediatamente, entraron al camiÃ³n para (ir a) investigar el incendio, mientras Skye y yo llamÃ¡bamos a todos en el valle.PapÃ¡ predijo que el fuego no nos impactarÃ­a realmente durante otras dos horas. Mientras esperÃ¡bamos, pusimos sistemas de aspersores, preparamos nuestras bombas de agua y retiramos los tanques de gas de la casa... todo mientras la radio emitÃ­a llamados de auxilio. Hubo llamadas de personas que se encontraban en peligro, llamadas de la tripulaciÃ³n que necesitaba ayuda urgente, asÃ­ como llamadas que solicitaban ambulancias que ahora se necesitaban por todas partes en la Costa Sur. Mi hermano nos contactÃ³ por radio. Ã‰l y otra bombera voluntaria, Ashley, habÃ­an ido a ver cÃ³mo estaban los miembros de la comunidad, pero, por la cantidad de Ã¡rboles caÃ­dos y el fuego que se dirigÃ­a directamente hacia ellos, no pudieron llegar con dos de nuestros miembros de la brigada. Se iban a quedar atrapados en su casa en el paso del fuego. No sabÃ­a si iba a volver a verlos". | | | Ver esta nota en Facebook | AtenciÃ³nEsta imagen es grÃ¡ficaToca para mostrarToca para mostrar

Title Headline: Pink Opened Up About How She "Cannot Get Behind" Plastic Surgery In A Series Of Tweets About Ageing

Content Body: Pink Opened Up About How She "Cannot Get Behind" Plastic Surgery In A Series Of Tweets About Ageing | "Iâ€™ve never really depended on my looks. Iâ€™ve decided that my talent and my individuality is far more important than my face." | Posted on January 21, 2020, 15:10 GMT | January 21, 2020, 15:10 GMT | Ellie WoodwardBuzzFeed Staff | | P!nk@Pink | P!nk | @Pink | Letter to self; Dear Me, youâ€™re getting older.I see lines.Especially when you smile.Your nose is getting bigger..You look(and feel) weird as you get used to this new reality.But your nose looks like your kids, and your face wrinkles where you laugh.And yeah you idiot..u smoked. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | P!nk@Pink | P!nk | @Pink | Continued note to self: Every once in a while you consider altering your face, and then you watch a show where you want to see what the person is feeling... and their face doesnâ€™t move. Iâ€™m cannot get behind it. I just canâ€™t. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | P!nk@Pink | P!nk | @Pink | I want my children to know what I look like when Iâ€™m angry | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | P!nk@Pink | P!nk | @Pink | Iâ€™m fortunate because Iâ€™ve never really depended on my looks. Title Headline: All You Need Is Love...But Also Maybe These 31 Products

Content Body: Shopping | All You Need Is Love...But Also Maybe These 31 Products | The Beatles were actually singing about all of these products. | Posted on January 25, 2020, 03:01 GMT | January 25, 2020, 03:01 GMT | Samantha WiederBuzzFeed Staff | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "Cannot stress enough how amazing these came out!!! I gave them as a Secret Santa gift to my two friends and they said they're the best gift theyâ€™ve ever received. I was a little concerned about the quality of the picture, since it was an iPhone-quality photo off of Facebook, but they came out 10 times better than I had even hoped. 5 stars for sure!!!!" â€”Amandax054Get the, from Amazon for $24 (available in 10 colors, and sizes S and L). | Amazon, amazon.comSome notable recipes include treacle tart, Molly's meat pies, and Kreacher's French onion soup. Pictured right: pumpkin pasties.Promising review: "I LOVE IT, I'm no master chef, but this cookbook might change that. I might even become a master wizard chef! Anyways the recipes are phenomenal, especially the pies! It's pretty basic sometimes, it's more European-type cuisine, so if you don't like haggis, liver, lamb, or other English/Scottish dishes, etc., then these recipes aren't for you. The book references are cute, and I vaguely remember some of them. My younger siblings go crazy when I make anything from this book because they love Harry Potter." â€”TigerlilyGet it from Amazon for free/Kindle Unlimited, or $10.95/hardcover. | amazon.comPromising review: "Wow! I've had it for an afternoon and I'm in love. I can't afford to keep going for human massages. *This* I can afford. I think I'm going to buy another one tomorrow so my wife and I don't fight over whose turn it is. Update a few days later: Okay, this many be getting out of hand! I purchased a second one for my wife last week (very smart thing to do). Today, she just asked me to buy two more, one for her daughter and her sister. I just placed the order. I'm using mine three of four 20 minute sessions a day. It continues to work great. Seriously, this is a wonderful product. Spread the word!" â€”Lynn Robert CarterGet it from Amazon for $49.95. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I got tired of breaking the bank over mascara. My sister suggested Essence Lash Princess False Lash Effect and I IMMEDIATELY fell in love. It provides dramatic length and great volume. I can honestly say I canâ€™t stop looking at my eyelashes in the mirror every single day because of how awesome they look. Also, it is very long wearing. I go from an 8 hour work day right to the gym and sweat like crazy...and this stuff doesnâ€™t budge! I love it!!" â€”Carrie E. MillerGet it from Amazon for $4.99. | AmazonPromising review: "I got these as a gift for a family member who is a wine aficionado, partly for a laugh but also for their great concept. When she opened them, I did get a huge laugh, but once she understood the concept she was amazed. I've received confirmation from her that they work wonders and truly provide an airtight seal. Now all the corks can go in the trash after they come out and a wine condom goes on!!" â€”ThomasGet a pack of six from Amazon for $16.97. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I really love this menu board. It's cute, easy-to-see, and gets the job done at the same time. It has made menu planning, keeping a grocery list, and keeping track of upcoming appointments so much easier. A friend who saw mine has already ordered one for herself. It comes with three markers â€” blue, pink, and green, and you do have to 'prime' the markers first. Once you do that, they work so well and are nice and bright. The menu board is a nice, big size and has a strong magnetic hold." â€”S. WinkeljohnGet it from Amazon for $19.99. | AmazonPromising review: "These were a suggested item for my bullet journal, and they were not at all expensive, so I went ahead and got them. I'm so glad I did. The colors are beautiful, and don't bleed through when writing normally, BUT you cannot hold the pen down in one spot for any amount of time, or they will bleed pretty badly. A great deal for the price." â€”DanielleGet a pack of 10 from Amazon for $5.49. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Very impressed with this belt. This one has a clasp, which makes it super easy and keeps the full design! Great quality and came nicely packaged. Have worn multiple times now and get lots of compliments. The buckle isnâ€™t too big but itâ€™s big enough to make a statement! Definitely recommend purchasing!" â€”Shannon PayneGet it from Amazon for $14.99+ (available in nine colors, and sizes XSâ€”XL). | amazon.comPromising review: "I love these! I was sick of having to scrape face mask gunk out from under my nails so these are a great alternative â€” plus I can use each for a different product if i'm using two at a time, and not risk cross-contamination. They are a little wide though, so they might not fit in all jars and some you might have to scoop the product out first onto another surface for that reason, or if like me, you use a volcanic clay mask, the product bends the silicone a bit if you try to scoop it from the jar since the clay is thick and the silicone is flimsy. BUT, the good news is they won't break from bending AND they are really easy to clean and wipe off!! Adore these and am definitely never going back to brushes that have fibers." â€”Amazon CustomerGet a pack of two from Amazon for $3.98. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I'll start off by saying all matte top coats are porous, so by their nature they won't wear as long as glossy polish. Having said that, the OPI matte top coat lasts just as long and re-applies much better than most other matte tops I've tried. Works great on top of gel manicures! If you're hooked on LED gels like me, this polish works great to matte down the ultra-wet appearance of LED-cured gel polishes. If you want the look of completely nude nails for any reason, (fashion, dress code, acting, etc.), but you don't want to sacrifice that protective shield of your super-strong gel manicures, try applying OPI Matte Top Coat over your clear OPI LED-cured manicure. No one will ever know your nails aren't nude, and they won't chip on every doorknob or keyboard." â€”M. SpaldingGet it from Amazon for $10.50. | AmazonCheck out our write-up of the delicious Mike's Hot Honey!Promising review: "I was a skeptic, but now I AM a believer. This mixed up honey is absolutely fabulous. I ordered three bottles more after my initial order. Why? Because it is really good on everything. And I mean EVERYTHING. Soft pretzels, toast, biscuits, waffles, cereal, yogurt, ice cream, and definitely pizza. Gives everything in your kitchen a small kick of sweet heat flavor without burning your mouth. I have told many of my friends about this magical elixir and they all agree â€” this is the BEST specialty honey any of us have ever had. Donâ€™t hesitate to buy it. It is absolutely wonderful stuff. I most HIGHLY recommended!" â€”Jeff R. ClowGet it from Amazon for $6.99. | AmazonPromising review: "Throw out the others, this is the one. I have a drawer full of wine pour spouts of varying designs. Some don't fit all bottles, some leak while pouring, and some are so tall that storing upright in a refrigerator is difficult and none seal completely. This spout/stopper seals completely and lets you lay the bottle on its side. The aerator allows air to move back into the bottle while pouring to avoid the 'glug glug' effect of other pour spouts. The strainer may filter large cork pieces, but is not fine enough for sediment. The portion of the corker that fits inside the bottle has fit every bottle I've tried it in, from standard size bottles to the larger 1.5 liter bottles. It appears to be made from a flexible material that doesn't add any unwanted taste to the wine. " â€”Jack DallasGet it from Amazon for $5.33. | AmazonPromising review: "I purchased this product to clean those little spaces in my car filled with random crumbs from my husband and dog hair, and it works amazing. Picked up everything and didnâ€™t leave a residue. The lemon scent was faint and didnâ€™t overpower the vehicle while I was cleaning it. But this definitely got in all the little nooks and crannies." â€”KimberlyGet it from Amazon for $7.99. | amazon.com, amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Another satisfied customer here. I developed some ugly coffee stains on my two front teeth earlier this summer. I could not get them off with regular brushing and they were making me very self-conscious. I found this product and, after less than a week, the stains are completely gone. Great product!" â€”laurapghGet it from Amazon for $9.99. | AmazonPromising review: "Love this little spoon! It fits perfectly on the edge of my coffee mug. Now, I no longer have to go searching for a spoon to stir my morning coffee! Since it sits on the edge of the cup my fingers don't get sticky from a wet handle. Plus, it's absolutely adorable and makes me think of my own kitty while I'm away at work. This spoon has become an essential part of my morning routine." â€”Brianna S.Get it from Amazon for $1.59. | amazon.com, amazon.comCheck out a BuzzFeeder's review on this incredible journal!Promising review: "I've been writing in this little journal for three years now and already bought a second one just to make sure I can continue this wonderful habit into a new volume. The quality of this journal is excellent: The creators obviously put some thought into how much use it would be getting. I'm especially pleased with the paper. I tend to press really hard when I'm writing, but the ink doesn't show through on the other side at all. Highly recommended! Get a few, as you'll probably want to give some away." â€”EdTech-LibrarianGet it from Amazon for $10.17. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedRead a BuzzFeeder's experience with this fabulous winged eyeliner stamp (#3).Promising review: "I just want to make my morning routine as easy as possible. I love winged liner, but I donâ€™t have the steady hand for it without mistakes. This makes the perfect and consistent wing every time. Love it!." â€”Julie BGet it from Amazon for $13.97. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I love this cute little makeup spatula! It's so convenient and useful. If you're a makeup/product junkie that doesn't like wasting, (like I am), this is the perfect problem solver for those empty bottles with product still caked on the inner walls. It's long too, so it works in just about any bottle or jar. I only bought one and I use it for everything. It's washable, so it will last you a long time. Great gift for a makeup artist, if they don't already have one!" â€”Samantha VillaGet it from Amazon for $5.99.

Title Headline: BTS Hung Out With Ariana Grande And Five Other K-Pop Headlines You Need To Read This Week
Short Description Sub Headline: New friends, nominations, and tours galore!
Content Body: Music | BTS Hung Out With Ariana Grande And Five Other K-Pop Headlines You Need To Read This Week | New friends, nominations, and tours galore! | Posted on January 24, 2020, 18:21 GMT | January 24, 2020, 18:21 GMT | Sarah HanBuzzFeed Staff | Emlyn TravisBuzzFeed Staff | | ë°©íƒ„ì†Œë…„ë‹¨@BTS_twt | ë°©íƒ„ì†Œë…„ë‹¨ | @BTS_twt | ìš°ì‹ì”¨ SAG ìƒ ì¶•í•˜í•´ | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Amoeba Culture / Via youtube.com, JYP EntertainmentChen and Dynamic Duo first collaborated in 2017 on the song "Nosedive."Step Out of ClÃ© has two English tracks, "Double Knot" (for which they released a performance video!) and "Levanter," which were previously released in Korean off of their album ClÃ©: Levanter. They're also about to kick off the US leg of their District 9: Unlock tour next week, which you can get tickets for here! | Yuehua Entertainment, Source Music / Via youtube.com, BlockBerry CreativeGfriend released the track list (featuring two tracks written by BTS' mastermind and CEO of Big Hit Entertainment, Hitman Bang â€” ICYMI, Big Hit acquired Gfriend's label last year) and a trailer titled "A Tale of the Glass Bead:Previous Story" for their upcoming album, Labyrinth. Ahead of the release of their first mini-album, Reminisce (which you can preorder on MyMusicTaste), on Feb. 3, Everglow announced their first US tour, the Everlasting Tour in USA! The five-date tour includes stops at Dallas, Atlanta, Chicago, Jersey City, and Los Angeles. Tickets have yet to go on sale, but we'll let you know as soon as they do. Loona unveiled the track list for their upcoming mini-album, #. They also opened their own TikTok channel!And the gifts continue, because (G)I-dle unveiled their 2020 I-land World Tour this week too! Stay tuned for deets!P.S. Dreamcatcher's main vocalist, Siyeon, will release a solo single on Jan. 29, ahead of a full group comeback (that's currently in the works).
